{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Sweden", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Sweden}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name               = [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2020 coronavirus pandemic]] in [[Sweden]]\n| map1               = COVID-19_Outbreak_Cases_in_Sweden_by_Number_with_Legend.svg\n| legend1            = {{Center|Map of confirmed cases in Sweden<br />(absolute numbers)<ref name=\"FHM_Official_stats\"/>}}\n| origin             = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], [[China]]\n| disease            = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain       = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location           = [[Sweden]]\n| first_case         = [[J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping]]\n| arrival_date       = 24 January 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=01|day1=24|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| date               = 21 April\n| deaths             = 1,765<ref name=\"FHM_Official_stats\"/>\n| confirmed_cases    = 15,322<ref name=\"FHM_Official_stats\"/>\n| hospitalized_cases = 1,158<ref name=\"FHM_Official_stats\"/>\n| website            = [https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/smittskydd-beredskap/utbrott/aktuella-utbrott/covid-19/ Swedish Public Health Agency Covid-19]<br />(''in Swedish'')\n}}\n<!-- General overview -->\nThe [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic|ongoing pandemic]] of [[COVID-19|coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19), caused by [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]] (SARS-CoV-2), was confirmed to have reached [[Sweden]] on 31 January 2020, when a woman returning from [[Wuhan]] tested positive. On 26 February, following outbreaks [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|in Italy]] and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iran|in Iran]], multiple travel-related clusters appeared in Sweden. [[Transmission (medicine)#Definition and related terms|Community transmission]] was confirmed on 9 March in the [[Stockholm Regional Council|Stockholm region]]. Since then, individuals in every [[Counties of Sweden|l\u00e4n (county)]] have tested positive for COVID-19. The first death was reported on 11 March in [[Stockholm]], a case of community transmission.\n<!-- References in main text, not lead--><!-- Restrictions -->\n\nSweden has, unlike many other countries, not applied any [[lockdown]], with most measures being voluntary. The [[Swedish Constitution|Swedish constitution]] prohibits [[Ministerstyre|ministerial rule]] and mandates that the relevant government body, here an expert agency \u2014 the [[Public Health Agency of Sweden|Public Health Agency]] \u2014 must initiate all actions to prevent the virus, making [[State epidemiologist (Sweden)|state epidemiologist]] [[Anders Tegnell]] a central figure in the crisis. The government can follow agency recommendations, as it has with legislation limiting [[freedom of assembly]], temporarily banning gatherings of over 50 individuals, banning people from visiting nursing homes, as well as physically closing [[secondary school]]s and [[University|universities]].<!--Reference in text--> Primary schools have remained open, in part to avoid healthcare workers staying home with their children.<!-- References in main text, not lead--><!-- Recommendations and health care changes -->\n\nThe Public Health Agency and government issued recommendations to: if possible, work from home; avoid unnecessary travel within the country; to engage in [[social distancing]]; and for people above 70 to stay at home, as much as possible. Those with even minimal symptoms which could be COVID-19, are recommended to stay home. The '[[Sick leave#Sweden|''karensdag'']]' or initial day without paid [[Sick leave|sick-leave]] has been removed by the government and the length of time one can stay home with pay without a doctor's note has been raised from 7 to 21 days.<!-- References in main text, not lead--><!-- Case number-->\n\n{{As of|2020|4|20|df=EU}}, there were 14,777 confirmed cases, of which 1,133 received intensive care, and 1,580 deaths related to the newly found virus in Sweden, with [[Stockholm County]] being the most affected.<ref name=\"FHM_Official_stats\">{{Cite web|url=https://experience.arcgis.com/experience/09f821667ce64bf7be6f9f87457ed9aa|title=Antal fall av covid-19 i Sverige - data uppdateras dagligen kl 11.30|last=|first=|date=2020-03-30|website=Public Health Agency of Sweden \u2014 Official statistics at arcgis|publisher=[[Public Health Agency of Sweden]] (Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten)|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-09|layurl=https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/smittskydd-beredskap/utbrott/aktuella-utbrott/covid-19/aktuellt-epidemiologiskt-lage/|laysource=Antal fall av covid-19 \u2014 Statistik \u2013 antal fall covid-19|language=Swedish|quote=\"Data updated daily at 11:30 [CET]\"}}</ref><!-- Reference added for statement that is subject to frequent change-->\n\n==Background==\n{{Further|2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic#History}}\nOn 12 January, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] (nCoV) was the cause of a [[COVID-19|respiratory illness]] in a cluster of people in [[Wuhan]], in [[Hubei|Hubei province]], [[China]], who had initially come to the WHO's attention on 31 December 2019. This cluster was initially linked to the [[Huanan Seafood Wholesale Market]] in Wuhan City.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> A few days later, on 16 January, the [[Swedish Public Health Agency]] issued a press release highlighting the discovery of the novel coronavirus, and the agency monitoring the situation. The risk of spread to Sweden was described as \"very low\" as there was yet no evidence that the virus [[transmission (medicine)|could spread between humans]], but they recommended that individuals developing [[cough]] or [[fever]] after visiting Wuhan should seek medical care, and asked for healthcare professionals to be observant.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/januari/nytt-coronavirus-upptackt-i-kina/|title=Nytt coronavirus uppt\u00e4ckt i Kina \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAfter the World Health Organization classified the novel Coronavirus as a [[Public Health Emergency of International Concern]] on 30 January and demanded that all member states should cooperate to prevent further spread of the virus, the Agency requested for the Swedish government to classify the novel disease as a [[notifiable disease|notifiable infectious disease]] in the [[Notifiable diseases in Sweden|Swedish Communicable Diseases Act]] as both [[Notifiable diseases in Sweden#List of notifiable diseases|dangerous to public health]] (allm\u00e4nfarlig) and [[Notifiable diseases in Sweden#List of notifiable diseases|dangerous to society]] (samh\u00e4llsfarlig), where [[contact tracing]] is required,<ref name=fhmpress200131>{{cite web |title=Utbrottet av nytt coronavirus kr\u00e4ver samordnade insatser internationellt \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten |url=https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/januari/utbrottet-av-nytt-coronavirus-kraver-samordnade-insatser-internationellt/ |website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se |accessdate=5 April 2020 |language=sv |date=30 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten f\u00f6resl\u00e5r att nytt coronavirus tas upp i smittskyddslagen \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten |url=https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/januari/folkhalsomyndigheten-foreslar-att-nytt-coronavirus-tas-upp-i-smittskyddslagen/ |website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se |accessdate=1 April 2020 |language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Blohm |first1=Lisa |title=Coronavirus p\u00e5 v\u00e4g klassas som samh\u00e4llsfarligt |url=https://www.dagensmedicin.se/artiklar/2020/01/31/coronavirus-pa-vag-klassas-som-samhallsfarligt/ |website=Dagens Medicin |accessdate=1 April 2020 |language=sv}}</ref> giving the disease the same legislative status as [[Ebola]], [[SARS]] and [[Smallpox]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Anm\u00e4lningspliktiga sjukdomar \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten |url=https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/smittskydd-beredskap/overvakning-och-rapportering/anmalningspliktiga-sjukdomar/ |website=www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se |accessdate=12 April 2020 |language=sv |date=3 March 2020}}</ref> The agency also announced that they have [[COVID-19 testing|analysing methods]] that can diagnose a case of the novel disease \u2018within hours\u2019 after testing, and that such tests had already been carried out, but that all had turned out negative.<ref name=fhmpress200131 />\n\n===Preparedness===\nIn the [[Global Health Security Index|2019 Global Health Security Index]] published by the [[Johns Hopkins Center for Health Security]], Sweden was considered to be one of the \u2018most prepared\u2019 countries in the world for an epidemic or a pandemic, ranking 7th overall. Sweden was considered to be among the countries most capable of preventing the emergence of a new pathogen, early detection of an epidemic and reporting an epidemic of international concern and having a low risk environment. However, the [[Healthcare in Sweden|Swedish health system]] received a lower score, questioning if it was sufficient and robust enough to treat the sick and protect health workers.<ref>{{cite web |title=GHS Index: Findings and Recommendations |url=https://www.ghsindex.org/ |accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nBefore the outbreak of the new coronavirus, Sweden had a relatively low [[List of countries by hospital beds|number of hospital beds per capita]], with 2.2 beds per 1000 people (2017),<ref>{{cite web|title=Health Care Resources|url=http://stats.oecd.org/index.aspx?DataSetCode=HEALTH_REAC#|website=stats.oecd.org|accessdate=17 October 2017}}</ref> and [[List of countries by hospital beds#Numbers|intensive care unit (ICU) beds per capita]] of 5.8 per 100.000 people.<ref name=\"Rhodes2012\">{{Cite journal |last=Rhodes |first=A. |last2=Ferdinande |first2=P. |last3=Flaatten |first3=H. |last4=Guidet |first4=B. |last5=Metnitz |first5=P. G. |last6=Moreno |first6=R. P. |date=2012-10-01 |title=The variability of critical care bed numbers in Europe |journal=Intensive Care Medicine |language=en |volume=38 |issue=10 |pages=1647\u20131653 |doi=10.1007/s00134-012-2627-8 |pmid=22777516 |issn=1432-1238|doi-access=free }}</ref> Both numbers were lower than most countries' in the [[European Union|EU]]. The total number of ICU beds in Swedish hospitals was 526.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Frejdeman |first1=Hannah |title=\u201dEfterrapportering att v\u00e4nta efter helgen\u201d |url=https://www.svd.se/just-nu-folkhalsomyndigheten-haller-presstraff |website=Svenska Dagbladet |language=sv |date=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Sweden medical cases chart}}\n<!-- NOTICE\nGraph is to wide. Keep in mind that the page displays differently depending on platform. Either make it less wide, or let the line break below stay in place. \n-->\n{{clear}}\n<!-- NOTICE\n     Keep this section short!\n     Sections below are\n     more detailed.\n     Minor details can\n     be added to the\n     timeline below! -->\nOn 31 January, the first Swedish case was confirmed in a woman in [[J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping]] who had travelled to Sweden from Wuhan on 24 January directly from Wuhan. The case was fully isolated and there are no reports of further spread.<ref name=\"fhm0226\" /><ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gp.se/1.24829340|title=F\u00f6rsta svenska coronafallet kliniskt frisk|last=Abrahamsson|first=Anders|date=3 March 2020|website=gp.se|language=sv|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref> The second case was diagnosed at [[Sahlgrenska University Hospital]], [[Gothenburg]] on 26 February, after a man who had recently returned from northern [[Italy]] following the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|COVID-19 outbreak in Italy]] had developed symptoms.<ref name=\"bolin1\">{{Cite news|last=Bolin|first=Mattias|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/vast/bekraftat-coronafall-i-goteborg-person-vardas-pa-sahlgrenska|title=Bekr\u00e4ftat coronafall i G\u00f6teborg \u2013 person v\u00e5rdas p\u00e5 Sahlgrenska|date=26 February 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=26 February 2020|language=sv}}</ref><ref name=\"fhm0226\">{{cite web|url=https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/nytt-bekraftat-fall-av-covid-19/|title=Nytt bekr\u00e4ftat fall av covid-19|date=26 February 2020|website=Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|language=sv|trans-title=New confirmed case of covid-19|url-status=live|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> With five additional cases confirmed on 27 February,<ref>https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/inbjudan-till-presstraff-ytterligare-fall-av-covid-19-i-flera-regioner2/</ref> the Swedish Public Health Agency ('''Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten''<nowiki/>') put out a statement that these cases were all related to travel to high-risk zones and that there was no evidence of [[Transmission (medicine)|community transmission]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/inbjudan-till-presstraff-ytterligare-fall-av-covid-19-i-flera-regioner2/|title=Inbjudan till presstr\u00e4ff: Ytterligare fall av covid-19 i flera regioner \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref> Disease control measures, including extensive [[contact tracing]] turned up over 200 travel-related cases in the following weeks, all with connection to confirmed cases or travel to high risk regions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/snabbkollen/30-40-i-karantan-pa-stockholmssjukhus|title=M\u00f6jliga fall av inhemsk smitta|date=9 March 2020|website=svt.se|url-status=live|access-date=27 March 2020|language=sv|trans-title=Possible cases of domestic infection}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 February, [[Uppsala County]] confirmed its first case in a woman with a travel history to Germany, where she had met with an Italian colleague, and had been admitted to [[Uppsala University Hospital]]<ref name=\"Via TT\">{{cite web|url=https://via.tt.se/embedded/release/patient-med-bekraftat-coronavirus-vardas-pa-akademiska?publisherId=3235664&releaseId=3271133|title=Via TT|website=via.tt.se|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> after seeking medical attention with flu-like symptoms. [[Halland County|Halland]], [[Norrbotten County|Norrbotten]], [[S\u00f6dermanland County|S\u00f6dermanland]], [[V\u00e4sterbotten County|V\u00e4sterbotten]] and [[\u00d6sterg\u00f6tland County|\u00d6sterg\u00f6tland]] all confirmed their first cases on 9 March.,<ref name=\"news - Region Halland\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.regionhalland.se/nyheter/ett-bekraftat-fall-i-halland-av-coronavirus/|title=news - Region Halland|website=www.regionhalland.se|access-date=9 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Bekr\u00e4ftat fall av coronavirus i S\u00f6r\">{{cite web|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/sormland/bekraftat-fall-av-coronavirus-i-sormland|title=Bekr\u00e4ftat fall av coronavirus i S\u00f6rmland|last=|first=|date=|website=SVT|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref name=\"SVT9\">{{cite news|last1=Larsson|first1=Erica|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/norrbotten/forsta-coronafallet-i-norrbotten|title=F\u00f6rsta coronafallet konstaterat i Norrbotten|date=9 March 2020|access-date=11 March 2020|publisher=Sveriges Television|last2=Haupt|first2=Inger|language=Swedish}}</ref><ref name=\"vasterbotten0309\">{{cite web|url=https://www.regionvasterbotten.se/bekraftade-fall-av-coronavirus-i-vasterbotten|title=Bekr\u00e4ftade fall av coronavirus i V\u00e4sterbotten|website=Region V\u00e4sterbotten|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"regionostergotland.se\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.regionostergotland.se/Om-regionen/Pressrum/Nyheter/ett-fall-av-coronavirus-bekraftat-i-ostergotland/|title=Ett fall av coronavirus bekr\u00e4ftat i \u00d6sterg\u00f6taland|website=www.regionostergotland.se|language=sv|access-date=9 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"SVT9\"/> This came as the first cases of community transmission was confirmed among two patients who had sought care at [[Saint G\u00f6ran Hospital|S:t G\u00f6ran Hospital]], [[Stockholm]], on 6 March.<ref name=\"20employees\">{{Cite news|last=Erlandsson|first=\u00c5sa|url=https://www.svd.se/coronasmittad-pa-st-goran--personal-satt-i-karantan|title=20 anst\u00e4llda i karant\u00e4n \u2013 S:t G\u00f6rans i stabsl\u00e4ge|date=9 March 2020|work=Svenska Dagbladet|access-date=9 March 2020|language=sv|trans-title=20 employees in quarantine - S: t G\u00f6rans in staff position|issn=1101-2412}}</ref> They were assumed to have been infected through community transmission approximately 7 days before seeking care.{{Citation needed|date=March 2020}} The following day, [[J\u00e4mtland County|J\u00e4mtland]] and [[V\u00e4sternorrland County|V\u00e4sternorrland]] also confirmed initial cases.<ref name=\"regionjh.se\">{{cite web|url=https://www.regionjh.se/nyheter/pressmeddelanden/rjhpress/enpersonijamtlandslankonstateratsmittadavcoronaviruset.5.55412b91170402c7d222e632.html|title=En person i J\u00e4mtlands l\u00e4n konstaterat smittad av coronaviruset - Region J\u00e4mtland H\u00e4rjedalen|website=regionjh.se|language=sv|access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"rvn.se\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rvn.se/sv/Om-regionen/Aktuellt-i-Region-Vasternorrland/Nyheter/tre-personer-i-vasternorrland-smittade-av-coronaviruset/|title=Tre personer i V\u00e4sternorrland smittade av coronaviruset|website=rvn.se|language=sv|access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nResponding to indications of local transmission in the [[Stockholm county|Stockholm]] area and [[V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland County|V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland]], the Public Health Agency on 10 March raised the risk assessment of community spread from ''moderate'' to ''very high'', which is the highest level.<ref name=\"folkhalsomyndigheten.se\">{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/flera-tecken-pa-samhallsspridning-av-covid-19-i-sverige/|title=Flera tecken p\u00e5 samh\u00e4llsspridning av covid-19 i Sverige \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"folkhalsomyndigheten.se\" /><ref>{{Cite news|last=Stefansson|first=Klara|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/risken-for-coronaspridning-i-sverige-hojs-till-mycket-hog|title=Risken f\u00f6r coronaspridning i Sverige h\u00f6js till \"mycket h\u00f6g\"|date=10 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=10 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/flera-tecken-pa-samhallsspridning-av-covid-19-i-sverige/|title=Flera tecken p\u00e5 samh\u00e4llsspridning av Covid-19 i Sverige|last=|first=|date=|website=Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=10 March 2020|access-date=}}</ref> The first death was reported on 11 March, when a person in their 70s from the Stockholm region died in the intensive care unit of [[Karolinska University Hospital]]. The person was reported to have acquired the virus through community transmission, believed to have occurred about one week before death. The person also belonged to a risk group.<ref name=\":33\">{{Cite news|last=Claesson|first=Frida|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/stockholm/en-person-har-avlidit-av-coronaviruset|title=En person har avlidit till f\u00f6ljd av coronaviruset|date=11 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=11 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref>\n\nThe COVID-19 outbreak, which the World Health Organization (WHO) declared a pandemic on 11 March,<ref name=\"nyt sports\">{{Cite news|last=Deb|first=Sopan|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/11/sports/basketball/warriors-coronavirus-fans.html|title=Sports Leagues Bar Fans and Cancel Games Amid Coronavirus Outbreak|date=11 March 2020|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=12 March 2020|last2=Cacciola|first2=Scott|issn=0362-4331|last3=Stein|first3=Marc}}</ref> has had a disparate impact on different areas of Sweden.\n\nThe Public Health Agency of Sweden declared on 13 March that stopping the spread of Covid-19 has entered a \"new phase\" which requires \"other efforts\". The continued focus is now to delay spread among the population and to protect the elderly and most vulnerable against the disease.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/ny-fas-kraver-nya-insatser-mot-covid-19/|title=Ny fas kr\u00e4ver nya insatser mot covid-19 \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref> The health agency believed that 5-10% of the population in Stockholm County were carrying the virus on 9 April.<ref Name=mellan5och10>{{cite web |last1=Zachrisson |first1=Lotta |title=Tegnell: \"Mellan fem och tio procent b\u00e4r p\u00e5 viruset\" |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/ny-studie-2-5-av-stockholmarna-bar-pa-viruset |website=SVT Nyheter |accessdate=9 April 2020 |language=sv |date=9 April 2020}}</ref> In mid-April, it was reported that out of the approximately 1300 people who had died after having caught the virus, one third had been living at [[nursing home|nursing homes]]. The figure differed between the regions. In Stockholm, the city most affected by the pandemic, half of the deaths had been residents in one of its many nursing homes.<ref name=\"tredjedel\">{{cite web |last1=Larsson |first1=Ylva |title=En tredjedel av alla d\u00f6dsfall fr\u00e5n \u00e4ldreboenden i Sverige |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/en-tredjedel-av-alla-dodsfall-fran-aldreboenden-i-sverige |website=SVT Nyheter |accessdate=18 April 2020 |language=sv |date=16 April 2020}}</ref> The Health Agency saw the spread at the homes as their biggest concern as of then, but \"not as a failure of our overall strategy, but as a failure of our way to protect the elderly\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sundholm |first1=Marianne |title=1 200 d\u00f6da, fr\u00e4mst p\u00e5 \u00e4ldreboenden, men Sverige h\u00e5ller fast vid sin linje: \"Vi forts\u00e4tter, vi har arbetat utifr\u00e5n vad vi tror p\u00e5\" |url=https://svenska.yle.fi/artikel/2020/04/15/1-200-doda-framst-pa-aldreboenden-men-sverige-haller-fast-vid-sin-linje-vi |website=svenska.yle.fi |accessdate=18 April 2020 |language=sv-FI}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u00c4ldreboenden st\u00f6rsta bekymret enligt Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten |url=https://www.dagensmedicin.se/artiklar/2020/04/06/aldreboenden-storsta-bekymret-enligt-folkhalsomyndigheten/ |website=Dagens Medicin |accessdate=18 April 2020 |language=sv}}</ref>. The situation led to the [[Health and Social Care Inspectorate]] to begin carrying out controls at the homes.<ref name=\"tredjedel\" />\n\n==Government policy==\nThe [[Government of Sweden#Present Cabinet|Swedish government]] has tried to focus efforts on encouraging the right behaviour and creating social norms rather than mandatory restrictions. Government officials including [[Prime Minister of Sweden|Swedish prime minister]] [[Stefan L\u00f6fven]], as well as the [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]] have encouraged each individual to take responsibility for their own health and the health of others.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dn.se/nyheter/sverige/ewa-stenberg-lofven-vill-hellre-overtyga-an-forbjuda/|title=Ewa Stenberg: L\u00f6fven vill hellre \u00f6vertyga \u00e4n f\u00f6rbjuda|date=27 March 2020|website=DN.SE|language=sv|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref> The [[Swedish Constitution|Swedish constitution]] mandates that the relevant expert agency, in this case [[Public Health Agency of Sweden|the Public Health Agency]], must issue advice prior to any government actions aiming to prevent the spread of the virus with a strong mandate that the expert agencies should initiate actions, avoiding [[Ministerstyre|rule by ministers]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gp.se/1.26081990|title=\"Vi epidemiologer har f\u00e5tt lite f\u00f6r stor makt\"|last=TT|date=2020-03-28|website=gp.se|language=sv|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> The independence of Swedish agencies and the choice of 'recommendations' instead of legislation has received much coverage in international media.<ref name=\"samtalet8aprilsida4\">{{cite web |title=Samtalet om Sverige 1\u20137 april 2020 |url=https://si.se/app/uploads/2020/04/samtalet-om-sverige-1-7-april-1.pdf |website=www.si.se |accessdate=14 April 2020 |page=4 |language=sv |date=8 April 2020}}</ref> Swedish [[Minister of Foreign Affairs (Sweden)|foreign minister]], [[Ann Linde]] described Sweden as having \u2018rather small ministries, but rather big authorities\u2019 (with the Public Health Agency being one such authority), and this going back 300-400 years, and Sweden being characterized by a very high level of trust in its authorities from both the people and the politicians, and that Swedes had a very strong urge to following recommendations from authorities, thus making legislation largely unnecessary. When asked if Sweden would consider tougher restrictions, L\u00f6fven and Linde both made clear that the Swedish government wouldn't hesitate to do so if deemed necessary and on advice from the expert agencies, but that such measures needed to be taken at the right time, and they believe it's hard to make people adhere to [[lockdown|lockdowns]] for an extended period.<ref name=\"lindecnn\">{{cite web |title=Ann Linde: \u201dFinns m\u00e5nga myter om svenska strategin\u201d |url=https://www.expressen.se/nyheter/ann-linde-finns-manga-myter-om-svenska-strategin/ |website=www.expressen.se |accessdate=14 April 2020 |language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=9359b030-704e-11ea-aa9a-936e6c4209ee&url=L25ld3MvYXJ0aWNsZXMvMjAyMC0wMy0yMi9zd2VkZW4tcHJpbWUtbWluaXN0ZXItc2F5cy1wcmVwYXJlLWZvci1tb3JlLXJlc3RyaWN0aXZlLXBvbGljaWVz|title=Sweden Prime Minister Says Prepare for More Restrictive Policies|last=Rolander|first=Niclas|date=22 March 2020|website=bloomberg.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Government response==\n\n[[File:FHM-Covid-19-Undvik-smitta-a4-engelska-raster.svg|thumb|upright=1.5|In response to COVID-19, the [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]] issued a series of infographics in different languages describing how to protect oneself and others from infection.]]<!--This image is specially made in response to COVID-19, and is general on purpose-->\n===Recommendations===\nOn 10 March, responding to indications of [[Transmission (medicine)#Definition and related terms|community transmission]], the [[Public Health Agency of Sweden|Public Health Agency]] advised everyone with respiratory infection, even mild ones, to refrain from social contacts where there is a risk of spreading the virus, in private as well as working life. They also ask health care staff working with risk groups, including [[nursing home|nursing homes]], not work if they have any symptoms of respiratory infection. Relatives of elderly should also avoid unnecessary visits at hospitals and in facilities for elderly, and never visit if there are any respiratory symptoms.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/flera-tecken-pa-samhallsspridning-av-covid-19-i-sverige/|title=Flera tecken p\u00e5 samh\u00e4llsspridning av covid-19 i Sverige \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Stefansson |first1=Klara |title=Risken f\u00f6r coronaspridning i Sverige h\u00f6js till \"mycket h\u00f6g\" |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/risken-for-coronaspridning-i-sverige-hojs-till-mycket-hog |website=SVT Nyheter |language=sv |date=10 March 2020}}</ref> On 16 March, the agency recommended that people over 70 should limit close contact with other people, and employers should recommend their employees work from home.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/personer-over-70-bor-begransa-sociala-kontakter-tills-vidare/|title=Personer \u00f6ver 70 b\u00f6r begr\u00e4nsa sociala kontakter tills vidare \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se}}</ref> One month later, statistics showed that roughly half the Swedish workforce was now working from home.<ref name=\"guardian1000\">{{cite web |last1=Henley |first1=Jon |last2=correspondent |first2=Europe |title=Critics question Swedish approach as coronavirus death toll reaches 1,000 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/15/sweden-coronavirus-death-toll-reaches-1000 |website=The Guardian |accessdate=15 April 2020 |date=15 April 2020}}</ref> The following day, the agency recommended that secondary schools and universities use distance learning,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/larosaten-och-gymnasieskolor-uppmanas-nu-att-bedriva-distansundervisning/|title=L\u00e4ros\u00e4ten och gymnasieskolor uppmanas nu att bedriva distansundervisning \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se}}</ref> with schools following suit all over the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.svd.se/presstraff-i-dag-med-utbildningsministern|title=L\u00f6fven: Gymnasier ska g\u00e5 \u00f6ver till distansstudier}}</ref>\n\nIn April, many of the organisations running the\u00a0[[public transport|public transport systems]] for the Swedish [[County (Sweden)|counties]] had reported a 50% drop of public transport usage, including Kalmar L\u00e4nstrafik in [[Kalmar County]], [[Sk\u00e5netrafiken]] in [[Sk\u00e5ne County]], [[Storstockholms Lokaltrafik|Stockholm Public Transport]] in [[Stockholm County]], and [[V\u00e4sttrafik]] in [[V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland County]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gunnarsson |first1=Linus |title=Stor minskning av resande med kollektivtrafik i l\u00e4net |url=https://www.kalmarposten.se/article/stor-minskning-av-resande-med-kollektivtrafik-i-lanet/ |website=Kalmarposten |accessdate=15 April 2020 |language=sv-SE |date=15 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ros\u00e9n |first1=Robert |title=Resandet halverat hos Sk\u00e5netrafiken |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/nyheter/a/Op7rjq/resandet-halverat-hos-skanetrafiken |website=Aftonbladet |accessdate=15 April 2020 |language=sv |date=25 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"guardian1000\" /><ref>{{cite web |title=DEBATT. V\u00e4sttrafik tar coronakrisen p\u00e5 allra st\u00f6rsta allvar |url=https://www.expressen.se/gt/debatt-gt/vasttrafik-tar-coronakrisen-pa-allra-storsta-allvar/ |website=www.expressen.se |accessdate=15 April 2020 |language=sv}}</ref> In Stockholm, the streets grew increasingly emptier, with a 30% drop in the number of cars,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hovne |first1=Anders |title=N\u00e4ra var tredje bil borta fr\u00e5n Stockholms gator |url=https://omni.se/nara-var-tredje-bil-borta-fran-stockholms-gator/a/awQ7jL |website=Omni |accessdate=15 April 2020 |language=sv |date=31 March 2020}}</ref> and 70% less pedestrians.<ref name=\"guardian1000\" />\n\nAccording to an analysis of mobile network data from the [[Easter|Easter week]] carried out by [[mobile network operator]] [[Telia]], most Swedes had followed the agency's recommendations to avoid unnecessary travels during the Easter holidays. Overall, travel from the Stockholm region had decreased by 80-90%, and the number of citizens of [[Stockholm]] travelling to popular holiday destinations like [[Gotland]] and the ski resorts in [[\u00c5re]] had fallen with more than 90%. Travel between other regions in Sweden had fallen as well.<ref>{{cite web |title=Stockholmare stannar hemma i p\u00e5sk |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/snabbkollen/stockholmare-stannar-hemma-i-pask |website=SVT Nyheter |accessdate=13 April 2020 |language=sv |date=9 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Svenskarna stannar hemma under p\u00e5sklovet |url=http://press.telia.se/pressreleases/svenskarna-stannar-hemma-under-paasklovet-2990179 |website=Mynewsdesk |accessdate=13 April 2020 |language=sv}}</ref> [[Ferry|Ferry-line]] operator [[Destination Gotland]], who previously had called on their customers to rethink their planned trips for Easter, reported that 85% of all bookings had been rescheduled.<ref>{{cite web |last1=S. Zetterdahl |first1=Christian |title=85 procent har bokat av p\u00e5skresan med Gotlandsf\u00e4rjan |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/ost/85-procent-har-bokat-av-resan-med-gotlandsfarjan |website=SVT Nyheter |accessdate=13 April 2020 |language=sv |date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Rules and legislation===\nOn 11 March, the same day as the first Swedish death to COVID-19, the Swedish government passed a new law, limiting [[freedom of assembly]] by temporarily banning all gatherings larger than 500 people, with threat of fine and prison.<ref name=\":34\">{{Cite news|last=V. Nyheter|first=S.|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/snabbkollen/regeringen-stoppar-stora-moten|title=Regeringen stoppar stora m\u00f6ten|date=11 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=11 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref> The ban will apply until further notice.<ref name=\"Klart\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gp.se/nyheter/sverige/klart-inga-evenemang-med-fler-%C3%A4n-500-bes%C3%B6kare-1.25224161|title=Klart: Inga evenemang med fler \u00e4n 500 bes\u00f6kare|date=11 March 2020|website=gp.se|language=sv|trans-title=Clear: No events with more than 500 visitors}}</ref>\nOn 27 March the government announced that gatherings of more than 50 people were banned.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.krisinformation.se/nyheter/2020/mars/ytterligare-begransning-sammankomster|title=F\u00f6rbud mot allm\u00e4nna sammankomster med fler \u00e4n 50 personer|date=2020-03-27|access-date=2020-03-28|language=sv}}</ref><ref name=\"SVD50people\">{{cite web |url=https://www.svd.se/stefan-lofven-och-rikspolischefen-haller-presstraff/ |title=Sammankomster p\u00e5 \u00f6ver 50 personer f\u00f6rbjuds |first1=Hanna| last1=Frejdeman |date=27 March 2020 |website= |publisher=SvD |access-date=27 March 2020 |quote= |language=Swedish}}</ref>\n\nAgain, on the 11th of March, the karensdag, the unpaid first day of sick leave, was temporarily discontinued in an effort to encourage people to stay home if they were experiencing symptoms that are consistent with COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.se/20200311/sweden-changes-sick-pay-rules-to-help-fight-coronavirus|title=Sweden Changes Sick Pay Rules to Help Fight CoronaVirus|last=|first=|date=|website=thelocal.se|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref> On 13 March, the government decided to temporarily abolish the demand of a doctor's certificate for 14 days for people staying home from work due to illness (i.e. sick pay period). Previously a doctor's certificate was needed after seven days.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Olsson|first=Jonas|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/regeringen-kravet-pa-lakarintyg-vid-sjukdom-avskaffas|title=Regeringen: Kravet p\u00e5 sjukintyg avskaffas tillf\u00e4lligt|date=13 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=13 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March 2020, the government introduced new restrictions to bars and restaurants requiring all service to be table service only. Restaurants were also recommended increase the space between the tables. Venues that do not adhere to the new restrictions could be shut down.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Larsson|first=Ylva|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/nya-forbudet-endast-bordsservering-tillats-pa-restauranger-och-barer|title=Nya restriktioner: Endast bordsservering till\u00e5ts p\u00e5 restauranger och barer|date=2020-03-24|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=2020-03-27|language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/nya-forbudet-endast-bordsservering-tillats-pa-restauranger-och-barer|title=Nya restriktioner: Endast bordsservering till\u00e5ts p\u00e5 restauranger och barer|date=24 March 2020|language=sv|accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nBeginning on 1 April, all private visits to nursing homes was outlawed by the government. Many [[Municipality (Sweden)|municipalities]] had already forbidden such visits. The national ban was however general, and those in charge of the facilities would be able to make exceptions under special circumstances, provided that the risk of spread of the virus was low.<ref>{{cite web |title=Nationellt bes\u00f6ksf\u00f6rbud p\u00e5 \u00e4ldreboenden |url=https://www.lidkopingsnytt.nu/2020/03/31/nationellt-besoksforbud-pa-aldreboenden/ |website=Lidk\u00f6pingsnytt |accessdate=12 April 2020 |language=sv |date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Travel restrictions===\nThe government has issued progressively stricter advisories against travel. Beginning on 17 February, the [[Ministry for Foreign Affairs (Sweden)|Swedish Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] advised against all trips to [[Hubei Province]], [[China]], as well as non-essential travel to the rest of [[China]] apart from [[Hong Kong]] and [[Macao]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regeringen.se/uds-reseinformation/ud-avrader/kina---avradan/|title=Kina - avr\u00e5dan|last=Regeringskansliet|first=Regeringen och|date=26 January 2020|website=Regeringskansliet|language=sv|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dn.se/nyheter/varlden/ud-stramar-at-rekommendationerna-for-resor-till-kina/|title=UD stramar \u00e5t rekommendationerna f\u00f6r resor till Kina|date=2020-02-17|website=DN.SE|language=sv|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\nOn 2 March the Ministry for Foreign Affairs advised against trips to [[Iran]], due to the uncontrolled spread of the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|Covid-19]] in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regeringen.se/uds-reseinformation/ud-avrader/iran---avradan/|title=Iran - avr\u00e5dan|last=Regeringskansliet|first=Regeringen och|date=27 February 2020|website=Regeringskansliet|language=sv|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref> The [[Swedish Transport Agency]] also revoked [[Iran Air]]'s permit for Iranian flights to land in Sweden from the same date.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Andersson|first=Jane|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/skane/inga-sarskilda-coronakontroller-pa-kastrup|title=Inga flyg med Iran Air till Kastrup|date=3 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=15 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regeringen.se/uds-reseinformation/ud-avrader/iran---avradan/|title=Iran - avr\u00e5dan|last=Regeringskansliet|first=Regeringen och|date=2020-02-27|website=Regeringskansliet|language=sv|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> According to the foreign ministry, there were several thousands Swedish citizens in Iran at the time of the ban, many of them with difficulties getting back to Sweden.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Param |first1=Babak |last2=Axelsson |first2=Staffan |title=Svenskar fast i Iran \u2013 \u201dIngen fr\u00e5n Sverige har s\u00f6kt mig\u201d |url=https://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=83&artikel=7418320 |website=Sveriges Radio |accessdate=12 April 2020 |language=sv}}</ref> On 6 March, the Ministry for Foreign Affairs advised against all non-necessary trips to northern [[Italy]], specifically the regions of [[Piedmont|Piemonte]], [[Liguria]], [[Lombardy|Lombardia]], [[Emilia-Romagna]], [[Trentino-Alto Adige/S\u00fcdtirol|Trentino-Alto Adige]], [[Aosta Valley|Valle d'Aosta]], [[Veneto]], [[Friuli Venezia Giulia]], [[Marche]] and [[Tuscany|Toscana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regeringen.se/uds-reseinformation/ud-avrader/italien---avradan/|title=Italien - avr\u00e5dan|last=Regeringskansliet|first=Regeringen och|date=6 March 2020|website=Regeringskansliet|language=sv|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref> [[Turin]], [[Milan]], [[Venice]], [[Verona]], [[Trieste]] and [[Florence]] are large cities in these regions. The [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]], who initiated the recommendation for the Ministry for Foreign Affairs, states that the decision is based solely on the strain of the Italian health care system.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/folkhalsomyndigheten-har-rekommenderat-avradan-fran-resor-till-norra-italien/|title=Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten har rekommenderat avr\u00e5dan fr\u00e5n resor till norra Italien \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> On similar grounds, the foreign affairs ministry also advised against all non-necessary travel to the city of [[Daegu]] and the province of [[North Gyeongsang Province|Gyeongbuk]] in [[South Korea]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regeringen.se/uds-reseinformation/ud-avrader/sydkorea---avradan/|title=Sydkorea - avr\u00e5dan|last=Regeringskansliet|first=Regeringen och|date=6 March 2020|website=Regeringskansliet|language=sv|access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> The advice regarding travels to Italy was extended 10 March to include all of its regions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regeringen.se/uds-reseinformation/ud-avrader/italien---avradan/|title=Italien - avr\u00e5dan|last=Regeringskansliet|first=Regeringen och|date=2020-03-10|website=Regeringskansliet|language=sv|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> Finally, all international travel was discouraged on 14 March. The advice was to be in place for one month, after which it would be up for review.<ref name=exceptionelltlage>{{cite web |last1=Karlsson |first1=Amanda |title=UD om strandade svenskarna: \"Exceptionellt l\u00e4ge\" |url=https://www.bohuslaningen.se/nyheter/v%C3%A4rlden/ud-om-strandade-svenskarna-exceptionellt-l%C3%A4ge-1.26027863 |website=bohuslaningen.se |accessdate=12 April 2020 |language=sv |date=27 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Makar|first=Maria|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/coronaviruset-ud-avrader-fran-icke-nodvandiga-resor-till-alla-lander|title=Coronaviruset \u2013 UD avr\u00e5der fr\u00e5n icke n\u00f6dv\u00e4ndiga resor till alla l\u00e4nder|date=2020-03-14|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=2020-03-27|language=sv}}</ref> Travel from non-[[European Union|EU]]/[[European Economic Area|EEA]] member states was stopped on 17 March<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regeringen.se/artiklar/2020/03/fragor-och-svar--inresestopp-till-eu-via-sverige/|title=Fr\u00e5gor och svar \u2013 inresef\u00f6rbud till EU via Sverige|last=Regeringskansliet|first=Regeringen och|date=2020-03-17|website=Regeringskansliet|language=sv|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> and unnecessary travel within Sweden was advised against on 19 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.krisinformation.se/nyheter/2020/mars/tank-over-om-resan-ar-nodvandig|title=Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten: T\u00e4nk \u00f6ver om resan verkligen \u00e4r n\u00f6dv\u00e4ndig|website=krisinformation.se|language=sv|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/mars/tank-over-om-resan-verkligen-ar-nodvandig|title=T\u00e4nk \u00f6ver om resan verkligen \u00e4r n\u00f6dvandig|date=19 March 2020|language=sv|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe foreign ministry estimated that between 40,000 and 60,000 Swedes were stranded abroad in late March.<ref name=exceptionelltlage /><ref name=tiotusentalsstrandadesvenskar>{{cite web |author1=Emma Bouvin |author2=Karin Eriksson |title=Tiotusentals strandade svenskar v\u00e4djar om hj\u00e4lp att komma hem - DN.SE |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328103701/https://www.dn.se/nyheter/sverige/tiotusentals-strandade-svenskar-vadjar-om-hjalp-att-komma-hem/ |website=web.archive.org |accessdate=12 April 2020 |date=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 April, the foreign ministry extended the advice against all non-essential travel abroad until 15 June, when it would again be reconsidered.<ref>{{cite web |title=Utlandsresor \u2013 f\u00f6rl\u00e4ngd avr\u00e5dan fr\u00e5n icke n\u00f6dv\u00e4ndiga resor till alla l\u00e4nder |url=https://www.regeringen.se/pressmeddelanden/2020/04/utlandsresor--forlangd-avradan-fran-icke-nodvandiga-resor-till-alla-lander |website=Regeringskansliet och Regeringskansliet |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=sv |date=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Economics===\nIn mid-March, the government proposed a 300 billion [[Swedish krona|SEK]] (\u20ac27bn) emergency package to reduce the economic impact of the crisis. The proposal included a system with a reduction in [[working time|work hours]] where the government will pay half to salary, aiming to help businesses stay afloat without having to do layoffs. Further, the government would pay the employer's expenses for any [[sick leave]]s, which is normally shared between the employer and the state.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Liljestr\u00f6m |first1=Elias |url=https://www.thelocal.se/20200317/what-does-the-coronavirus-mean-for-swedish-economy |title=What does the coronavirus mean for the Swedish economy?|website=thelocal.se |accessdate=5 April 2020 |date=17 March 2020}}</ref> The normal costs of employer contributions have also been temporarily discontinued for small business owners. This will save small businesses approximately 5000 SEK per employee each month but will result in a loss of tax revenue of 33 billion SEK.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dn.se/nyheter/sverige/nytt-krispaket-presenteras-av-regeringen/|title=Tillf\u00e4lligt slopad arbetsgivaravgift i nytt krispaket|date=25 March 2020|website=DN.SE|language=sv|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref> The budget emergency package proposed by the government in mid-March to lessen the economic impact of the crisis was supported across the political spectrum, including all parties in opposition in the [[Riksdag]]. It was also welcomed by [[trade union]]s as well as the private and business sectors. However, some union representatives stressed that 'it won't be enough', a view shared by the biggest [[employer's organisation]], the [[Confederation of Swedish Enterprise]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Larsson |first1=Thomas |title=Oppositionen sluter upp bakom regeringens st\u00f6dpaket |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/ekonomi/oppositionen-sluter-upp-bakom-regeringens-stodpaket |website=SVT Nyheter |language=sv |date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nLocal governments, such as the [[G\u00e4vle kommun|municipal government in G\u00e4vle]], have applied measures to businesses delaying the payment of invoices until September 1, 2020 at the earliest and deferring rent payments.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gavle.se/service-och-information/information-om-coronaviruset/foretag-och-naringsliv-gallande-coronaviruset/|title=F\u00f6retag och n\u00e4ringsliv \u2013 coronaviruset|work=G\u00e4vle kommun|access-date=2020-03-27|language=sv-SE}}</ref>\nOn 2 April, the [[Financial Supervisory Authority (Sweden)|Financial Supervisory Authority]] ('''Finansinspektionen''<nowiki/>') decided that Swedish banks temporarily can allow exemptions for housing mortgage lenders regarding amortizing of loans.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fi.se/sv/publicerat/pressmeddelanden/2020/banker-far-ge-alla-bolanetagare-undantag-fran-amortering/|title=Banker f\u00e5r ge alla bol\u00e5netagare undantag fr\u00e5n amortering - Finansinspektionen|website=fi.se|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n\n==Response from the public healthcare system==\n\n===Testing===\nThe first tests were carried out in January, and according to the [[Swedish Public Health Agency]], \u2018around twenty tests\u2019 had already been carried out before the first positive case was confirmed on 30 January.<ref name=fhmpress200131 /> The agency considered that all individuals who developed any symptoms of disease in the respiratory tract after visiting [[Wuhan]] should be tested, even those with less severe symptoms.<ref name=\"annuingacoronafall\">{{cite web |last1=Cederberg |first1=Jesper |title=\u00c4nnu inga coronafall i Sverige |url=https://lakartidningen.se/Aktuellt/Nyheter/2020/01/Annu-inga-coronafall-i-Sverige/ |website=L\u00e4kartidningen |accessdate=12 April 2020 |language=sv-SE |date=27 January 2020}}</ref> The Public Health Agency expanded testing for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|Covid-19]] on 4 March beyond only those who have been in risk areas abroad, to also test cases of pneumonia without known cause.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Thomsen|first=Dante|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/nu-ska-fler-svenskar-testas-for-coronavirus|title=Nu ska fler svenskar testas f\u00f6r coronavirus|date=4 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=7 March 2020|language=sv}}</ref>\n\nInitially, all tests were carried out at the agency's [[Public Health Agency of Sweden#High-containment laboratory|high-containment laboratory]] in [[Solna]]. But in mid-February, in order to increase testing capacity and allow for faster test results, testing also began at the [[Medical laboratory|clinical medical laboratories]] in [[Sahlgrenska University Hospital|G\u00f6teborg]], [[Halmstad]], [[Sk\u00e5ne University Hospital|Lund]], [[Sk\u00f6vde]], [[Stockholm]], [[Norrland University Hospital|Ume\u00e5]] and [[University Hospital|Uppsala]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pramsten |first1=Sara |title=Fler labb f\u00e5r m\u00f6jlighet att analysera coronavirus |url=https://lakartidningen.se/Aktuellt/Nyheter/2020/02/Fler-labb-far-mojlighet-att-analysera-Coronavirus/# |website=L\u00e4kartidningen |publisher=L\u00e4kartidningen F\u00f6rlag AB |accessdate=12 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308211841/https://lakartidningen.se/Aktuellt/Nyheter/2020/02/Fler-labb-far-mojlighet-att-analysera-Coronavirus/ |archivedate=8 March 2020 |language=sv-SE |date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nBetween 27 March and 3 April, the health agency tested approximately 800 randomly selected individuals in Stockholm County, to seek knowledge of the then current infection rate.<ref name=\"Resultat fr\u00e5n unders\u00f6kning av f\u00f6rek\">{{cite web |title=Resultat fr\u00e5n unders\u00f6kning av f\u00f6rekomsten av covid-19 i region Stockholm \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten |url=https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/april/resultat-fran-undersokning-av-forekomsten-av-covid-19-i-region-stockholm/ |website=www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se |accessdate=9 April 2020 |language=sv |format=Press release |date=9 April 2020}}</ref> \nAs it was estimated that Stockholm County by then had the highest infection rate in Sweden, the agency choose to focus on that region.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hansson |first1=Anna |title=Tester ska visa coronakurvan i Sverige |url=https://www.nyteknik.se/samhalle/tester-ska-visa-coronakurvan-i-sverige-6991681 |website=Ny Teknik |accessdate=10 April 2020 |language=sv |date=24 March 2020}}</ref> According to the results, 2.5% of the local population were carrying the virus in the upper respiratory tract during the surveyed period.<ref name=\"Resultat fr\u00e5n unders\u00f6kning av f\u00f6rek\"/>\nBased on the study and a [[doubling time]] of 6-7 days, the agency concluded that 5-10% of the population in the region were carrying the virus on 9 April.<ref Name=mellan5och10 />\n\nAt the end of March, the number of tests carried out each week numbered 10.000.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bergendorff |first1=Johan |title=Tegnell: Mer testning skulle skydda \u00e4ldre b\u00e4ttre |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/vetenskap/tegnell-mer-testning-skulle-skydda-aldre-battre |website=SVT Nyheter |accessdate=12 April 2020 |language=sv |date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Capacity===\nThe [[Stockholm International Fairs]], Stockholmsm\u00e4ssan, are being converted into a field hospital with the help of the [[Swedish Army|Swedish Defence Forces]]. The field hospital will be able to house 600 seriously and critically sick patients.<ref name=\"stockholmsmassan\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dn.se/sthlm/har-byggs-stockholmsmassan-om-till-sjukhus/|title=H\u00e4r byggs Stockholmsm\u00e4ssan om till sjukhus|date=2020-03-27|website=DN.SE|language=sv|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> The Swedish Defence Forces will provide equipment for 30 of the 600 beds and the [[Stockholm Regional Council]] will provide the remaining 570.<ref name=\"stockholmsmassan\"/> The facilities are used for treating less severe cases, as opposed to those needing [[Intensive care unit|intensive care]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bj\u00f6rk |first1=Frida |title=\u00d6verl\u00e4kare sl\u00e5r larm om t\u00e4ltet p\u00e5 \u00d6stra: \u201dRiskerar m\u00e4nniskors liv\u201d |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/vast/overlakare-slar-larm-om-taltet-pa-ostra-riskerar-manniskors-liv |website=SVT Nyheter |accessdate=13 April 2020 |language=sv |date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:\u00d6stra Sjukhuset COVID-19 F\u00e4ltsjukhus.jpg|thumb|An army-constructed [[field hospital]] outside [[Sahlgrenska University Hospital|\u00d6stra Sjukhuset]] in [[Gothenburg]] on 23 March 2020. The tents contain temporary [[intensive care unit]]<nowiki/>s for COVID-19 patients. ]]\n[[File:Coronat\u00e4ltet .jpg|thumb|Medical tent set up outside [[Visby]] Hospital, 14 March 2020.]]\n[[File:Sahlgrenska_Corona_20200229_142008.jpg|thumb|Streetsigns outside Sahlgrenska hospital from late February telling those with potential symptoms of COVID-19 to wait outside the hospital.]]\nThe increasing number of cases in large areas such as Stockholm and Uppsala has resulted in the cancellation or postponement of up to 90% of planned surgeries, including cancer related surgeries.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Carl\u00e9n|first=Linnea|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/nara-halften-av-alla-planerade-operationer-installda|title=N\u00e4ra h\u00e4lften av alla planerade operationer inst\u00e4llda|date=2020-03-27|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=2020-03-27|last2=Sima|first2=Lotta|language=sv}}</ref>\n\nBefore the pandemic, the Swedish healthcare system had the capacity to treat approximately 500 persons in [[Intensive Care Unit|intensive care units]] (ICU). The relatively low number of beds had stayed a source of concern as the crisis evolved, and even though the number had increased to 800 at the beginning of April, healthcare professionals continued to express worry that their hospitals would eventually run out of beds. According to the calculations of the Swedish health agency, up to 1300 ICU beds would be needed when Sweden reached the top of the pandemic.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Olin |first1=Elisabet |title=Stor oro f\u00f6r kommande brist p\u00e5 intensivv\u00e5rdsplatser |url=https://lakartidningen.se/aktuellt/nyheter/2020/04/stor-oro-for-kommande-brist-pa-intensivvardsplatser/ |website=L\u00e4kartidningen}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Grill |first1=Marja |last2=Sima |first2=Lotta |last3=Velizelos |first3=Aris |last4=Ulander |first4=Kenneth |title=IVA-platserna sinar i landet \u2013 stor os\u00e4kerhet om de kommer att r\u00e4cka |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/iva-platserna-sinar-i-landet-stor-osakerhet-om-platserna-kreported(cka |website=SVT Nyheter |accessdate=2002-04-13|language=sv |date=2 April 2020}}</ref> On 13 April, the [[National Board of Health and Welfare (Sweden)|National Board of Health and Welfare]] reported that the total number of ICU beds had risen to 1039, with an occupancy of 80%.<ref>{{cite web |title=20 nya d\u00f6dsfall i Sverige |url=https://www.nsk.se/2020/04/13/20-nya-dodsfall-i-sverige/ |website=Norra Sk\u00e5ne |accessdate=13 April 2020|language=sv-SE}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Frejdeman |first1=Hannah |title=\u201dEfterrapportering att v\u00e4nta efter helgen\u201d |url=https://www.svd.se/just-nu-folkhalsomyndigheten-haller-presstraff |website=Svenska Dagbladet |accessdate=13 April 2020 |language=sv |date=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Equipment===\nOn 13 March, media reported that there is a shortage in [[personal protective equipment]] (PPE) for health care staff, and hospitals in Stockholm have been forced to reuse disposable PPEs after sanitation. The regional Health Care Director warned about this scenario in early March and government agencies have temporarily waived the public procurement law in order to hastily procure more supplies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/nyheter/coronaviruset/vardforraden-borjar-sina-engangsskydd-ateranvands/|title=Sjukhusens f\u00f6rr\u00e5d b\u00f6rjar sina \u2013 eng\u00e5ngsskydd \u00e5teranv\u00e4nds i Stockholm|website=expressen.se|language=sv|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref> The [[National Board of Health and Welfare (Sweden)|National Board of Health and Welfare]] ('''Socialstyrelsen''<nowiki/>') confirmed that there is no preparedness storage and nothing to distribute to the health care sector.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/tv/nyheter/coronaviruset/socialstyrelsen-det-finns-ingenting-att-distribuera/|title=Covid-19: Brist p\u00e5 skyddsutrustning och provtagningsmaterial|website=Expressen TV|language=sv|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/lA5mAo|title=Larmet inifr\u00e5n v\u00e5rden: \"Finns ingen skyddsutrustning\"|website=Aftonbladet|language=sv|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Staffing===\nOn 25 March 2020, Bj\u00f6rn Eriksson, the Director of Healthcare in Stockholm, appealed to anyone in the [[Stockholm Regional Council|Stockholm region]] who had experience in healthcare to volunteer. As of the 26 March 2020, 5100 people with healthcare experience had registered as volunteers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dn.se/sthlm/over-5000-har-anmalt-sig-for-att-forstarka-varden-i-stockholm/|title=\u00d6ver 5.000 har anm\u00e4lt sig f\u00f6r att f\u00f6rst\u00e4rka v\u00e5rden i Stockholm|date=27 March 2020|website=DN.SE|language=sv|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe increasing number of cases in large areas such as Stockholm and Uppsala has resulted in the cancellation or postponement of up to 90% of planned surgeries, including cancer related surgeries.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Carl\u00e9n|first=Linnea|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/nara-halften-av-alla-planerade-operationer-installda|title=N\u00e4ra h\u00e4lften av alla planerade operationer inst\u00e4llda|date=2020-03-27|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=2020-03-27|last2=Sima|first2=Lotta|language=sv}}</ref>\n\n==Impact on society==\n===Transport===\n[[Rail transport in Sweden]], which is principally run by the public operator, [[SJ AB]], has continued to operate throughout the pandemic, albeit with a slightly reduced schedule so that additional carriages can be added to trains, which in conjunction with fewer tickets being made available for sale, aims to ensure [[social distancing]] of those passengers that continue to travel.<ref>SJ Website Coronavirus info, https://www.sj.se/en/about/about-sj/latest-info-coronavirus.html</ref>\n\nAir transport in Sweden is primarily run by private companies (principally [[Scandinavian Airlines|SAS]] and [[Norwegian Air Shuttle]]) and has been severely impacted by the pandemic and has been heavily reduced. Like airlines around the world, Sweden's carriers have reduced the frequency of their flights, reduced their work force and asked the local government for financial assistance. On 15 March, [[Scandinavian Airlines|SAS]] announced that they would temporarily reduce their workforce by 10,000 people which constitutes roughly 90% of their workforce.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sasgroup.net/newsroom/press-releases/2020/sas-pausar-merparten-av-verksamheten/ |title=SAS pausar merparten av verksamheten |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=15 March 2020 |website= |publisher=SAS |access-date=27 March 2020 |quote= |language=Swedish}}</ref> Soon almost every domestic flight were cancelled. Swedish authorities advised against all non-essential travel inside and out of Sweden. [[SAS Group|SAS]] decided to from 6 April 2020 fly only four domestic departures and four domestic arrivals from Arlanda, plus some international<ref>[https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/sas-fortsatter-trafikera-kiruna-och-lulea SAS beh\u00e5ller ett inrikesflyg \u2013 forts\u00e4tter trafikera fyra orter]</ref> while Norwegian cancelled all domestic flights in Sweden.<ref>[https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/norrbotten/norwegian-staller-in-alla-inrikesflyg Norwegian st\u00e4ller in alla inrikesflyg]</ref> Several airports closed temporarily.\n\nThe decrease in travel had a big impact on the [[public transport|public transport sector]] due to a loss of revenue in ticket sales, which led to [[trade association]] Swedish Public Transport Association (''Svensk kollektivtrafik'') asking the government for financial aid.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kollektivtrafik tappar resor \u2013 ber om st\u00f6d |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/nyheter/a/JoyyJ6/kollektivtrafik-tappar-resor--ber-om-stod |website=Aftonbladet |accessdate=16 April 2020 |language=sv |date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Education===\nOn 13 March 2020 the spring [[Swedish Scholastic Aptitude Test]] (''\u2032H\u00f6gskoleprovet\u2032''), was cancelled affecting approximately 70,000 prospective students who had registered themselves. This was the first time the Swedish Scholastic Aptitude Test has been cancelled since it was established in 1977.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Balcer Bednarska|first=Jaqueline|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/hogskoleprovet-3|title=H\u00f6gskoleprovet st\u00e4lls in \u2013 70 000 personer drabbas|date=2020-03-13|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=2020-03-27|language=sv}}</ref> On 23 March 2020 the [[National Agency for Education (Sweden)|Swedish National Agency for Education]] ('''Skolverket''<nowiki/>'), cancelled the [[Education in Sweden#National tests|national tests]] to give teachers in Sweden more time to prepare for the possibility of distance education.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skolverket.se/om-oss/press/pressmeddelanden/pressmeddelanden/2020-03-23-varens-nationella-prov-stalls-in|title=[2020-03-23] V\u00e5rens nationella prov st\u00e4lls in|website=skolverket.se|language=sv|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\n===Defence===\nThe [[Swedish Armed Forces]] cancelled the international [[military exercise]] Aurora 20 which was scheduled to be held between May and June. [[Austrian Armed Forces|Austria]] and [[Canadian Armed Forces|Canada]] had previously announced their cancellation of their planned participation.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Olsson |first1=Jonas |title=Milit\u00e4r\u00f6vningen Aurora skjuts upp |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/militarovningen-aurora-skjuts-upp |website=SVT Nyheter |accessdate=3 April 2020 |language=sv |date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Politics===\nOn 25 March, The [[Swedish Social Democratic Party]] together with the [[Swedish Trade Union Confederation]] decided to cancel their traditional [[May Day|May Day demonstrations]]. They will instead hold an event on a digital platform, which will include speeches by the Swedish prime minister and leader of the Social Democrats, [[Stefan L\u00f6fven]], as well as union confederation leader [[Karl-Petter Thorwaldsson]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Yohannes |first1=Sofia |title=Socialdemokraternas 1 maj-t\u00e5g st\u00e4lls in |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/socialdemokraternas-1-maj-tag-stalls-in |website=SVT Nyheter |accessdate=30 March 2020 |language=sv |date=26 March 2020}}</ref> The [[Left Party (Sweden)]] also cancelled their nationwide demonstrations, and announced that there would instead be a digital celebration, including a speech by party leader [[Jonas Sj\u00f6stedt]].<ref>{{cite web |title=V\u00e4nsterpartiet anordnar digitalt f\u00f6rsta maj |url=https://www.etc.se/inrikes/vansterpartiet-anordnar-digitalt-forsta-maj |website=ETC |accessdate=30 March 2020 |language=sv |date=27 March 2020}}</ref> The [[Almedalen Week]], considered to be the biggest and most important forum in Sweden for seminars, debates and political speeches on current social issues, held in [[Visby]] every summer,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Wendt|first1=Maria|title=Almedalen \u2013 ett nationalromantiskt spektakel|trans-title=The Almedalen Week \u2013 a spectacle in the spirit of national romanticism|url=http://www.svd.se/kultur/understrecket/almedalen-ett-nationalromantiskt-spektakel_3711736.svd|website=svd.se|publisher=[[Svenska Dagbladet]]|date=6 July 2014|language=Swedish|accessdate=7 February 2015}}</ref> was cancelled as a result of the ban on large gatherings. The decision was taken on 1 April by the [[Gotland Municipality|organiser]] after consultation with the major political parties.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Johansson |first1=Sara |title=Almedalsveckan 2020 st\u00e4lls in |url=https://www.dagensjuridik.se/nyheter/almedalsveckan-2020-stalls-in/ |website=Dagens Juridik |publisher=Blendow Publishing AB |accessdate=2 April 2020 |language=sv-SE |date=2 April 2020}}</ref> Prime Minister Stefan L\u00f6fv\u00e9n had already announced that he had cancelled his planned participation in the upcoming event.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Larsson |first1=Carl |title=Statsministern avst\u00e5r Almedalen i sommar |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/ost/statsministern-avstar-almedalen-i-sommar |website=SVT Nyheter |accessdate=2 April 2020 |language=sv |date=2 April 2020}}</ref> A similar event in Stockholm, 'J\u00e4rvaveckan', was also cancelled, and won't be held until 2021.<ref>{{cite web |last1=R\u00e5gsj\u00f6 Thorell |first1=Andreas |title=J\u00e4rvaveckan flyttas fram till 2021 |url=https://www.resume.se/marknadsforing/sponsring-event/jarvaveckan-flyttas-fram-till-2021/ |website=www.resume.se |accessdate=14 April 2020 |language=sv |date=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Culture===\nOn 6 March, Swedish National Broadcaster [[SVT]] held a crisis meeting to consider broadcasting the live finals of [[Melodifestivalen 2020]] on 7 March without an audience, as a response to the growing outbreak. The Danish equivalent had recently decided to broadcast [[Dansk Melodi Grand Prix|their version]] of the finals without an audience. Ultimately, SVT decided to allow the audience to enter the arena, although they advised people who felt sick to stay at home.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Laurell|first=Agnes|url=https://www.dn.se/kultur-noje/danska-melodifestivalen-framfors-utan-publik/|title=SVT inf\u00f6r Melodifestivalen: Stanna hemma om du k\u00e4nner dig sjuk|date=6 March 2020|work=DN|access-date=8 March 2020|url-status=live|last2=Lenas|first2=Sverker|language=sv}}</ref>\n\nStarting 30 March 2020 the public library in G\u00e4vle will start with a book delivery service for people aged 70 or older. The library will also start a take-away service where you can pre-loan books and pick them in a take-away bag.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gavle.se/omsorg-och-stod/gavle-bibliotek-infor-take-away-bokkasse-for-alla-och-hemleverans-av-bocker-for-riskgruppe/|title=G\u00e4vle bibliotek inf\u00f6r Take away-bokkasse f\u00f6r alla och hemleverans av b\u00f6cker f\u00f6r riskgrupper|work=G\u00e4vle kommun|access-date=27 March 2020|language=sv-SE}}</ref>\n\n===Sports===\nIn [[Sport of athletics|athletics]], all [[2020 Diamond League]] events scheduled to be held in May were postponed, which included the meet in [[Stockholm]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Diamond League i Stockholm uppskjutet |url=https://www.svt.se/sport/friidrott/diamond-league-i-stockholm-uppskjutet |website=SVT Sport |accessdate=5 April 2020 |language=sv |date=27 March 2020}}</ref> The world's largest [[half marathon]] in Gothenburg, [[G\u00f6teborgsvarvet]], was postponed until later in 2020 and then cancelled completely on 27 March.<ref>{{cite web|author=Publicerad |url=https://www.svd.se/goteborgsvarvet-helt-installt-i-ar |title=G\u00f6teborgsvarvet helt inst\u00e4llt i \u00e5r &#124; SvD |publisher=Svd.se |date= |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref> The annual recreational [[road bicycle racing|bicycle race]] [[V\u00e4tternrundan]], scheduled to be held in June, was also cancelled as a result of the pandemic. The organisers made the decision public on 2 April.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Holmqvist |first1=Tobias |title=V\u00e4tternrundan 2020 st\u00e4lls in |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/ost/vatternrundan-2020-stalls-in|website=SVT Nyheter |accessdate=2 April 2020 |date=2 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Klart: V\u00e4tternrundan inst\u00e4lld |url=https://www.dn.se/sport/klart-vatternrundan-installd/ |website=DN.SE |accessdate=2 April 2020 |language=sv |date=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 March, [[Swedish Football Association|the governing body for association football in Sweden]] formally announced that the premiere of the 2020 season for the first and second division leagues, men's [[Allsvenskan]] and [[Superettan]] as well as women's [[Damallsvenskan]] and [[Elitettan]], will be postponed to late May or early June. The decision will not affect the leagues below the second level.<ref>{{cite web |title=Klart: Allsvenskan skjuts upp |url=https://www.svt.se/sport/fotboll/klart-allsvenskan-stalls-in |website=SVT Sport |accessdate=30 March 2020 |language=sv |date=19 March 2020}}</ref> Two days later it was announced that the 2020 edition of the association football award ceremony [[Fotbollsgalan]] was cancelled.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Simon |first1=Bank |title=Sportbladet avsl\u00f6jar: Fotbollsgalan 2020 st\u00e4lls in |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/AdMegj/sportbladet-avslojar-fotbollsgalan-2020-stalls-in |website=Aftonbladet |accessdate=30 March 2020 |language=sv |date=19 March 2020}}</ref> Many of the professional teams in the highest division warned that the loss of income following the postponement of the season would have a severe impact on their economy.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Aronsson |first1=Claes |title=Allsvenska klubbarna planerar f\u00f6r katastrofl\u00e4ge - Radiosporten |url=https://sverigesradio.se/artikel/7434156 |website=sverigesradio.se |accessdate=15 April 2020 |language=sv |date=20 March 2020}}</ref> Professional [[handball]] was also affected, with the last rounds and the finals in the highest men's and women's leagues, [[Handbollsligan]] and [[Svensk handbollselit|Svensk handbollselit]], being cancelled.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Radio |first1=Sveriges |title=Svensk handboll st\u00e4ller in hela s\u00e4songen - Radiosporten |url=https://sverigesradio.se/artikel/7430818 |website=sverigesradio.se |accessdate=15 April 2020 |language=sv |date=16 March 2020}}</ref> Similarly, the [[Swedish Basketball Federation]] choose to stop all games until May, effectively stopping the highest divisions [[Swedish Basketball League|SBL]] and [[Basketligan dam|SBL Dam]] mid-season.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Flink |first1=Johan |last2=Wahlberg |first2=Malin |title=St\u00e4ller in all basket resten av s\u00e4songen |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/a/70GQbo/staller-in-all-basket-resten-av-sasongen |website=Aftonbladet |accessdate=15 April 2020 |language=sv |date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Motorcycle speedway|Speedway]], the start of [[Elitserien (speedway)|Elitserien]], the highest league in [[Speedway in Sweden|the Swedish league system]], was rescheduled to 2 June. In order to manage a tighter schedule, the [[Sports governing body|sport's governing body]] Swedish Motorcycle and Snowmobile Federation also decided to cancel the quarterfinals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Elitserien i speedway slopar kvartsfinalerna |url=https://ekuriren.se/sport/elitserien-i-speedway-slopar-kvartsfinalerna-sm5371664.aspx |website=ekuriren.se |accessdate=5 April 2020 |date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Debate==\nMany outside Sweden considered the Swedish policies and the measures taken by its [[Government of Sweden|government]] to fight the pandemic to be different when compared to most other countries.<ref>Jon Henley [https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/15/sweden-coronavirus-death-toll-reaches-1000 Critics question Swedish approach as coronavirus death toll reaches 1,000' Scientists question light-touch tactics as other Nordic countries record lower death rates] 15 April 2020 The Guardian</ref>  As a result, there was an increase in international news coverage of Sweden. Much of the coverage was neutral, but some of it also contained criticism.<ref name=\"samtalet8aprilsida5\">{{cite web |title=Samtalet om Sverige 1\u20137 april 2020 |url=https://si.se/app/uploads/2020/04/samtalet-om-sverige-1-7-april-1.pdf |website=www.si.se |accessdate=14 April 2020 |page=5 |language=sv |date=8 April 2020}}</ref> One of the most vocal critics has been \n[[immunologist]] [[Cecilia S\u00f6derberg-Naucl\u00e9r]] who received much coverage in international news coverage,<ref name=\"samtalet8aprilsida7till8\">{{cite web |title=Samtalet om Sverige 1\u20137 april 2020 |url=https://si.se/app/uploads/2020/04/samtalet-om-sverige-1-7-april-1.pdf |website=www.si.se |accessdate=14 April 2020 |page=7-8 |language=sv |date=8 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"samtalet15aprilsida9\">{{cite web |title=Samtalet om Sverige 8\u201314 april 2020 |url=https://si.se/app/uploads/2020/04/samtalet-om-sverige-2020-04-15.pdf |website=www.si.se |accessdate=15 April 2020 |page=5 |language=sv |date=16 April 2020}}</ref>, and was quoted accusing the government of \"leading us to catastrophe\" and having \"decided to let people die.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Robertson |first1=Derek |title='They are leading us to catastrophe': Sweden's coronavirus stoicism begins to jar |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/30/catastrophe-sweden-coronavirus-stoicism-lockdown-europe |website=The Guardian |accessdate=16 April 2020 |language=en |date=30 March 2020}}</ref> [[Global Times]], closely linked to the ruling [[Communist Party of China]], accused Sweden of having capitulated to the virus, calling the country 'a black hole' and called for the international community to condemn Sweden's actions.<ref name=\"kinakritiserar\">{{cite web |last1=Djurberg |first1=Bj\u00f6rn |title=Kina kritiserar Sveriges coronahantering |url=https://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=83&artikel=7429175 |website=Sveriges Radio |accessdate=15 April 2020 |language=sv |date=14 March 2020}}</ref> Some, including Swedish [[Minister for Justice (Sweden)|justice minister]] [[Morgan Johansson]], speculated that the strong criticism may be partly linked to the [[China\u2013Sweden relations#Conflict over Gui Minhai|poor relations between the two countries]] after China's imprisonment of the Swedish book publisher [[Gui Minhai]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Foster |first1=Keith |title=China attacks Swedish virus response |url=https://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=2054&artikel=7429323 |website=Radio Sweden |accessdate=15 April 2020 |language=en |date=14 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"kinakritiserar\" /> Many claimed the Sweden was pursuing a [[herd immunity|herd immunity strategy]],<ref name=\"samtalet8aprilsida5\" /> including [[President of the United States|US president]] [[Donald Trump]], who during a press briefing told the assembled media that Sweden was 'suffering very greatly' due to what he referred to as 'the herd', and that the US, if done the same, 'would have lost hundreds of thousands more people'.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sweden says Trump criticism of coronavirus strategy 'factually wrong' |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/sweden-says-trump-criticism-of-coronavirus-strategy-factually-wrong |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=14 April 2020 |language=en |date=8 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{citation |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/utrikes/trump-usa-hade-haft-tva-miljoner-doda-om-vi-foljt-sveriges-coronalinje |title=Trump: USA hade kanske haft tv\u00e5 miljoner d\u00f6da om vi f\u00f6ljt Sveriges coronalinje |publisher=SVT |author=Maria Makar|date=April 10, 2020|accessdate=April 13, 2020|lang=sv}}</ref> Responding partly to Trump's remarks, which she described by using the word \u2018misinformation\u2019, Swedish [[Minister for Foreign Affairs (Sweden)|foreign minister]] [[Ann Linde]] said that the \u2018so-called Swedish strategy\u2019 was one of many myths about Sweden, and described it as \u2018absolutely false\u2019. Linde said that the Swedish goal was no different from most other countries; to save lives, hinder the spread of the virus and make the situation manageable for [[Healthcare in Sweden|the health system]].<ref name=\"lindecnn\" /> Sweden's [[State epidemiologist (Sweden)|state epidemiologist]], [[Anders Tegnell]], when asked about Trump's remarks, said that in his opinion Sweden was doing relatively well, and were no worse off than [[New York (state)|New York]].<ref>{{citation |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/tegnell-om-trumps-utspel-jamfort-med-new-york-fungerar-det-bra-i-sverige |title=Tegnell om Trumps utspel: Man ska inte ta det p\u00e5 allvar |publisher=SVT |author=Prescilia Haddad|date=April 8, 2020|accessdate=April 13, 2020|lang=sv}}</ref> Many news stories in international media painted a picture of things being 'business as usual in Sweden, with its citizens ignoring the recommendations to practice [[social distancing]] and avoiding unnecessary travel.<ref name=\"samtalet8aprilsida5\" /> According to Linde, this was another of the myths in the reporting about Sweden, and she claimed Sweden's combination of recommendations and legally binding measures had so far proven effective.<ref name=\"lindecnn\" />\n\nWith Sweden having taken some of the least strict measures of any European country or of countries with a similar number of cases, the response has been both criticised and praised by international media.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=b63abe70-704c-11ea-ba39-7b28c7fe6635&url=L29waW5pb24vYXJ0aWNsZXMvMjAyMC0wMy0yNy9jb3JvbmF2aXJ1cy13YW50LXRvLWVzY2FwZS1hLWxvY2tkb3duLXRyeS1zd2VkZW4/c3JuZD1wcmVtaXVtLWV1cm9wZQ==|title=Want to Escape a Lockdown? Try Sweden \u2014 Do you trust millions of your fellow citizens to do the right thing in a pandemic?|last=Laurent|first=Lionel|date=27 March 2020|website=Bloomberg L.P.|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=088c5a30-704d-11ea-a57a-3956084aed93&url=L25ld3MvYXJ0aWNsZXMvMjAyMC0wMy0yMy9zd2VkZXMtdHJ5LWxhaXNzZXotZmFpcmUtbW9kZWwtaW4tY29udHJvdmVyc2lhbC12aXJ1cy1yZXNwb25zZQ==|title=Swedes Try Laissez-Faire Model in Controversial Virus Response|last=Rolander|first=Niclas|date=23 March 2020|website=Bloomberg L.P.|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/31de03b8-6dbc-11ea-89df-41bea055720b|title=Sweden bucks global trend with experimental virus strategy {{!}} Free to read|last=Milne|first=Richard|date=25 March 2020|website=Financial Times|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nSweden's response to the pandemic was also heavily debated within Sweden. On 14 April, a debate article was sent to Swedish newspapers signed by 22 academics, claiming that the strategy of the Swedish public health agency will lead to \"chaos in the healthcare system\". Moreover, they claimed that there is no transparency regarding the data used in the models made by the agency. [[Anders Tegnell]] from the public health agency responded to the criticism by saying that there is no lack in transparency in the agency's work and that all data is available to be downloaded by the public as an excel-file on their website. <ref>{{cite web |title=Ann Linde: \u201dForskare om Sveriges strategi: \u201dKommer att bli kaos\u201d\u201d |url=https://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=83&artikel=7451820 |website=www.sverigesradio.se |accessdate=14 April 2020 |language=sv}}</ref>  Additionally Tegnell stated that the numbers of deaths presented in the published article are wrong, especially regarding the specific number of deaths per day. Another claim in the article saying that Sweden's statistics are closing in on to the ones of Italy was countered by Anders Tegnell saying that unlike Sweden, Italy and many other countries only report on deaths in hospitals, making it hard to compare the numbers of the different countries. <ref>{{cite web |title=\"Tegnells svar p\u00e5 skarpa kritiken i DN-debatt: Grundl\u00e4ggande felaktigheter\" |url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/forskare-kritiska-til-fhm-lat-politikerna-ta-over |website=www.svt.se |accessdate=14 April 2020 |language=sv}}</ref>\n\nAccording to surveys carried out in late March and early April , three out of four Swedes (71-76%) trusted the Public Health Agency, and nearly half of the people surveyed (47%) said they had 'very high trust' in the agency. A majority said they trusted the government, and 85% said they trusted the Swedish health-care system.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronastatus 0401 - Novus |url=https://novus.se/coronastatus-0401/ |website=Novus - kunskap och insiktsf\u00f6retag |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=sv-SE}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=St\u00e5hle |first1=Mathias |title=\u00d6kat f\u00f6rtroende f\u00f6r Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten |url=https://www.svd.se/okat-fortroende-for-folkhalsomyndigheten |website=Svenska Dagbladet |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=sv |date=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Forsberg |first1=Oskar |title=F\u00f6rtroendet f\u00f6r Tegnell och L\u00f6fven \u00f6kar |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/nyheter/a/70OzwW/fortroendet-for-tegnell-och-lofven-okar |website=Aftonbladet |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=sv |date=19 April 2020}}</ref> A March 2020 survey reported that more than half (53%) of the Swedish population had trust in the state epidemiologist, Anders Tegnell, a higher share than for any of the current leaders of the Swedish political parties. The share of respondents who said that they didn't trust Tegnell was 18%.\n<ref>{{cite web |title=Mer \u00e4n h\u00e4lften av svenskarna har f\u00f6rtroende f\u00f6r Anders Tegnell - Nyheterna - tv4.se |url=https://www.tv4.se/nyheterna/klipp/mer-\u00e4n-h\u00e4lften-av-svenskarna-har-f\u00f6rtroende-f\u00f6r-anders-tegnell-12533941 |website=www.tv4.se |accessdate=18 April 2020 |language=sv}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Sweden medical cases}}\n {{clear}}\n\n===Additional data===\nAs of 27 March, nearly 3 out of 4 patients in intensive care in Sweden were men. The majority of them had underlying symptoms such as high blood pressure. Also, a disproportionately high number of deaths among males was reported.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Larsson|first=Ylva|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/nastan-8-av-10-av-de-svarast-sjuka-i-sverige-ar-man|title=N\u00e4stan 3 av 4 av de som intensivv\u00e5rdats i Sverige \u00e4r m\u00e4n|date=26 March 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=27 March 2020|last2=Andersson|first2=Ki|language=sv}}</ref>\n\nAt a point, it was reported that a disproportionate number of those that had died by then were Somali (6)<ref name=\"Randhawa\">{{Cite news|last=Randhawa|first=Rebecca|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/lakarforening-larmar-over-halften-av-de-doda-ar-svensksomalier|title=L\u00e4karf\u00f6rening larmar: Flera svensksomalier bland coronad\u00f6dsfall i Stockholmsomr\u00e5det|date=2020-03-23|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=2020-03-27|language=sv}}</ref>  out of 89<ref>{{cite web |title=30 mars: L\u00e4gesrapport om arbetet med det nya coronaviruset |url=https://www.sll.se/verksamhet/halsa-och-vard/nyheter-halsa-och-vard/2020/03/30-mars-lagesrapport-om-arbetet-med-det-nya-coronaviruset/ |website=Region Stockholm |accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref> deaths being members of the Somali community in the Stockholm Region.<ref name=\"Randhawa\"/>\n\n====Charts====\n<small>\n'''Note:''' \nData is compiled by Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten at 11:30 (UTC+02:00) each day. Reports of new cases and deaths to Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten might be delayed by up to several days, especially around weekends, possibly introducing delays in reported number of cases for the last few days.<ref name=\"FHM_Aktuellt_l\u00e4ge\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/smittskydd-beredskap/utbrott/aktuella-utbrott/covid-19/aktuellt-epidemiologiskt-lage/|title=Bekr\u00e4ftade fall i Sverige \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref><br />\n</small>\n\n<!-- Leave OFF THE LAST DAY as its only a small part of data and will give the charts a false shape -->\n<!-- Do NOT ONLY update the last day, this will invalidate the graphs! Update at least the last 14 days, as data is backdated by source -->\n{{Image frame|caption={{small|{{right|source: FOHM<ref name=\"FHM_Official_stats\"/>}}}}{{Center|'''Total confirmed cases'''}}|pos=top|align=left|border=no|content=\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=720\n|linewidth=1\n|yGrid=|xGrid=\n|colors=#FF4500\n|xAxisAngle=-45\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|x=4 Feb, ., 26 Feb, 27 Feb, 28 Feb, 29 Feb, 1 Mar, 2 Mar, 3 Mar, 4 Mar, 5 Mar, 6 Mar, 7 Mar, 8 Mar, 9 Mar, 10 Mar, 11 Mar, 12 Mar, 13 Mar, 14 Mar, 15 Mar, 16 Mar, 17 Mar, 18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar, 21 Mar, 22 Mar, 23 Mar, 24 Mar, 25 Mar, 26 Mar, 27 Mar, 28 Mar, 29 Mar, 30 Mar, 31 Mar, 1 Apr, 2 Apr, 3 Apr, 4 Apr, 5 Apr, 6 Apr, 7 Apr, 8 Apr, 9 Apr, 10 Apr, 11 Apr, 12 Apr, 13 Apr, 14 Apr, 15 Apr, 16 Apr, 17 Apr, 18 Apr, 19 A