{"title_page": "Mi Notebook Air", "text_new": "{{Copy edit|date=April 2020}}\n{{Overly detailed|date=April 2020}}\n{{More citations needed|date=April 2020}}\n[[File:Xiaomi Notebook Air 12.5 Motherboard.jpg|thumb|Xiaomi Notebook Air 12.5 Motherboard]]\n\n'''Mi Notebook Air''' is a portable computer introduced in 2016 by [[Xiaomi|Xiaomi Corporation]]. There are versions with two screen sizes (12.5-inch and 13.5-inch). The first 12.5-inch generation used an [[Intel Core m3|Intel Core M3-6Y30]] microprocessor, which was later upgraded to the [[List of Intel Core M microprocessors|Intel Core m3-7Y30]] microprocessor. The computer with a 12.5-inch screen is configured with a [[Samsung]] 128 GB [[NVM Express|NVMe]] [[Solid-state drive|SSD]] and 4 GB of soldered [[DDR3 SDRAM|DDR3L]]-[[SDRAM]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mi.com/global/mibookair|title=Mi Global Home|website=www.mi.com|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> Both models feature a [[Fullhd|Full-HD]] screen with a back-lit [[Computer keyboard|keyboard]].\n\n=== Operating system ===\nThe Xiaomi Mi Notebook Air is configured with an OEM activated [[Windows 10]] operating system. However, it supports the most recent [[Linux kernel|Linux]] [[Linux distribution|Distributions]], as demonstrated by the Deepin's team<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/linux_deepin/status/877061333631369216|title=A present to @Linus__Torvalds with #deepin installed on @xiaomi #XiaomiMiAir! #LinusTorvalds @XiaomiUSApic.twitter.com/iLsPrq0xYJ|last=deepin|date=2017-06-20|website=@linux_deepin|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> to [[Linus Torvalds|Mr. Linus Torvalds]] in 2017.\n\n=== Processor ===\nThe Mi Laptop Air 13.3\" version comes with Intel\u00ae Core\u2122 i5 Processor and the 12.5\" version comes with Intel\u00ae Core\u2122 M Processor. 6th Generation Intel\u00ae Core\u2122 i Processor series are 18% faster than their predecessors. Power consumption is significantly reduced, and the processors can be used to view 4K videos.\n\n=== Motherboard ===\nThe [[motherboard]] installed in the Xiaomi Mi Notebook Air is [[manufactured]] by Timi Personal Computing Co. Ltd.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.stiwe.com/xiaomi-mi-notebook-air-12-5-thin-but-with-elegant-looks-and-outstanding-performance/|title=Xiaomi Mi Notebook Air 12.5 {{!}} Thin But With Elegant Looks And Outstanding Performance {{!}}|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n=== Power Management ===\nMi Laptop Air supports 1C fast charging technology, so it can be charged up to 50% in under 30 minutes.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jackson |first1=Thomas |title=Mi Global Home |url=https://www.mi.com/global/mibookair |website=Mi Global |publisher=Mi Global |accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Netbooks]]\n[[Category:Xiaomi]]\n", "text_old": "{{Copy edit|date=April 2020}}\n{{Overly detailed|date=April 2020}}\n{{More citations needed|date=April 2020}}\n[[File:Xiaomi Notebook Air 12.5 Motherboard.jpg|thumb|Xiaomi Notebook Air 12.5 Motherboard]]\n\n'''Mi Notebook Air''' is a portable computer introduced in 2016 by [[Xiaomi|Xiaomi Corporation]]. There are versions with two screen sizes (12.5-inch and 13.5-inch). The first 12.5-inch generation used an [[Intel Core m3|Intel Core M3-6Y30]] microprocessor, which was later upgraded to the [[List of Intel Core M microprocessors|Intel Core m3-7Y30]] microprocessor. The computer with a 12.5-inch screen is configured with a [[Samsung]] 128 GB [[NVM Express|NVMe]] [[Solid-state drive|SSD]] and 4 GB of soldered [[DDR3 SDRAM|DDR3L]]-[[SDRAM]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mi.com/global/mibookair|title=Mi Global Home|website=www.mi.com|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> Both models feature a [[Fullhd|Full-HD]] screen with a back-light [[Computer keyboard|keyboard]].\n\n=== Operating system ===\nThe Xiaomi Mi Notebook Air is configured with an OEM activated [[Windows 10]] operating system. However, it supports the most recent [[Linux kernel|Linux]] [[Linux distribution|Distributions]], as demonstrated by the Deepin's team<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/linux_deepin/status/877061333631369216|title=A present to @Linus__Torvalds with #deepin installed on @xiaomi #XiaomiMiAir! #LinusTorvalds @XiaomiUSApic.twitter.com/iLsPrq0xYJ|last=deepin|date=2017-06-20|website=@linux_deepin|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> to [[Linus Torvalds|Mr. Linus Torvalds]] in 2017.\n\n=== Processor ===\nThe Mi Laptop Air 13.3\" version comes with Intel\u00ae Core\u2122 i5 Processor and the 12.5\" version comes with Intel\u00ae Core\u2122 M Processor. 6th Generation Intel\u00ae Core\u2122 i Processor series are 18% faster than their predecessors. Power consumption is significantly reduced, and the processors can be used to view 4K videos.\n\n=== Motherboard ===\nThe [[motherboard]] installed in the Xiaomi Mi Notebook Air is [[manufactured]] by Timi Personal Computing Co. Ltd.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.stiwe.com/xiaomi-mi-notebook-air-12-5-thin-but-with-elegant-looks-and-outstanding-performance/|title=Xiaomi Mi Notebook Air 12.5 {{!}} Thin But With Elegant Looks And Outstanding Performance {{!}}|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n=== Power Management ===\nMi Laptop Air supports 1C fast charging technology, so it can be charged up to 50% in under 30 minutes.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jackson |first1=Thomas |title=Mi Global Home |url=https://www.mi.com/global/mibookair |website=Mi Global |publisher=Mi Global |accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Netbooks]]\n[[Category:Xiaomi]]\n", "name_user": "Hind History", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eOperating system", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mi_Notebook_Air"}
{"title_page": "Siege of Ramsej", "text_new": "\n\n\nSiege of Ramsej(1682-1688) was a series of military confrontations between Maratha empire headed by Sambhaji and Mughal empire led by Aurangzeb regarding the control of [[Ramsej|Ramsej fort]] in the Nashik region. Aurangzeb arrived in Deccan in late 1681 with a 5,00,000 strong army to destroy the Maratha Empire and the Deccan Sultanates of Adilshahi and Qutubshahi. He wanted to capture the forts held by the Marathas in Nashik and Baglana region. Hence he decided to begin his Deccan campaign with an attack on Ramsej fort which is near Nashik.\n\n== Before the Siege ==\nShivaji's general Moropant Pingle had captured Ramsej in the year 1671-72. Since then it became a part of Maratha Empire. Ramsej was fort lying in open lands without excessive forest cover. Aurangzeb thought that it will be a good idea to capture an easy fort like Ramsej right at the beginning so as to increase the morale of his troops. \n\n== Battles ==\n\n\nRamsej fort saw the war against [[Mughal Empire]] for six and a half years. The first killedar (fort commander) was Suryaji Jadhav, but after five and a half years he was transferred and a new killedar was appointed as per the rotation of posts policy of Maratha empire. In 1682 [[Aurangzeb]] sent Sahabuddin Khan to conquer the fort. Shahbuddin Khan had vowed to capture the fort with his 40,000 army and strong artillery within a few hours. But the 600 Maratha soldiers on the fort kept his forces at bay for many months by fierce array of slingshots, lit haystack and huge stones even though they did not have cannons on the fort. Once the Mughal artillery managed to break the fort walls in the evening and they assumed that the fort will be captured easily. But all 600 Marathas on the fort worked for a full night and rebuilt the entire broken section of the wall, much to the despair and awe of the Mughals. Such fierce resistance made the Mughal soldiers believe that the Marathas on the fort knew black magic. The inability of Mughal Sardar to capture the fort started frustrating Aurangzeb. He raised a wooden platform to storm the fort. Marathas were very smart in the fact that Shivaji and his son Sambhaji had a policy of keeping enough ammunition even on the forts having no cannons or guns. Ramshej was no exception and even though it did not have cannons it had sufficient ammunition. The fort commander had an idea and utilised amply available animal skin and wood on the fort to make wooden cannons. Coupled with the ammunition already present on the fort these wooden cannons started inflicting heavy losses on mughal army. The retaliation from the Marathas was so strong that he left the responsibility to Bahadurkhan and went to Junnar. Bahadurkhan also tried to capture the fort by fooling Marathas into believing that the Mughals were preparing for a full fledged frontal assault. While his real plan was send 200 of his best troops from the rear side of the fort by climbing the steep cliff. The Maratha commander was aware of the fact and allowed these 200 soldiers to climb the rope. Once they had climbed up the rope, he cut the rope as a result of which 200 of the best mughal soldiers fell and died in the valley. Bahadurkhan was distraught and found that Marathas were receiving secret supplies from the nearby forts. He carefully blocked all the paths to nearby Maratha forts. There was dire shortage of food on the fort. Seeing this situation Maratha King Sambhaji acted quickly by sending his sardars Rupaji Bhosle and Manaji More with an 8,000 strong army and supplies. They tried to break through the Mughal line but we're unable to supply the fort. Sambhaji was in great worry that his fiercely brave warriors were fighting without food. But the luck supported the Marathas and due to severe bad weather Bahadurkhan relaxed his encirclement for one day enabling Rupaji and Manaji to supply the fort with supplies enough for 6 more months. Bahadurkhan then tried to win the fort with the help of a 'mantrik' as he believed that the Marathas had ghosts under their control. The Marathas again fooled him as the mantrik was himself a maratha soldier in disguise who led the Mughal army in a deadly ambush of the marathas. Bahadurkhan and Mughals fled the deadly ambush and several Mughals were killed in this surprise attack. Bahadurkhan was also unable to siege the fort, finally, he burnt the wooden platform and left the battle. [[Aurangzeb]] sent Kasim Khan Kirmani to lead the battle and it is said that the Mughals conquered Ramshej Fort by paying [[Bribery|bribe]] to the new killedar. <ref>{{Cite book|last=Sawant|first=Indrajit|title=Marathyanche Swatantrayuddha Bhag - 1 Chhatrapati Sambhaji Maharaj|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite book|last=Sawant|first=Shivaji|title=Chhava|publisher=Continental Publishers|year=|isbn=|location=Pune|pages=}}</ref>\n\n== Legacy ==\nThe resistance of barely 600 Marathas to such a strong Mughal army of 40,000 consistently for six years is considered to be a folklore in Maratha culture. The defence of Ramsej by the Marathas became a symbol of resistance and determination against the Mughals. \n\n== References ==\n<br />\n", "text_old": "\n\n\nSiege of Ramsej(1682-1688) was a series of military confrontations between Maratha empire headed by Sambhaji and Mughal empire led by Aurangzeb regarding the control of [[Ramsej|Ramsej fort]] in the Nashik region. Aurangzeb arrived in Deccan in late 1681 with a 5,00,000 strong army to destroy the Maratha Empire and the Deccan Sultanates of Adilshahi and Qutubshahi. He wanted to capture the forts held by the Marathas in Nashik and Baglana region. Hence he decided to begin his Deccan campaign with an attack on Ramsej fort which is near Nashik.\n\n== Background\ufffc ==\nShivaji's general Moropant Pingle had captured Ramsej in the year 1671-72. Since then it became a part of Maratha Empire. Ramsej was fort lying in open lands without excessive forest cover. Aurangzeb thought that it will be a good idea to capture an easy fort like Ramsej right at the beginning so as to increase the morale of his troops. \n\n== Battles ==\n\n\nRamsej fort saw the war against [[Mughal Empire]] for six and a half years. The first killedar (fort commander) was Suryaji Jadhav, but after five and a half years he was transferred and a new killedar was appointed as per the rotation of posts policy of Maratha empire. In 1682 [[Aurangzeb]] sent Sahabuddin Khan to conquer the fort. Shahbuddin Khan had vowed to capture the fort with his 40,000 army and strong artillery within a few hours. But the 600 Maratha soldiers on the fort kept his forces at bay for many months by fierce array of slingshots, lit haystack and huge stones even though they did not have cannons on the fort. Once the Mughal artillery managed to break the fort walls in the evening and they assumed that the fort will be captured easily. But all 600 Marathas on the fort worked for a full night and rebuilt the entire broken section of the wall, much to the despair and awe of the Mughals. Such fierce resistance made the Mughal soldiers believe that the Marathas on the fort knew black magic. The inability of Mughal Sardar to capture the fort started frustrating Aurangzeb. He raised a wooden platform to storm the fort. Marathas were very smart in the fact that Shivaji and his son Sambhaji had a policy of keeping enough ammunition even on the forts having no cannons or guns. Ramshej was no exception and even though it did not have cannons it had sufficient ammunition. The fort commander had an idea and utilised amply available animal skin and wood on the fort to make wooden cannons. Coupled with the ammunition already present on the fort these wooden cannons started inflicting heavy losses on mughal army. The retaliation from the Marathas was so strong that he left the responsibility to Bahadurkhan and went to Junnar. Bahadurkhan also tried to capture the fort by fooling Marathas into believing that the Mughals were preparing for a full fledged frontal assault. While his real plan was send 200 of his best troops from the rear side of the fort by climbing the steep cliff. The Maratha commander was aware of the fact and allowed these 200 soldiers to climb the rope. Once they had climbed up the rope, he cut the rope as a result of which 200 of the best mughal soldiers fell and died in the valley. Bahadurkhan was distraught and found that Marathas were receiving secret supplies from the nearby forts. He carefully blocked all the paths to nearby Maratha forts. There was dire shortage of food on the fort. Seeing this situation Maratha King Sambhaji acted quickly by sending his sardars Rupaji Bhosle and Manaji More with an 8,000 strong army and supplies. They tried to break through the Mughal line but we're unable to supply the fort. Sambhaji was in great worry that his fiercely brave warriors were fighting without food. But the luck supported the Marathas and due to severe bad weather Bahadurkhan relaxed his encirclement for one day enabling Rupaji and Manaji to supply the fort with supplies enough for 6 more months. Bahadurkhan then tried to win the fort with the help of a 'mantrik' as he believed that the Marathas had ghosts under their control. The Marathas again fooled him as the mantrik was himself a maratha soldier in disguise who led the Mughal army in a deadly ambush of the marathas. Bahadurkhan and Mughals fled the deadly ambush and several Mughals were killed in this surprise attack. Bahadurkhan was also unable to siege the fort, finally, he burnt the wooden platform and left the battle. [[Aurangzeb]] sent Kasim Khan Kirmani to lead the battle and it is said that the Mughals conquered Ramshej Fort by paying [[Bribery|bribe]] to the new killedar. <ref>{{Cite book|last=Sawant|first=Indrajit|title=Marathyanche Swatantrayuddha Bhag - 1 Chhatrapati Sambhaji Maharaj|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite book|last=Sawant|first=Shivaji|title=Chhava|publisher=Continental Publishers|year=|isbn=|location=Pune|pages=}}</ref>\n\n== Legacy ==\nThe resistance of barely 600 Marathas to such a strong Mughal army of 40,000 consistently for six years is considered to be a folklore in Maratha culture. The defence of Ramsej by the Marathas became a symbol of resistance and determination against the Mughals. \n\n== References ==\n<br />\n", "name_user": "Charvak157", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siege_of_Ramsej"}
{"title_page": "Pope Benedict XVI's visit to the United Kingdom", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=November 2013}}\n[[File:Papal visit in Westminster (17th September 2010).jpg|thumb|right|300px|The papal visit in [[Westminster]], [[London]]]]\n\nThe state visit of Pope Benedict XVI to the United Kingdom was held from 16 to 19 September 2010 and was the first visit by a Pope to Britain after [[Pope John Paul II]] made a [[Pope John Paul II's visit to the United Kingdom|pastoral, rather than state, visit]] in 1982. The visit included the [[beatification]] of [[John Henry Newman|Cardinal Newman]] as a \"pastoral highlight\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.christiantoday.com/article/catholic.church.seeks.to.clarify.purpose.of.popes.visit/26105.htm |title=Catholic Church seeks to clarify purpose of Pope\u2019s visit 124; Christian News on Christian Today |publisher=Christiantoday.com |date=15 June 2010 |accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref>\n\nPope Benedict's visit included meetings with [[Elizabeth II]] ([[Queen of the United Kingdom]] and [[Supreme Governor]] of the [[Church of England]]), the [[First Minister of Scotland]] [[Alex Salmond]], [[Archbishop of Canterbury]] [[Rowan Williams]], [[British Prime Minister|Prime Minister]] and [[UK Conservative Party|Conservative Party]] leader [[David Cameron]], and leaders of the other main political parties.\n\nThe Pope's itinerary included open air Masses in Glasgow and Birmingham, a youth vigil in Hyde Park in London, and Mass at Westminster Cathedral in London, attended by over 200,000 people.\n\n==Invitation and planning==\n{{Expand section|date=September 2010}}\nAn invitation to visit Britain was extended to [[Pope Benedict XVI]] by then [[Prime Minister]] [[Gordon Brown]] in February 2009. The Pope's visit featured in the debates between party leaders in April 2010, prior to the [[2010 United Kingdom general election]], where all three party leaders expressed support for the visit, while expressing disagreement with some of the Pope's views.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/shared/bsp/hi/pdfs/23_04_10_seconddebate.pdf Second prime ministerial debate, 22 April 2010, Transcript] ''[[BBC News]]'' 23 April 2010</ref>\n\nAnjoum Noorani of the [[Foreign and Commonwealth Office]] was originally a key contact between the [[British Government]] and the papal visit team. However, he was suspended from overseas postings and given a final warning, to last for five years, after approving the [[Foreign Office papal visit memo|sending of a memo]] written by Steven Mulvain, a 23-year-old Oxford graduate, mocking the visit.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/7804506/Diplomat-who-sent-Pope-condom-memo-given-final-warning-and-banned-from-overseas-postings.html | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | title=Diplomat who sent Pope 'condom' memo given final warning and banned from overseas postings | first=Martin | last=Beckford | date=6 June 2010}}</ref> Subsequently the new Government appointed liberal Catholic<ref>{{Cite news| url=http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/news/damianthompson/100046639/lord-patten-im-like-lot-of-catholics-i-dont-agree-with-everything-the-vatican-says/ | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | title=Lord Patten: 'I'm like lot of Catholics. I don't agree with everything the Vatican says' | date=8 July 2010}}</ref> [[Chris Patten|Lord Patten]] to get the visit back on track following a series of setbacks.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/7803820/Lord-Patten-will-co-ordinate-Pope-Benedict-XVIs-trip-to-Britain.html | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | title=Lord Patten will co-ordinate Pope Benedict XVI's trip to Britain | first=Martin | last=Beckford | date=4 June 2010}}</ref>\n\n===Ticketed events===\nThere were three specific ticketed events open to the public during the Pope's visit. These were a [[Mass (liturgy)|Mass]] in [[Bellahouston Park]], Glasgow, on the afternoon of Thursday 16 September, an evening prayer vigil in [[Hyde Park, London|Hyde Park]], London, on Saturday 18 September, and the Mass of Beatification of John Henry Newman in Cofton Park, [[Longbridge]], Birmingham, on Sunday 19 September.\n\nIn contrast with the previous Papal visit to Britain, that of Pope John Paul II in 1982, where anyone could attend open-air events, there was tight security for the 2010 Papal visit, with all attendees required to register in advance through their parish and to attend in a group with a 'Pilgrim Leader' from that parish, who as leader had the responsibility to vouch for all members of his group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepapalvisit.org.uk/2010-Visit/Visit-Event-Information/Attending-Events/How-can-I-see-the-Pope-in-the-UK |title=Article-How can I see the Pope in the UK? |publisher=Thepapalvisit.org.uk |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> All registered attendees received a 'Pilgrim Pass', required for admission to events. Non-Catholics were permitted to attend, by contacting their local parish.<ref>{{cite news|last=Beckford |first=Martin |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/the-pope/7873291/Non-Catholics-encouraged-to-take-part-in-Popes-visit-to-Britain.html |title=Non-Catholics encouraged to take part in Pope's visit to Britain |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=5 July 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010 |location=London}}</ref>\n\nThe Mass of Beatification in Cofton Park was originally arranged for [[Coventry Airport]], with a capacity of up to 250,000.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/coventry_warwickshire/8576825.stm |title=Mass to be held at Coventry Airport by Pope Benedict |publisher=BBC News |date=19 March 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> The planned event at the airport, which had seen 350,000 attend the visit of Pope John Paul II in 1982,<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=WggOAAAAIBAJ&sjid=l20DAAAAIBAJ&pg=6855,6458500]{{dead link|date=October 2010}}</ref> was the subject of an Isle of Man commemorative stamp.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholicherald.co.uk/catholiclife/2010/08/13/newman-and-papal-visit-receive-stamp-of-approval/ |title=Newman and papal visit receive stamp of approval |work=Catholicherald.co.uk |date=13 August 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> However the event was switched to the much smaller Cofton Park, [[Longbridge]], a switch that the church denied was to reduce costs, instead stating that Cofton Park had a greater connection to Newman, who had lived in the area and walked around the park.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/10509127 |title=Pope's UK visit 'could cost taxpayers \u00a312m' |work=BBC News |date=5 July 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n===Costs===\nThe visit of the Pope was the first state visit of a Pope to Britain; the visit of his predecessor, Pope John Paul II, had been a pastoral visit, and as such the British government did not pay the costs of that visit, although expenses were incurred by local governments in areas that he visited.<ref name=visit1982>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=Js8fAAAAIBAJ&sjid=BNkEAAAAIBAJ&pg=3067,6922073|title=The Fort Scott Tribune - Google News Archive Search|website=News.google.com|accessdate=26 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe final cost to the British taxpayer (excluding policing costs) of the visit was \u00a310 million.<ref name=\"guardian1\">{{cite news|author=Riazat Butt, religious affairs correspondent |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/oct/28/catholic-church-papal-visit-uk |title=Catholic church struggles with cost of pope's visit to UK |work=The Guardian |date=28 October 2010 |accessdate=5 December 2010 |location=London}}</ref><ref name=bbcCosts>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-11305217 |title=David Cameron offers 'warm welcome' to Pope in video |work=BBC News |date=14 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> The cost to the taxpayer was criticised, with a [[ComRes]] poll showing that 76% of people in the UK agreed with the statement that 'The Pope is a religious figure so the taxpayer should not be contributing to the costs of his visit'.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://campaigndirector.moodia.com/Client/Theos/Files/TheosPopePoll.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=24 September 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714113841/http://campaigndirector.moodia.com/Client/Theos/Files/TheosPopePoll.pdf |archivedate=14 July 2011  }}</ref> The cost was defended by the Archbishop of Westminster, leader of the Catholic Church in England and Wales, who said that it was right for the government to pay for official State Visits,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-11191386 |title=Archbishop says UK taxpayer should help fund Pope visit |work=BBC News |date=5 September 2010 |accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref> as well as by Lord Patten, who said that the cost compared favourably with the \u00a320 million spent on the [[2009 G-20 London Summit]].<ref>[https://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5i399yZzlQndOhF_77tHM7TeLAMEwD9I3OCP81]{{dead link|date=October 2010}}</ref> The visit was predicted to cost Edinburgh City council \u00a3400,000.<ref>{{cite web|last=Blackley |first=Michael |url=http://edinburghnews.scotsman.com/topstories/Pope39s-visit-to-Edinburgh-will.6456024.jp |title=Pope's visit to Edinburgh will cost city \u00a3400k - Edinburgh Evening News |publisher=edinburghnews.scotsman.com |date= |accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe financial benefits as well as costs of the Papal visit were reported, with the councillor coordinating the visit to Birmingham, which incurred \u00a380,000 in direct costs, estimated before the event a \u00a312.5 million boost to the city,<ref>{{cite news |author=Neil Elkes |url=http://www.birminghampost.net/dailybulletin/news2/2010/09/07/pope-visit-worth-12-5-million-to-birmingham-s-economy-65233-27221936/ |title=Pope visit worth \u00a312.5 million to Birmingham's economy |work=Birmingham Post |date=7 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> while Scott Taylor of Glasgow City Marketing Bureau said that there was a direct \u00a34.25m benefit to Glasgow, with further valuable publicity from the resultant media coverage of the city.\n\nIt was announced in July that attendees at events would be charged for a compulsory 'Pilgrim Pack', including commemorative items, in order to fund transport costs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholicherald.co.uk/news/2010/07/14/faithful-urged-to-apply-as-soon-as-possible-for-papal-visit-places/ |title=Catholics urged to apply as soon as possible for papal visit places |work=Catholicherald.co.uk |date=14 July 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> The costs were \u00a35 for the Hyde Park vigil (which did not include transport), \u00a325 to attend the Cofton Park event and \u00a320 to attend Bellahouston Park Mass.<ref>{{cite news|last=Beckford |first=Martin |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/the-pope/8000247/Pope-visit-Church-blames-early-start-for-low-ticket-sales.html |title=Pope visit: Church blames early start for low ticket sales |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=14 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010 |location=London}}</ref> The \u00a320 charge for Bellahouston Park was levied on the parish, which had discretion as to whether it recouped the cost directly from attendees.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepapalvisit.org.uk/content/download/9874/64535/file/PAPAL%20MASS%20BELLAHOUSTON%20FAQS.pdf|format=PDF|title=Papal Mass \u2013 Bellahouston Park : Thursday 16th September 2010 : Frequently Asked Questions|website=Thepapalvisit.org.uk|accessdate=26 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120309071414/http://www.thepapalvisit.org.uk/content/download/9874/64535/file/PAPAL%20MASS%20BELLAHOUSTON%20FAQS.pdf|archive-date=9 March 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> The charges were said to be the first ever levied for attending Papal events,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2010/07/28/catholics-pay-attend-big-events-england-popes-visit-september/ |title=Pilgrims must pay to attend 2 big events in England during pope's visit in September |work=Fox News |date=7 April 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> and came amid reports that the church was \u00a32.6 million short of its donation target.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/catholic-church-struggles-to-raise-funds-for-popes-visit-2052311.html | location=London | work=The Independent | title=Catholic Church struggles to raise funds for Pope's visit | first=Jerome | last=Taylor | date=14 August 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe cost to the Catholic Church was \u00a310 million,<ref name=\"guardian1\"/><ref name=bbcCosts /> against the \u00a37 million published on the Papal Visit website.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/catholic-church-struggles-to-raise-funds-for-popes-visit-2052311.html |title=Catholic Church struggles to raise funds for Pope's visit |work=The Independent |date=14 August 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010 |location=London |first=Jerome |last=Taylor}}</ref> The bulk of the \u00a37m, \u00a35.2m was for staging the three large-scale public events, a further \u00a30.6m for three smaller pastoral events, with the remaining \u00a31.2m covering evangelism, planning and communication.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thepapalvisit.com/Donate/Why-does-the-Church-need-to-raise-7m-and-what-will-it-be-spent-on |title=Article-Why does the Church need to raise \u00a37m and what will it be spent on? |work=Thepapalvisit.com |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> \u00a31.1 million was raised through a [[Pentecost]] Sunday special collection in churches and \u00a34m from wealthy individual donors. As of November 2010 the church had a \u00a33.5m shortfall, due to be repaid to the Government by April 2011.<ref name=\"guardian1\"/>\n\n==Visit==\n\n===Scotland===\n\n====16 September====\nPope Benedict XVI began his official visit in [[Scotland]] at [[Edinburgh Airport]] on 16 September, where he was greeted by [[Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh|Prince Philip]] and the Archbishops of [[Vincent Nichols|Westminster]] and [[Keith O'Brien|St Andrews and Edinburgh]]. He then met [[Elizabeth II|the Queen]] for the first time at [[Holyrood Palace]] in [[Edinburgh]], the Queen's official residence in Scotland, with the ceremonial [[Guard of honour]] formed by the [[Royal Regiment of Scotland]], the [[Royal Company of Archers]] and the [[High Constables and Guard of Honour of the Palace of Holyroodhouse|High Constables of Holyroodhouse]].\n\nIn his speech at Holyrood Palace, the Pope associated [[State atheism|atheist extremism]] with [[Nazism]], causing controversy.<ref name=audiencequeen>{{cite web|url=https://www.vatican.va/holy_father/benedict_xvi/speeches/2010/september/documents/hf_ben-xvi_spe_20100916_incontro-autorita_en.html |title=Audience with H.M. The Queen and State Reception Address of His Holiness Benedict XVI |publisher=Vatican.va |date=16 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref><ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-11332515 Row after Pope's remarks on atheism and Nazis] ''[[BBC News]]'', 16 September 2010</ref><ref>[http://www.digitaljournal.com/article/297690 Fury as Pope appears to equate UK atheism with Nazism] ''Digital Journal'', 17 September 2010</ref><ref>[http://content.usatoday.com/communities/Religion/post/2010/09/pope-benedict-atheists-nazis-richard-dawkins/1 Atheist Dawkins rages at pope tying godless, Nazis] ''[[USA Today]]'', 17 September 2010</ref> The Pope said:\n{{cquote|Even in our own lifetime, we can recall how [[United Kingdom|Britain]] and her leaders stood against a [[Nazi Germany|Nazi tyranny]] that wished to eradicate [[God]] from society and denied our [[humanism|common humanity]] to many, especially the [[Jews]], who were thought unfit to live. I also recall the regime\u2019s attitude to Christian pastors and religious who spoke the truth in love, opposed the Nazis and paid for that opposition with their lives. As we reflect on the sobering lessons of the atheist extremism of the twentieth century, let us never forget how the exclusion of God, religion and virtue from public life leads ultimately to a truncated vision of man and of society and thus to a \u201creductive vision of the person and his destiny\u201d<ref name=\"audiencequeen\" />}}\n\nA parade for [[Saint Ninian]]'s day was held at 11am, the route beginning on Regent Road, Edinburgh, and proceeding along [[Princes Street]]. Attendance was open to all, with a parade of school children and figures from Scotland's Christian history, in honour of St Ninian of Galloway, who brought Christianity to Scotland from Rome in the fifth century. After the parade, which was attended by around 125,000 people, the Pope proceeded by Popemobile <ref name=popemobile>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepapalvisit.org.uk/2010-Visit/Visit-Event-Information/Popemobile-Routes |title=Pope Benedict XVI-Popemobile Routes |work=Thepapalvisit.org.uk |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> to have lunch with [[Keith O'Brien|Cardinal O'Brien]] at his home before travelling by car to [[Glasgow]].\n\nThe Pope was greeted by the [[Mario Conti|Archbishop of Glasgow]] for the ticketed Mass of the Feast of St Ninian in [[Bellahouston Park]]. [[Susan Boyle]] and [[Pop Idol]] winner [[Michelle McManus]] performed before the start of the mass.{{citation needed|date=December 2018}} Attendance was around 65,000 people.<ref>{{cite news|last=Cramb |first=Auslan |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/the-pope/8007705/Pope-visit-thousands-make-the-pilgrimage-to-Bellahouston-Park.html |title=Pope visit: thousands make the pilgrimage to Bellahouston Park |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=16 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010 |location=London}}</ref> The Pope flew from [[Glasgow Airport]] to London [[Heathrow airport]] that evening.<ref name=itinerary>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepapalvisit.org.uk/2010-Visit/Events-Timeline |title=Article-Events Timeline / 2010 Visit |work=Thepapalvisit.org.uk |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n===England===\n\n====17 September====\nOn the second day of his visit to the United Kingdom the Pope began the day with a private Mass in the chapel at [[54 Parkside]], Wimbledon, south west London, the official residence of the [[Nunciature to Great Britain|Apostolic Nunciature to Great Britain]]. His first public engagement was a celebration of Catholic education with a visit to address educators and students at [[St Mary's University, Twickenham]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stmarys.ac.uk/about/papal-visit/overview.aspx|title=The 2010 Papal Visit &#124; St Mary's University, Twickenham |publisher=Stmarys.ac.uk |date=17 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> which was followed by a meeting with people of faith in the University's Waldegrave Drawing Room.\n\nHe became the first Pope to enter [[Lambeth Palace]], where he met the [[Rowan Williams|Archbishop of Canterbury]].{{citation needed|date=December 2018}} He made the journey from Lambeth Palace to the [[Palace of Westminster]] by Popemobile,<ref name=popemobile /> making an Address to Civil Society from the spot in [[Westminster Hall]] where [[Thomas More|St Thomas More]] died a martyr's death in 1535, being accused of high treason for holding to his Catholic faith in refusing to acknowledge the validity of the [[First Succession Act|Act of Succession]].\n\nIn the evening there was an ecumenical celebration of evening prayer at [[Westminster Abbey]] with representatives from all the main Christian churches including the Greek Orthodox, Coptic and Free Churches. He later venerated the tomb of [[Edward the Confessor]] at the Abbey.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.westminster-abbey.org/press/news/news/2010/september/historic-abbey-service-for-pope |title=Historic Abbey Service for Pope |publisher=Westminster Abbey |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n====18 September====\n[[File:Hyde Park Vigil.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Pope Benedict leads the vigil in Hyde Park.]]\n[[File:Hyde Park Vigil 80000.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Some of the 80,000 attending the vigil in Hyde Park.]]\nThe Pope began the day with meetings with [[David Cameron]], Prime Minister, [[Nick Clegg]], as Deputy Prime Minister, and [[Harriet Harman]], Acting Leader of the Opposition. This was followed with morning Mass in [[Westminster Cathedral]]. In his sermon, the Pope referenced [[Catholic sexual scandal in the United Kingdom|sexual abuse by priests]], saying: \"Here, too, I think of the immense suffering caused by the abuse of children, especially within the church and by her ministers. Above all, I express my deep sorrow to the innocent victims of these unspeakable crimes\", saying \"I also acknowledge with you the shame and humiliation which all of us have suffered because of these sins\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/sep/18/pope-benedict-sermon-westminster-cathedral |title=Pope Benedict XVI's sermon at Westminster Cathedral |work=The Guardian |date= 18 September 2010|accessdate=16 October 2010 |location=London}}</ref>\n\nAfter Mass, the Pope used the middle part of the day to meet five victims of child sex abuse at the Apostolic Nunciature, apologising to them and describing the Church's measures to protect young people.<ref>{{cite news|last=Pigott |first=Robert |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-11361749 |title=What has the Pope's visit achieved? 19 September 2010 |work=BBC News |date=19 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> The meeting had been planned before the Pope's visit, and time was left free in his schedule to allow for it.{{citation needed|date=December 2018}}\n\nIn the evening the Pope visited St Peter's Residence for Older People, run by [[Little Sisters of the Poor]]. The Pope travelled to the day's main event, the ticketed Hyde Park Prayer Vigil on the Eve of the Beatification of Cardinal Newman, by Popemobile.<ref name=popemobile /> The vigil was attended by 80,000 people.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/uk-world-news/2010/09/19/the-pope-apologises-to-abuse-victims-as-80-000-pray-in-london-park-86908-22572592/ |title=The Pope apologises to abuse victims as 80,000 pray in London park |work=The Daily Record |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> The Pope's speech described Newman's life's work \"as a struggle against the growing tendency to view religion as a purely private and subjective matter, a question of personal opinion\", stating that it was a lesson for today, in which \"an intellectual and moral relativism threatens to sap the very foundations of our society\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholicherald.co.uk/news/2010/09/18/papal-visit-2010-popes-address-at-hyde-park-vigil-full-text/ |title=Papal Visit 2010: Pope\u2019s Address at Hyde Park Vigil \u2013 full text |work=Catholicherald.co.uk |date=18 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n====19 September====\n[[File:Stage preparations, Cofton Park, 090910, cropped.JPG|thumb|right|Stage being prepared for ceremony in Cofton Park]]\nThe final day of the Pope's visit saw the Pope fly by helicopter from London to [[Birmingham]] for the main event of his visit, the [[beatification]] of [[Cardinal (Catholicism)|Cardinal]] [[John Henry Newman]] in [[Cofton Park]] in Birmingham. Local residents were required to carry vehicle passes as well as to carry proof of identity in order to leave their own homes.<ref>{{cite news|last=Peek |first=Sitala |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-birmingham-11303899 |title=Pope's visit: historic event or one to avoid? |work=BBC News |date=15 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> Attendance at the event was approximately 55,000,<ref>{{cite web |last=Hesketh |first=Jane |url=http://www.itv.com/central-west/pope-at-cofton-park51831/ |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130127024240/http://www.itv.com/central-west/pope-at-cofton-park51831/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=27 January 2013 |title=Central Regional News (ITV Central Tonight) - ITV Local |publisher=Itv.com |date=19 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010 }}</ref> a figure said to have been reduced by the requirement to arrive at the location between 3am and 7am on special coaches for the 10am start.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/local-national/uk/administration-problems-blamed-for-pope-visit-ticket-slump-14947215.html |title='Administration problems' blamed for Pope visit ticket slump |work=Belfast Telegraph |date=13 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe Cofton Park Mass was followed by a private visit to [[Birmingham Oratory]], founded by John Henry Newman.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thepapalvisit.org.uk/2010-Visit/Visit-Event-Information/Itinerary/19-September-2010/The-Birmingham-Oratory |title=The Birmingham Oratory |work=Thepapalvisit.org.uk |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100920163138/http://www.thepapalvisit.org.uk/2010-Visit/Visit-Event-Information/Itinerary/19-September-2010/The-Birmingham-Oratory |archive-date=20 September 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The visit was preceded by controversy due to the exiling of three priests to monasteries in separate parts of the world.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/the-pope/7956204/Popes-visit-could-be-overshadowed-by-exile-of-Birmingham-priests.html | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | title=Pope's visit could be overshadowed by exile of Birmingham priests | first=Martin | last=Beckford | date=21 August 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe visit concluded with lunch and a meeting with the bishops of England, Scotland and Wales at [[St Mary's College, Oscott]]. The Pope gave a final speech at [[Birmingham Airport, England|Birmingham Airport]], before departing for [[Rome]] on a chartered [[Alitalia]] Airbus A320. [[British Airways]], as UK flag carrier, would have been the usual choice for a state Papal visit, but they were reportedly rejected due to concerns about strikes.{{citation needed|date=December 2018}}\n\n===Other events===\nThe Pope's schedule reportedly included free time to allow for the 83-year-old to take naps.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/popes-uk-visit-schedule-to-contain-nap-breaks-2055909.html | location=London | work=The Independent | title=Pope's UK visit schedule to contain nap breaks | first=Jerome | last=Taylor | date=18 August 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn conjunction with the visit, an exhibition of [[Sistine Chapel#Raphael's tapestries|Raphael's tapestries]] for the [[Sistine Chapel]] took place at London's [[Victoria and Albert Museum]] from 8 September to 17 October 2010 where they were displayed for the first time alongside the [[Raphael cartoons]] used to make them; the cartoons having been in the British [[Royal Collection]] since 1623. This followed a reported scaling-back of earlier plans for a large exhibition of Vatican artworks at London's [[Royal Academy]].<ref>{{Cite news| url=http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/news/damianthompson/100047995/popes-visit-what-happened-to-the-major-exhibition-of-vatican-treasures-at-the-royal-academy/ | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | title=Pope's visit: What happened to the major exhibition of Vatican treasures at the Royal Academy? | date=21 July 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Anti-terrorism arrests==\nOn 17 September 2010 the [[Metropolitan Police]] arrested five street cleaners under the [[Terrorism Act 2000]] in a pre-dawn raid at a London cleaning depot, in a suspected terrorist plot against the Pope on the second day of his state visit; a sixth person was arrested later in the day at his home \"on suspicion of the commission, preparation or instigation of acts of terrorism\".<ref>{{Cite news| title = Six held over Pope terror alert | date = 17 September 2010 | url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-11346001 | work = BBC News | accessdate = 17 September 2010}}</ref> The men, aged between 26 and 50, had been working as street cleaners for contractors [[Veolia Environnement]], on behalf of [[Westminster City Council]] and were based at the Chiltern Street depot in [[Marylebone]].\n\nThe suspects were questioned at an unidentified London police station. The police did not uncover any hazardous items during an initial search of the business premises and other properties.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5i399yZzlQndOhF_77tHM7TeLAMEwD9I9RPO00 | location=London | agency=Associated Press | title=6 arrested in UK in alleged terror threat to pope | first=Nicole | last=Winfield | date=17 September 2010}}</ref>\n\nAccording to police some of the suspects were thought to be immigrants to Britain, from a variety of nations including a number from Algeria.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/the-pope/8010002/Pope-visit-sixth-man-arrested-over-alleged-assassination-plot.html | location=London | work=The Telegraph | title=Pope visit: sixth man arrested over alleged assassination plot | first=Duncan | last=Gardham | date=17 September 2010}}</ref>\n\nAll the men were released without charge before the Pope's visit ended. It turned out they were arrested after joking about how the [[Popemobile]] could not withstand an [[Rocket-propelled grenade|RPG]] attack.{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n\n==Response==\n\n===Support===\n[[File:Flag of the Vatican City flying in Bradford (21st September 2010).jpg|thumb|upright|The [[Flag of Vatican City]] flying in [[Bradford]], [[West Yorkshire]] in honour of the papal visit.]]\nThe visit saw support from a range of people and organisations, including several leaders within other religions. The President of the [[Ahmadiyya Muslim Community]] UK, Rafiq Hayat stated that \"Religious leaders have a pivotal role to play in promoting peace and serving humanity. Indeed religions have far more commonalities than differences and we welcome moves that will help forge unity and foster greater understanding.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sys-con.com/node/1537040|title=UK Muslim Leader Welcomes Visit by Pope|date= 17 September 2010|accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref>\n\nVivian Wineman, President of the [[Board of Deputies of British Jews]], said \"In an age where scepticism and ill-will towards religion is rising, it will be an excellent opportunity to demonstrate that there is much to unite people of faith and much that can be achieved when we work together for the greater good not only of our members, but for society as a whole.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rcdow.org.uk/papalvisit/blog/?25|title=Papal visit to Great Britain|date=15 September 2010|accessdate=15 September 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928133035/http://www.rcdow.org.uk/papalvisit/blog/?25|archive-date=28 September 2011|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nMedia coverage of the visit, which was largely critical before the event, was more positive during and following the Pope's visit. A BBC News correspondent noted that 'there was a tangible sense of relief, even of euphoria, among Pope Benedict's entourage during the return flight to Rome from Birmingham'.<ref>{{cite news|last=Willey |first=David |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-11372501 |title=Pope's visit is deemed to challenge stereotypes |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=20 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n===Opposition===\n{{Further|Anti-Catholicism in the United Kingdom|Criticism of the Catholic Church}}\n[[File:2010 protest the pope rally.png|thumb|right|Protest during the Pope's visit]]\n\nThe visit was opposed by a range of people and organisations including some Protestants, LGBT and secular groups due to a number of reasons, such as the Church's policies on the [[ordination of women]], [[Homosexuality and Roman Catholicism|homosexuality]], [[Catholic contraception|contraception]] and [[Roman Catholic Church and AIDS|AIDS]], as well as complaints over [[Catholic sex abuse cases|historical sexual abuse of children by Catholic priests]].<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite news|last=Wynne |first=Jonathan |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/the-pope/7981933/Public-believes-taxpayers-should-not-fund-papal-visit.html |title=Public believes taxpayers should not fund papal visit |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=5 September 2010 |accessdate=17 September 2010 |location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2010/06/03/church-costs-for-popes-visit-out-of-control/ |title=Church costs for Pope\u2019s visit \u2018out of control\u2019 - from Pink News |work=Pink News |date=3 June 2010 |accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref> Former DUP leader [[Ian Paisley]] (known for his staunch [[Anti-Catholicism]] in [[Northern Ireland]]) called the visit a \"mistake\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/10484122 |title=Pope Benedict XVI UK visit a 'mistake' says Ian Paisley |work=BBC News |date=2 July 2010 |accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref> and the principal of Scotland's [[Free Church Training College]] said the visit airbrushed the [[Protestant Reformation]] out of history and dishonoured reformer and nationalist [[John Knox]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholicherald.co.uk/news/2010/07/14/faithful-urged-to-apply-as-soon-as-possible-for-papal-visit-places/ |title=Catholics urged to apply as soon as possible for papal visit places |work=Catholicherald.co.uk |date=14 July 2010 |accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref> On the eve of the visit, a letter by 50 public figures argued that the Pope's tour should not have been accorded the status of a state visit.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/sep/15/pope-uk-state-visit-protest Pope's visit: pontiff should not be 'honoured' with state visit] ''[[The Guardian]]'', 15 September 2010</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/sep/15/harsh-judgments-on-pope-religion |title=Letter by 50 public figures for not giving the honour of state to Pope |work=The Guardian |date= 15 September 2010|accessdate=16 October 2010 |location=London}}</ref>\n\nA number of groups, including the [[British Humanist Association]] and the [[National Secular Society]] organised a campaign of protests against the visit.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.protest-the-pope.org.uk/ |title=Protest The Pope |publisher=Protest The Pope |accessdate=18 September 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100813034024/http://www.protest-the-pope.org.uk/ |archivedate=13 August 2010  }}</ref> The Roman Catholic [[pressure group]] \"Catholic Women's Ordination\" arranged for London buses to carry advertisements encouraging the Pope to \"Ordain Women Now\"<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/jul/22/london-bus-female-ordination-pope | location=London | work=The Guardian | title=London buses to carry female ordination advert during pope's visit. | first=Riazat | last=Butt | date=22 July 2010}}</ref> and also planned further unspecified lobbying action. Religious and secular correspondents noted that only 3 women appeared at Lambeth Palace to support the ordination of women.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic-womens-ordination.org.uk/news.htm#Pope |title=Local Groups |work=Catholic-womens-ordination.org.uk |date= |accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Richard dawkins speaking at the protest the pope rally 2010.png|thumb|right|[[Richard Dawkins]] speaking at the protest, with [[Peter Tatchell]] on the left at the back.]]\n[[Richard Dawkins]] gave a speech to over 10,000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/sep/18/pope-benedict-xvi-protest|title=Protest the Pope rally sees 10,000 march through London's streets|first=Tracy|last=Mcveigh|date=18 September 2010|accessdate=26 November 2017|website=Theguardian.com}}</ref> people at the \"Protest the Pope\" rally, declaring the pope \"an enemy of humanity\", and countering the Pope's claim that [[the holocaust]] was the result of atheism by arguing that [[Hitler]] was a Roman Catholic.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://richarddawkins.net/articles/521113-ratzinger-is-an-enemy-of-humanity |title=Dawkins speech |publisher=Richarddawkins.net |date=22 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Science |url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/punctuated-equilibrium/2010/sep/20/1 |title=Richard Dawkins' unedited speech at 'Protest the Pope' march in London |work=The Guardian |date= 20 September 2010|accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> Dawkins had previously supported a call for the Pope's arrest for \"crimes against humanity\", an idea first proposed by [[Christopher Hitchens]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://richarddawkins.net/videos/5434-christopher-hitchens-arrest-the-pope | title=Christopher Hitchens: Arrest The Pope!}}</ref> and described by a former editor of the ''[[Catholic Herald]]'' as \"lunatic\",<ref>{{Cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/8614232.stm | work=BBC News | title=Dawkins backs plan to arrest Pope | date=13 April 2010}}</ref> and human rights lawyer [[Geoffrey Robertson]] was reported to have looked at options to [[Geoffrey Robertson#Putting Pope Benedict XVI on trial|charge the Pope]] over his alleged cover-up of sexual abuse in the Catholic Church.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/belief/2010/apr/13/pope-prosecution-dawkins |title=The pope should stand trial |work=The Guardian |date= 13 April 2010|accessdate=18 September 2010 |location=London |first=Richard |last=Dawkins}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2010, the UK government announced plans to change the law on universal jurisdiction to prevent the issue of an arrest warrant.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/article/295022 |title=UK government acts to prevent arrest of Pope |publisher=Digitaljournal.com |date=23 July 2010 |accessdate=18 September 2010}}</ref> Attempts to make a citizen's arrest on the Pope were abandoned by [[Peter Tatchell]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/peter-tatchell-scraps-idea-of-making-citizens-arrest-on-the-pope-2074273.html |title=Peter Tatchell scraps idea of making citizen's arrest on the Pope |work=The Independent |date= 9 September 2010|accessdate=17 September 2010 |location=London |first=Jerome |last=Taylor}}</ref> Members of [[Muslims Against Crusades]] protested against the Pope in London.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Multiple authors|title=Pope Benedict XVI's UK visit: Day three|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/gallery/2010/sep/18/pope-benedict-xvi-london|accessdate=10 April 2016|work=The Guardian|agency=Reuters|date=18 September 2010}}</ref> ''The Guardian'' reported that around 10,000 protesters marched in London against the Pope's visit on 18 September 2010.<ref>{{cite news|author=Tracy Mcveigh |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/sep/18/pope-benedict-xvi-protest |title=Protest the Pope rally sees 10,000 march through London's streets |work=The Guardian |date= 18 September 2010|accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Media coverage==\nThe [[BBC]] marked the visit with documentaries including:<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/mandrake/7866684/Pope-Benedict-XVI-about-to-be-put-on-trial-by-the-BBC.html | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | title=Pope Benedict XVI about to be put on trial by the BBC | first=Tim | last=Walker | date=2 July 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2010/aug/03/bbc-papal-visit | location=London | work=The Guardian | title=BBC to mark Pope's UK visit with documentary on clerical abuse scandals | first=Tara | last=Conlan | date=3 August 2010}}</ref>\n\n* ''Vatican: The Hidden World'', a profile of the [[Holy See|Vatican]] with unprecedented access given\n* ''The Real Joseph Ratzinger'', a papal profile\n*''Newman: Saint or Sinner?'', a documentary about [[Cardinal Newman]]\n*''Benedict - Trials of a Pope'', a documentary about the life of the Pope<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00ttj16 |title=Benedict: Trials of a Pope |publisher=BBC |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|United Kingdom|Catholicism|Christianity}}\n*[[List of journeys of Pope Benedict XVI]]\n*[[Roman Catholicism in the United Kingdom]]\n*[[Foreign Office papal visit memo]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikinews|Pope Benedict XVI heads to the UK amid protests}}\n{{Commons category}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20111119175338/http://thepapalvisit.co.uk/ Apostolic journey to Britain] - official website from [[Catholic Church in England and Wales]]\n*[https://www.vatican.va/holy_father/benedict_xvi/travels/2010/index_regno-unito_en.htm Apostolic Journey to the United Kingdom] - official website from the [[Holy See]]\n\n<br />\n{{Benedict XVI}}\n{{Elizabeth II}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pope Benedict Xvi's Visit To The United Kingdom}}\n[[Category:Pope Benedict XVI]]\n[[Category:Foreign relations of the Holy See]]\n[[Category:History of Christianity in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:2010 in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:2010 in Christianity]]\n[[Category:Foreign trips by popes|Benedict XVI, United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Holy See\u2013United Kingdom relations]]\n[[Category:Catholic Church in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Diplomatic visits to the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:September 2010 events in the United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=November 2013}}\n[[File:Papal visit in Westminster (17th September 2010).jpg|thumb|right|300px|The papal visit in [[Westminster]], [[London]]]]\n\nThe state visit of Pope Benedict XVI to the United Kingdom was held from 16 to 19 September 2010 and was the first visit by a Pope to Britain after [[Pope John Paul II]] made a [[Pope John Paul II's visit to the United Kingdom|pastoral, rather than state, visit]] in 1982. The visit included the [[beatification]] of [[John Henry Newman|Cardinal Newman]] as a \"pastoral highlight\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.christiantoday.com/article/catholic.church.seeks.to.clarify.purpose.of.popes.visit/26105.htm |title=Catholic Church seeks to clarify purpose of Pope\u2019s visit 124; Christian News on Christian Today |publisher=Christiantoday.com |date=15 June 2010 |accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref>\n\nPope Benedict's visit included meetings with [[Elizabeth II]] ([[Queen of the United Kingdom]] and [[Supreme Governor]] of the [[Church of England]]), the [[First Minister of Scotland]] [[Alex Salmond]], [[Archbishop of Canterbury]] [[Rowan Williams]], [[British Prime Minister|Prime Minister]] and [[UK Conservative Party|Conservative Party]] leader [[David Cameron]], and leaders of the other main political parties.\n\nThe Pope's itinerary included open air Masses in Glasgow and Birmingham, a youth vigil in Hyde Park in London, and Mass at Westminster Cathedral in London, attended by over 200,000 people.\n\n==Invitation and planning==\n{{Expand section|date=September 2010}}\nAn invitation to visit Britain was extended to [[Pope Benedict XVI]] by then [[Prime Minister]] [[Gordon Brown]] in February 2009. The Pope's visit featured in the debates between party leaders in April 2010, prior to the [[2010 United Kingdom general election]], where all three party leaders expressed support for the visit, while expressing disagreement with some of the Pope's views.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/shared/bsp/hi/pdfs/23_04_10_seconddebate.pdf Second prime ministerial debate, 22 April 2010, Transcript] ''[[BBC News]]'' 23 April 2010</ref>\n\nAnjoum Noorani of the [[Foreign and Commonwealth Office]] was originally a key contact between the [[British Government]] and the papal visit team. However, he was suspended from overseas postings and given a final warning, to last for five years, after approving the [[Foreign Office papal visit memo|sending of a memo]] written by Steven Mulvain, a 23-year-old Oxford graduate, mocking the visit.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/7804506/Diplomat-who-sent-Pope-condom-memo-given-final-warning-and-banned-from-overseas-postings.html | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | title=Diplomat who sent Pope 'condom' memo given final warning and banned from overseas postings | first=Martin | last=Beckford | date=6 June 2010}}</ref> Subsequently the new Government appointed liberal Catholic<ref>{{Cite news| url=http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/news/damianthompson/100046639/lord-patten-im-like-lot-of-catholics-i-dont-agree-with-everything-the-vatican-says/ | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | title=Lord Patten: 'I'm like lot of Catholics. I don't agree with everything the Vatican says' | date=8 July 2010}}</ref> [[Chris Patten|Lord Patten]] to get the visit back on track following a series of setbacks.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/7803820/Lord-Patten-will-co-ordinate-Pope-Benedict-XVIs-trip-to-Britain.html | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | title=Lord Patten will co-ordinate Pope Benedict XVI's trip to Britain | first=Martin | last=Beckford | date=4 June 2010}}</ref>\n\n===Ticketed events===\nThere were three specific ticketed events open to the public during the Pope's visit. These were a [[Mass (liturgy)|Mass]] in [[Bellahouston Park]], Glasgow, on the afternoon of Thursday 16 September, an evening prayer vigil in [[Hyde Park, London|Hyde Park]], London, on Saturday 18 September, and the Mass of Beatification of John Henry Newman in Cofton Park, [[Longbridge]], Birmingham on Sunday 19 September.\n\nIn contrast with the previous Papal visit to Britain, that of Pope John Paul II in 1982, where anyone could attend open-air events, there was tight security for the 2010 Papal visit, with all attendees required to register in advance through their parish and to attend in a group with a 'Pilgrim Leader' from that parish, who as leader had the responsibility to vouch for all members of his group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepapalvisit.org.uk/2010-Visit/Visit-Event-Information/Attending-Events/How-can-I-see-the-Pope-in-the-UK |title=Article-How can I see the Pope in the UK? |publisher=Thepapalvisit.org.uk |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> All registered attendees received a 'Pilgrim Pass', required for admission to events. Non-Catholics were permitted to attend, by contacting their local parish.<ref>{{cite news|last=Beckford |first=Martin |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/the-pope/7873291/Non-Catholics-encouraged-to-take-part-in-Popes-visit-to-Britain.html |title=Non-Catholics encouraged to take part in Pope's visit to Britain |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=5 July 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010 |location=London}}</ref>\n\nThe mass of Beatification in Cofton Park was originally arranged for [[Coventry Airport]], with a capacity of up to 250,000.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/coventry_warwickshire/8576825.stm |title=Mass to be held at Coventry Airport by Pope Benedict |publisher=BBC News |date=19 March 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> The planned event at the airport, which had seen 350,000 attend the visit of Pope John Paul II in 1982,<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=WggOAAAAIBAJ&sjid=l20DAAAAIBAJ&pg=6855,6458500]{{dead link|date=October 2010}}</ref> was the subject of an Isle of Man commemorative stamp.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholicherald.co.uk/catholiclife/2010/08/13/newman-and-papal-visit-receive-stamp-of-approval/ |title=Newman and papal visit receive stamp of approval |work=Catholicherald.co.uk |date=13 August 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> However the event was switched to the much smaller Cofton Park, [[Longbridge]], a switch that the church denied was to reduce costs, instead stating that Cofton Park had a greater connection to Newman, who had lived in the area and walked around the park.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/10509127 |title=Pope's UK visit 'could cost taxpayers \u00a312m' |work=BBC News |date=5 July 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n===Costs===\nThe visit of the Pope was the first state visit of a Pope to Britain; the visit of his predecessor, Pope John Paul II, had been a pastoral visit, and as such the British government did not pay the costs of that visit, although expenses were incurred by local governments in areas that he visited.<ref name=visit1982>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=Js8fAAAAIBAJ&sjid=BNkEAAAAIBAJ&pg=3067,6922073|title=The Fort Scott Tribune - Google News Archive Search|website=News.google.com|accessdate=26 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe final cost to the British taxpayer (excluding policing costs) of the visit was \u00a310 million.<ref name=\"guardian1\">{{cite news|author=Riazat Butt, religious affairs correspondent |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/oct/28/catholic-church-papal-visit-uk |title=Catholic church struggles with cost of pope's visit to UK |work=The Guardian |date=28 October 2010 |accessdate=5 December 2010 |location=London}}</ref><ref name=bbcCosts>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-11305217 |title=David Cameron offers 'warm welcome' to Pope in video |work=BBC News |date=14 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> The cost to the taxpayer was criticised, with a [[ComRes]] poll showing that 76% of people in the UK agreed with the statement that 'The Pope is a religious figure so the taxpayer should not be contributing to the costs of his visit'.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://campaigndirector.moodia.com/Client/Theos/Files/TheosPopePoll.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=24 September 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714113841/http://campaigndirector.moodia.com/Client/Theos/Files/TheosPopePoll.pdf |archivedate=14 July 2011  }}</ref> The cost was defended by the Archbishop of Westminster, leader of the Catholic Church in England and Wales, who said that it was right for the government to pay for official State Visits,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-11191386 |title=Archbishop says UK taxpayer should help fund Pope visit |work=BBC News |date=5 September 2010 |accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref> as well as by Lord Patten, who said that the cost compared favourably with the \u00a320 million spent on the [[2009 G-20 London Summit]].<ref>[https://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5i399yZzlQndOhF_77tHM7TeLAMEwD9I3OCP81]{{dead link|date=October 2010}}</ref> The visit was predicted to cost Edinburgh City council \u00a3400,000.<ref>{{cite web|last=Blackley |first=Michael |url=http://edinburghnews.scotsman.com/topstories/Pope39s-visit-to-Edinburgh-will.6456024.jp |title=Pope's visit to Edinburgh will cost city \u00a3400k - Edinburgh Evening News |publisher=edinburghnews.scotsman.com |date= |accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe financial benefits as well as costs of the Papal visit were reported, with the councillor coordinating the visit to Birmingham, which incurred \u00a380,000 in direct costs, estimated before the event a \u00a312.5 million boost to the city,<ref>{{cite news |author=Neil Elkes |url=http://www.birminghampost.net/dailybulletin/news2/2010/09/07/pope-visit-worth-12-5-million-to-birmingham-s-economy-65233-27221936/ |title=Pope visit worth \u00a312.5 million to Birmingham's economy |work=Birmingham Post |date=7 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> while Scott Taylor of Glasgow City Marketing Bureau said that there was a direct \u00a34.25m benefit to Glasgow, with further valuable publicity from the resultant media coverage of the city.\n\nIt was announced in July that attendees at events would be charged for a compulsory 'Pilgrim Pack', including commemorative items, in order to fund transport costs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholicherald.co.uk/news/2010/07/14/faithful-urged-to-apply-as-soon-as-possible-for-papal-visit-places/ |title=Catholics urged to apply as soon as possible for papal visit places |work=Catholicherald.co.uk |date=14 July 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> The costs were \u00a35 for the Hyde Park vigil (which did not include transport), \u00a325 to attend the Cofton Park event and \u00a320 to attend Bellahouston Park mass.<ref>{{cite news|last=Beckford |first=Martin |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/the-pope/8000247/Pope-visit-Church-blames-early-start-for-low-ticket-sales.html |title=Pope visit: Church blames early start for low ticket sales |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=14 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010 |location=London}}</ref> The \u00a320 charge for Bellahouston Park was levied on the parish, which had discretion as to whether it recouped the cost directly from attendees.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepapalvisit.org.uk/content/download/9874/64535/file/PAPAL%20MASS%20BELLAHOUSTON%20FAQS.pdf|format=PDF|title=Papal Mass \u2013 Bellahouston Park : Thursday 16th September 2010 : Frequently Asked Questions|website=Thepapalvisit.org.uk|accessdate=26 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120309071414/http://www.thepapalvisit.org.uk/content/download/9874/64535/file/PAPAL%20MASS%20BELLAHOUSTON%20FAQS.pdf|archive-date=9 March 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> The charges were said to be the first ever levied for attending Papal events,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2010/07/28/catholics-pay-attend-big-events-england-popes-visit-september/ |title=Pilgrims must pay to attend 2 big events in England during pope's visit in September |work=Fox News |date=7 April 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> and came amid reports that the church was \u00a32.6 million short of its donation target.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/catholic-church-struggles-to-raise-funds-for-popes-visit-2052311.html | location=London | work=The Independent | title=Catholic Church struggles to raise funds for Pope's visit | first=Jerome | last=Taylor | date=14 August 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe cost to the Catholic Church was \u00a310 million,<ref name=\"guardian1\"/><ref name=bbcCosts /> against the \u00a37 million published on the Papal Visit website.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/catholic-church-struggles-to-raise-funds-for-popes-visit-2052311.html |title=Catholic Church struggles to raise funds for Pope's visit |work=The Independent |date=14 August 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010 |location=London |first=Jerome |last=Taylor}}</ref> The bulk of the \u00a37m, \u00a35.2m was for staging the three large-scale public events, a further \u00a30.6m for three smaller pastoral events, with the remaining \u00a31.2m covering evangelism, planning and communication.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thepapalvisit.com/Donate/Why-does-the-Church-need-to-raise-7m-and-what-will-it-be-spent-on |title=Article-Why does the Church need to raise \u00a37m and what will it be spent on? |work=Thepapalvisit.com |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> \u00a31.1 million was raised through a [[Pentecost]] Sunday special collection in churches and \u00a34m from wealthy individual donors. As of November 2010 the church had a \u00a33.5m shortfall, due to be repaid to the Government by April 2011.<ref name=\"guardian1\"/>\n\n==Visit==\n\n===Scotland===\n\n====16 September====\nPope Benedict XVI began his official visit in [[Scotland]] at [[Edinburgh Airport]] on 16 September, where he was greeted by [[Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh|Prince Philip]] and the Archbishops of [[Vincent Nichols|Westminster]] and [[Keith O'Brien|St Andrews and Edinburgh]]. He then met [[Elizabeth II|the Queen]] for the first time at [[Holyrood Palace]] in [[Edinburgh]], the Queen's official residence in Scotland, with the ceremonial [[Guard of honour]] formed by the [[Royal Regiment of Scotland]], the [[Royal Company of Archers]] and the [[High Constables and Guard of Honour of the Palace of Holyroodhouse|High Constables of Holyroodhouse]].\n\nIn his speech at Holyrood Palace, the Pope associated [[State atheism|atheist extremism]] with [[Nazism]], causing controversy.<ref name=audiencequeen>{{cite web|url=https://www.vatican.va/holy_father/benedict_xvi/speeches/2010/september/documents/hf_ben-xvi_spe_20100916_incontro-autorita_en.html |title=Audience with H.M. The Queen and State Reception Address of His Holiness Benedict XVI |publisher=Vatican.va |date=16 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref><ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-11332515 Row after Pope's remarks on atheism and Nazis] ''[[BBC News]]'', 16 September 2010</ref><ref>[http://www.digitaljournal.com/article/297690 Fury as Pope appears to equate UK atheism with Nazism] ''Digital Journal'', 17 September 2010</ref><ref>[http://content.usatoday.com/communities/Religion/post/2010/09/pope-benedict-atheists-nazis-richard-dawkins/1 Atheist Dawkins rages at pope tying godless, Nazis] ''[[USA Today]]'', 17 September 2010</ref> The Pope said:\n{{cquote|Even in our own lifetime, we can recall how [[United Kingdom|Britain]] and her leaders stood against a [[Nazi Germany|Nazi tyranny]] that wished to eradicate [[God]] from society and denied our [[humanism|common humanity]] to many, especially the [[Jews]], who were thought unfit to live. I also recall the regime\u2019s attitude to Christian pastors and religious who spoke the truth in love, opposed the Nazis and paid for that opposition with their lives. As we reflect on the sobering lessons of the atheist extremism of the twentieth century, let us never forget how the exclusion of God, religion and virtue from public life leads ultimately to a truncated vision of man and of society and thus to a \u201creductive vision of the person and his destiny\u201d<ref name=\"audiencequeen\" />}}\n\nA parade for [[Saint Ninian]]'s day was held at 11am, the route beginning on Regent Road, Edinburgh, and proceeding along [[Princes Street]]. Attendance was open to all, with a parade of school children and figures from Scotland's Christian history, in honour of St Ninian of Galloway, who brought Christianity to Scotland from Rome in the fifth century. After the parade, which was attended by around 125,000 people, the Pope proceeded by Popemobile <ref name=popemobile>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepapalvisit.org.uk/2010-Visit/Visit-Event-Information/Popemobile-Routes |title=Pope Benedict XVI-Popemobile Routes |work=Thepapalvisit.org.uk |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> to have lunch with [[Keith O'Brien|Cardinal O'Brien]] at his home before travelling by car to [[Glasgow]].\n\nThe Pope was greeted by the [[Mario Conti|Archbishop of Glasgow]] for the ticketed Mass of the Feast of St Ninian in [[Bellahouston Park]]. [[Susan Boyle]] and [[Pop Idol]] winner [[Michelle McManus]] performed before the start of the mass.{{citation needed|date=December 2018}} Attendance was around 65,000 people.<ref>{{cite news|last=Cramb |first=Auslan |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/the-pope/8007705/Pope-visit-thousands-make-the-pilgrimage-to-Bellahouston-Park.html |title=Pope visit: thousands make the pilgrimage to Bellahouston Park |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=16 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010 |location=London}}</ref> The Pope flew from [[Glasgow Airport]] to London [[Heathrow airport]] that evening.<ref name=itinerary>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepapalvisit.org.uk/2010-Visit/Events-Timeline |title=Article-Events Timeline / 2010 Visit |work=Thepapalvisit.org.uk |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n===England===\n\n====17 September====\nOn the second day of his visit to the United Kingdom the Pope began the day with a private Mass in the chapel at [[54 Parkside]], Wimbledon, south west London, the official residence of the [[Nunciature to Great Britain|Apostolic Nunciature to Great Britain]]. His first public engagement was a celebration of Catholic education with a visit to address educators and students at [[St Mary's University, Twickenham]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stmarys.ac.uk/about/papal-visit/overview.aspx|title=The 2010 Papal Visit &#124; St Mary's University, Twickenham |publisher=Stmarys.ac.uk |date=17 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> which was followed by a meeting with people of faith in the University's Waldegrave Drawing Room.\n\nHe became the first Pope to enter [[Lambeth Palace]], where he met the [[Rowan Williams|Archbishop of Canterbury]].{{citation needed|date=December 2018}} He made the journey from Lambeth Palace to the [[Palace of Westminster]] by Popemobile,<ref name=popemobile /> making an Address to Civil Society from the spot in [[Westminster Hall]] where [[Thomas More|St Thomas More]] died a martyr's death in 1535, being accused of high treason for holding to his Catholic faith in refusing to acknowledge the validity of the [[First Succession Act|Act of Succession]].\n\nIn the evening there was an ecumenical celebration of evening prayer at [[Westminster Abbey]] with representatives from all the main Christian churches including the Greek Orthodox, Coptic and Free Churches. He later venerated the tomb of [[Edward the Confessor]] at the Abbey.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.westminster-abbey.org/press/news/news/2010/september/historic-abbey-service-for-pope |title=Historic Abbey Service for Pope |publisher=Westminster Abbey |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n====18 September====\n[[File:Hyde Park Vigil.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Pope Benedict leads the vigil in Hyde Park.]]\n[[File:Hyde Park Vigil 80000.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Some of the 80,000 attending the vigil in Hyde Park.]]\nThe Pope began the day with meetings with [[David Cameron]], Prime Minister, [[Nick Clegg]], as Deputy Prime Minister, and [[Harriet Harman]], Acting Leader of the Opposition. This was followed with morning Mass in [[Westminster Cathedral]]. In his sermon, the Pope referenced [[Catholic sexual scandal in the United Kingdom|sexual abuse by priests]], saying: \"Here, too, I think of the immense suffering caused by the abuse of children, especially within the church and by her ministers. Above all, I express my deep sorrow to the innocent victims of these unspeakable crimes\", saying \"I also acknowledge with you the shame and humiliation which all of us have suffered because of these sins\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/sep/18/pope-benedict-sermon-westminster-cathedral |title=Pope Benedict XVI's sermon at Westminster Cathedral |work=The Guardian |date= 18 September 2010|accessdate=16 October 2010 |location=London}}</ref>\n\nAfter Mass, the Pope used the middle part of the day to meet five victims of child sex abuse at the Apostolic Nunciature, apologising to them and describing the Church's measures to protect young people.<ref>{{cite news|last=Pigott |first=Robert |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-11361749 |title=What has the Pope's visit achieved? 19 September 2010 |work=BBC News |date=19 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> The meeting had been planned before the Pope's visit, and time was left free in his schedule to allow for it.{{citation needed|date=December 2018}}\n\nIn the evening the Pope visited St Peter's Residence for Older People, run by [[Little Sisters of the Poor]]. The Pope travelled to the day's main event, the ticketed Hyde Park Prayer Vigil on the Eve of the Beatification of Cardinal Newman, by Popemobile.<ref name=popemobile /> The vigil was attended by 80,000 people.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/uk-world-news/2010/09/19/the-pope-apologises-to-abuse-victims-as-80-000-pray-in-london-park-86908-22572592/ |title=The Pope apologises to abuse victims as 80,000 pray in London park |work=The Daily Record |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> The Pope's speech described Newman's life's work \"as a struggle against the growing tendency to view religion as a purely private and subjective matter, a question of personal opinion\", stating that it was a lesson for today, in which \"an intellectual and moral relativism threatens to sap the very foundations of our society\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholicherald.co.uk/news/2010/09/18/papal-visit-2010-popes-address-at-hyde-park-vigil-full-text/ |title=Papal Visit 2010: Pope\u2019s Address at Hyde Park Vigil \u2013 full text |work=Catholicherald.co.uk |date=18 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n====19 September====\n[[File:Stage preparations, Cofton Park, 090910, cropped.JPG|thumb|right|Stage being prepared for ceremony in Cofton Park]]\nThe final day of the Pope's visit saw the Pope fly by helicopter from London to [[Birmingham]] for the main event of his visit, the [[beatification]] of [[Cardinal (Catholicism)|Cardinal]] [[John Henry Newman]] in [[Cofton Park]] in Birmingham. Local residents were required to carry vehicle passes as well as to carry proof of identity in order to leave their own homes.<ref>{{cite news|last=Peek |first=Sitala |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-birmingham-11303899 |title=Pope's visit: historic event or one to avoid? |work=BBC News |date=15 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> Attendance at the event was approximately 55,000,<ref>{{cite web |last=Hesketh |first=Jane |url=http://www.itv.com/central-west/pope-at-cofton-park51831/ |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130127024240/http://www.itv.com/central-west/pope-at-cofton-park51831/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=27 January 2013 |title=Central Regional News (ITV Central Tonight) - ITV Local |publisher=Itv.com |date=19 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010 }}</ref> a figure said to have been reduced by the requirement to arrive at the location between 3am and 7am on special coaches for the 10am start.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/local-national/uk/administration-problems-blamed-for-pope-visit-ticket-slump-14947215.html |title='Administration problems' blamed for Pope visit ticket slump |work=Belfast Telegraph |date=13 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe Cofton Park Mass was followed by a private visit to [[Birmingham Oratory]], founded by John Henry Newman.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thepapalvisit.org.uk/2010-Visit/Visit-Event-Information/Itinerary/19-September-2010/The-Birmingham-Oratory |title=The Birmingham Oratory |work=Thepapalvisit.org.uk |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100920163138/http://www.thepapalvisit.org.uk/2010-Visit/Visit-Event-Information/Itinerary/19-September-2010/The-Birmingham-Oratory |archive-date=20 September 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The visit was preceded by controversy due to the exiling of three priests to monasteries in separate parts of the world.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/the-pope/7956204/Popes-visit-could-be-overshadowed-by-exile-of-Birmingham-priests.html | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | title=Pope's visit could be overshadowed by exile of Birmingham priests | first=Martin | last=Beckford | date=21 August 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe visit concluded with lunch and a meeting with the bishops of England, Scotland and Wales at [[St Mary's College, Oscott]]. The Pope gave a final speech at [[Birmingham Airport, England|Birmingham Airport]], before departing for [[Rome]] on a chartered [[Alitalia]] Airbus A320. [[British Airways]], as UK flag carrier, would have been the usual choice for a state Papal visit, but they were reportedly rejected due to concerns about strikes.{{citation needed|date=December 2018}}\n\n===Other events===\nThe Pope's schedule reportedly included free time to allow for the 83-year-old to take naps.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/popes-uk-visit-schedule-to-contain-nap-breaks-2055909.html | location=London | work=The Independent | title=Pope's UK visit schedule to contain nap breaks | first=Jerome | last=Taylor | date=18 August 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn conjunction with the visit, an exhibition of [[Sistine Chapel#Raphael's tapestries|Raphael's tapestries]] for the [[Sistine Chapel]] took place at London's [[Victoria and Albert Museum]] from 8 September to 17 October 2010 where they were displayed for the first time alongside the [[Raphael cartoons]] used to make them; the cartoons having been in the British [[Royal Collection]] since 1623. This followed a reported scaling-back of earlier plans for a large exhibition of Vatican artworks at London's [[Royal Academy]].<ref>{{Cite news| url=http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/news/damianthompson/100047995/popes-visit-what-happened-to-the-major-exhibition-of-vatican-treasures-at-the-royal-academy/ | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | title=Pope's visit: What happened to the major exhibition of Vatican treasures at the Royal Academy? | date=21 July 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Anti-terrorism arrests==\nOn 17 September 2010 the [[Metropolitan Police]] arrested five street cleaners under the [[Terrorism Act 2000]] in a pre-dawn raid at a London cleaning depot, in a suspected terrorist plot against the Pope on the second day of his state visit; a sixth person was arrested later in the day at his home \"on suspicion of the commission, preparation or instigation of acts of terrorism\".<ref>{{Cite news| title = Six held over Pope terror alert | date = 17 September 2010 | url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-11346001 | work = BBC News | accessdate = 17 September 2010}}</ref> The men, aged between 26 and 50, had been working as street cleaners for contractors [[Veolia Environnement]], on behalf of [[Westminster City Council]] and were based at the Chiltern Street depot in [[Marylebone]].\n\nThe suspects were questioned at an unidentified London police station. The police did not uncover any hazardous items during an initial search of the business premises and other properties.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5i399yZzlQndOhF_77tHM7TeLAMEwD9I9RPO00 | location=London | agency=Associated Press | title=6 arrested in UK in alleged terror threat to pope | first=Nicole | last=Winfield | date=17 September 2010}}</ref>\n\nAccording to police some of the suspects were thought to be immigrants to Britain, from a variety of nations including a number from Algeria.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/the-pope/8010002/Pope-visit-sixth-man-arrested-over-alleged-assassination-plot.html | location=London | work=The Telegraph | title=Pope visit: sixth man arrested over alleged assassination plot | first=Duncan | last=Gardham | date=17 September 2010}}</ref>\n\nAll the men were released without charge before the Pope's visit ended. It turned out they were arrested after joking about how the [[Popemobile]] could not withstand an [[Rocket-propelled grenade|RPG]] attack.{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n\n==Response==\n\n===Support===\n[[File:Flag of the Vatican City flying in Bradford (21st September 2010).jpg|thumb|upright|The [[Flag of Vatican City]] flying in [[Bradford]], [[West Yorkshire]] in honour of the papal visit.]]\nThe visit saw support from a range of people and organisations, including several leaders within other religions. The President of the [[Ahmadiyya Muslim Community]] UK, Rafiq Hayat stated that \"Religious leaders have a pivotal role to play in promoting peace and serving humanity. Indeed religions have far more commonalities than differences and we welcome moves that will help forge unity and foster greater understanding.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sys-con.com/node/1537040|title=UK Muslim Leader Welcomes Visit by Pope|date= 17 September 2010|accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref>\n\nVivian Wineman, President of the [[Board of Deputies of British Jews]], said \"In an age where scepticism and ill-will towards religion is rising, it will be an excellent opportunity to demonstrate that there is much to unite people of faith and much that can be achieved when we work together for the greater good not only of our members, but for society as a whole.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rcdow.org.uk/papalvisit/blog/?25|title=Papal visit to Great Britain|date=15 September 2010|accessdate=15 September 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928133035/http://www.rcdow.org.uk/papalvisit/blog/?25|archive-date=28 September 2011|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nMedia coverage of the visit, which was largely critical before the event, was more positive during and following the Pope's visit. A BBC News correspondent noted that 'there was a tangible sense of relief, even of euphoria, among Pope Benedict's entourage during the return flight to Rome from Birmingham'.<ref>{{cite news|last=Willey |first=David |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-11372501 |title=Pope's visit is deemed to challenge stereotypes |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=20 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n===Opposition===\n{{Further|Anti-Catholicism in the United Kingdom|Criticism of the Catholic Church}}\n[[File:2010 protest the pope rally.png|thumb|right|Protest during the Pope's visit]]\n\nThe visit was opposed by a range of people and organisations including some Protestants, LGBT and secular groups due to a number of reasons, such as the Church's policies on the [[ordination of women]], [[Homosexuality and Roman Catholicism|homosexuality]], [[Catholic contraception|contraception]] and [[Roman Catholic Church and AIDS|AIDS]], as well as complaints over [[Catholic sex abuse cases|historical sexual abuse of children by Catholic priests]].<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite news|last=Wynne |first=Jonathan |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/religion/the-pope/7981933/Public-believes-taxpayers-should-not-fund-papal-visit.html |title=Public believes taxpayers should not fund papal visit |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=5 September 2010 |accessdate=17 September 2010 |location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2010/06/03/church-costs-for-popes-visit-out-of-control/ |title=Church costs for Pope\u2019s visit \u2018out of control\u2019 - from Pink News |work=Pink News |date=3 June 2010 |accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref> Former DUP leader [[Ian Paisley]] (known for his staunch [[Anti-Catholicism]] in [[Northern Ireland]]) called the visit a \"mistake\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/10484122 |title=Pope Benedict XVI UK visit a 'mistake' says Ian Paisley |work=BBC News |date=2 July 2010 |accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref> and the principal of Scotland's [[Free Church Training College]] said the visit airbrushed the [[Protestant Reformation]] out of history and dishonoured reformer and nationalist [[John Knox]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholicherald.co.uk/news/2010/07/14/faithful-urged-to-apply-as-soon-as-possible-for-papal-visit-places/ |title=Catholics urged to apply as soon as possible for papal visit places |work=Catholicherald.co.uk |date=14 July 2010 |accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref> On the eve of the visit, a letter by 50 public figures argued that the Pope's tour should not have been accorded the status of a state visit.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/sep/15/pope-uk-state-visit-protest Pope's visit: pontiff should not be 'honoured' with state visit] ''[[The Guardian]]'', 15 September 2010</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/sep/15/harsh-judgments-on-pope-religion |title=Letter by 50 public figures for not giving the honour of state to Pope |work=The Guardian |date= 15 September 2010|accessdate=16 October 2010 |location=London}}</ref>\n\nA number of groups, including the [[British Humanist Association]] and the [[National Secular Society]] organised a campaign of protests against the visit.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.protest-the-pope.org.uk/ |title=Protest The Pope |publisher=Protest The Pope |accessdate=18 September 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100813034024/http://www.protest-the-pope.org.uk/ |archivedate=13 August 2010  }}</ref> The Roman Catholic [[pressure group]] \"Catholic Women's Ordination\" arranged for London buses to carry advertisements encouraging the Pope to \"Ordain Women Now\"<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/jul/22/london-bus-female-ordination-pope | location=London | work=The Guardian | title=London buses to carry female ordination advert during pope's visit. | first=Riazat | last=Butt | date=22 July 2010}}</ref> and also planned further unspecified lobbying action. Religious and secular correspondents noted that only 3 women appeared at Lambeth Palace to support the ordination of women.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic-womens-ordination.org.uk/news.htm#Pope |title=Local Groups |work=Catholic-womens-ordination.org.uk |date= |accessdate=17 September 2010}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Richard dawkins speaking at the protest the pope rally 2010.png|thumb|right|[[Richard Dawkins]] speaking at the protest, with [[Peter Tatchell]] on the left at the back.]]\n[[Richard Dawkins]] gave a speech to over 10,000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/sep/18/pope-benedict-xvi-protest|title=Protest the Pope rally sees 10,000 march through London's streets|first=Tracy|last=Mcveigh|date=18 September 2010|accessdate=26 November 2017|website=Theguardian.com}}</ref> people at the \"Protest the Pope\" rally, declaring the pope \"an enemy of humanity\", and countering the Pope's claim that [[the holocaust]] was the result of atheism by arguing that [[Hitler]] was a Roman Catholic.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://richarddawkins.net/articles/521113-ratzinger-is-an-enemy-of-humanity |title=Dawkins speech |publisher=Richarddawkins.net |date=22 September 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Science |url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/punctuated-equilibrium/2010/sep/20/1 |title=Richard Dawkins' unedited speech at 'Protest the Pope' march in London |work=The Guardian |date= 20 September 2010|accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref> Dawkins had previously supported a call for the Pope's arrest for \"crimes against humanity\", an idea first proposed by [[Christopher Hitchens]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://richarddawkins.net/videos/5434-christopher-hitchens-arrest-the-pope | title=Christopher Hitchens: Arrest The Pope!}}</ref> and described by a former editor of the ''[[Catholic Herald]]'' as \"lunatic\",<ref>{{Cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/8614232.stm | work=BBC News | title=Dawkins backs plan to arrest Pope | date=13 April 2010}}</ref> and human rights lawyer [[Geoffrey Robertson]] was reported to have looked at options to [[Geoffrey Robertson#Putting Pope Benedict XVI on trial|charge the Pope]] over his alleged cover-up of sexual abuse in the Catholic Church.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/belief/2010/apr/13/pope-prosecution-dawkins |title=The pope should stand trial |work=The Guardian |date= 13 April 2010|accessdate=18 September 2010 |location=London |first=Richard |last=Dawkins}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2010, the UK government announced plans to change the law on universal jurisdiction to prevent the issue of an arrest warrant.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/article/295022 |title=UK government acts to prevent arrest of Pope |publisher=Digitaljournal.com |date=23 July 2010 |accessdate=18 September 2010}}</ref> Attempts to make a citizen's arrest on the Pope were abandoned by [[Peter Tatchell]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/peter-tatchell-scraps-idea-of-making-citizens-arrest-on-the-pope-2074273.html |title=Peter Tatchell scraps idea of making citizen's arrest on the Pope |work=The Independent |date= 9 September 2010|accessdate=17 September 2010 |location=London |first=Jerome |last=Taylor}}</ref> Members of [[Muslims Against Crusades]] protested against the Pope in London.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Multiple authors|title=Pope Benedict XVI's UK visit: Day three|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/gallery/2010/sep/18/pope-benedict-xvi-london|accessdate=10 April 2016|work=The Guardian|agency=Reuters|date=18 September 2010}}</ref> ''The Guardian'' reported that around 10,000 protesters marched in London against the Pope's visit on 18 September 2010.<ref>{{cite news|author=Tracy Mcveigh |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/sep/18/pope-benedict-xvi-protest |title=Protest the Pope rally sees 10,000 march through London's streets |work=The Guardian |date= 18 September 2010|accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Media coverage==\nThe [[BBC]] marked the visit with documentaries including:<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/mandrake/7866684/Pope-Benedict-XVI-about-to-be-put-on-trial-by-the-BBC.html | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | title=Pope Benedict XVI about to be put on trial by the BBC | first=Tim | last=Walker | date=2 July 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2010/aug/03/bbc-papal-visit | location=London | work=The Guardian | title=BBC to mark Pope's UK visit with documentary on clerical abuse scandals | first=Tara | last=Conlan | date=3 August 2010}}</ref>\n\n* ''Vatican: The Hidden World'', a profile of the [[Holy See|Vatican]] with unprecedented access given\n* ''The Real Joseph Ratzinger'', a papal profile\n*''Newman: Saint or Sinner?'', a documentary about [[Cardinal Newman]]\n*''Benedict - Trials of a Pope'', a documentary about the life of the Pope<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00ttj16 |title=Benedict: Trials of a Pope |publisher=BBC |date= |accessdate=16 October 2010}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|United Kingdom|Catholicism|Christianity}}\n*[[List of journeys of Pope Benedict XVI]]\n*[[Roman Catholicism in the United Kingdom]]\n*[[Foreign Office papal visit memo]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikinews|Pope Benedict XVI heads to the UK amid protests}}\n{{Commons category}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20111119175338/http://thepapalvisit.co.uk/ Apostolic journey to Britain] - official website from [[Catholic Church in England and Wales]]\n*[https://www.vatican.va/holy_father/benedict_xvi/travels/2010/index_regno-unito_en.htm Apostolic Journey to the United Kingdom] - official website from the [[Holy See]]\n\n<br />\n{{Benedict XVI}}\n{{Elizabeth II}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pope Benedict Xvi's Visit To The United Kingdom}}\n[[Category:Pope Benedict XVI]]\n[[Category:Foreign relations of the Holy See]]\n[[Category:History of Christianity in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:2010 in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:2010 in Christianity]]\n[[Category:Foreign trips by popes|Benedict XVI, United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Holy See\u2013United Kingdom relations]]\n[[Category:Catholic Church in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Diplomatic visits to the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:September 2010 events in the United Kingdom]]\n", "name_user": "Jzsj", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTicketed events:ce", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pope_Benedict_XVI%27s_visit_to_the_United_Kingdom"}
{"title_page": "Heart Book (All Nations Gospel Publishers)", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced|date=April 2020}}\n'''THE HEART OF MAN OR THE SPIRITUAL HEART MIRROR'''\n\n(''An Allegorical Representation in Ten Pictures'')\n\nTHE HEART OF MAN BOOKLET\n\nThis Booklet originated in France in 1732, was revised and rewritten for the mission fields of Africa by Rev. J.R. [https://globalchristiancenter.com/missions-inspiration/22542-memories-of-a-godly-missionary Gschwend]  in 1929, and has subsequently been translated and printed under copyright in over 538 indigenous languages by [http://www.angp.org ALL NATIONS GOSPEL PUBLISHERS] who are distributing it today in 127 mission countries. People of all languages, classes and religions are being led by this booklet to experience the deep spiritual truth and significance of God\u2019s message to mankind as expressed by the prophet [[Ezekiel]] 586 years before [[Christ]], \u201cI will give you a new heart and a new mind then you will be my people, and I will be your [[God]]!\u201d Ezekiel 36:26-28.\n\nThe text used is from the compact (or shorter) format of the booklet. Different formats of the booklet including the complete booklet in .pdf format can be downloaded free of charge.\n\nQuotes from [[Scripture]] was taken from [[Good News Bible|The Good News Bible]] \n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|ALL NATIONS GOSPEL PUBLISHERS\n|[[www.angp.org]]\n|-\n|Text written:\n|1929\n|-\n|Written by:\n|Rev. J.R. Gschwend\n|-\n|Text and pictures owned by:\n|ALL NATIONS GOSPEL PUBLISHERS\n|-\n|Number of translations available\n|481\n|-\n|Latest mission report:\n|<nowiki>http://www.angp.org/fileadmin/angp/sites/pdf/AN_englisch_aktuell.pdf</nowiki>\n|-\n|Download all booklets from:\n|[[Www.angp-hb.co.za|http://www.angp-hb.co.za]]\n|-\n|Download Booklet Format:\n|https://angp-hb.co.za/booklet-format/\n|-\n|Download Cell phone Format:\n|https://angp-hb.co.za/cellphone-format/\n|-\n|Download Print Format:\n|https://angp-hb.co.za/print-format/\n|-\n|Download Compact Format:\n|https://angp-hb.co.za/compact-format/\n|}\n\n== THE HEART OF MAN: THE TEMPLE OF GOD OR THE WORKSHOP OF SATAN ==\n'''(1 John 3:4-10)'''\n[[File:The heart of man booklet.jpg|alt=The Heart of man|thumb|The Heart of man booklet]]\nAs you read this book, please bear in mind that it is like a mirror in which you will be able to see yourself. Whether you are a heathen or a Christian, one who does not believe in [[Christ]] or a backslider, you will see yourself as [[God]] sees you. \u201cMan looks at the outward appearance, but I look at the heart.\u201d (1 Sam. 16:7). God sees us as we really are.\n\n[[Satan]] is the father of all lies. He is the prince of darkness and god of this world, who disguises himself as an angel of light to lead men and women the wrong way. In these days, as in times past, there are many false [[apostles]] who disguise themselves, pretending to be apostles of Christ. And no wonder, for Satan himself is transformed (disguised) into an angel of light (2 Corinthians 11:13,14). Satan, the god of this world, keeps people in the dark so that they cannot see that God loves them or that Jesus died to save them (2 Cor. 4:4). All sinners and those who do not believe are spiritually dead and blind concerning God. They are ruled by the evil of this world (Eph. 2:1-2). Unless their eyes are opened in some way to their lost condition, they are heading for eternal destruction. The person who says, \u201cI have never sinned\u201d is deceiving himself. For \u201cThe Son of God appeared for this very reason, to destroy what the devil had done.\u201d (1 John 3:8). \u201cSo then, submit to God. Resist the devil, and he will run away from you. Come near to God, and He will come near to you.\u201d (James 4:7,8)\n\nAs you read this book and study its pictures, you will be able to see your own heart. Allow God\u2019s searchlight to show you the condition of your heart. Acknowledge your sins and do not deny their existence, for God\u2019s Word tells us that \u201cIf we say that we have no sin, we deceive ourselves, and there is no truth in us. But if we confess our sins to God, He will keep His promise and do what is right: He will forgive us our sins and purify us from all our wrongdoing.\u201d (1 John 1:1-10). \u201cThe blood of Jesus, His Son, purifies us from every sin\u201d.\n\nYou are ruled either by Satan or by God; you are a slave to sin or a servant of God. If sin controls your life, do not deny it, but cry out to God. He will set you free through Jesus Christ who came to this world to save sinners, to break the power of Satan and sin over us. He is our Saviour. You are in the presence of a holy God who knows all the secrets, the hidden thoughts and actions of your life. It is impossible to hide yourself and actions from God, for \u201cGod made our ears \u2013 can\u2019t He hear? He made our eyes \u2013 can\u2019t He see?\u201d (Ps. 94:9).\n\nThe Lord keeps close watch over the whole world to give strength to those whose hearts are loyal to Him.\u201d (2 Chron.16:9).\n\nHe watches every step men take. There is no darkness dark enough to hide a sinner from God.\u201d (Job 34:21,22).\n\nBut [[Jesus]] did not trust Himself to them, because He knew them all.\u201d (John 2:24).\n\nTherefore \u201chappy are those whose sins are forgiven, whose wrongs are pardoned. Happy is the man whom the Lord does not accuse of doing wrong and who is free from all deceit.\u201d (Ps. 32:1-2).\n\n== THE SINNERS HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The sinners heart P1.jpg|alt=This picture shows the heart of a wordly sinful man or woman, described in the Bible as a sinner.|thumb|The Sinners Heart]]\n'''This picture shows the heart of a worldly sinful man or woman, described in the Bible as a sinner.'''\nBelow the head in this picture, the heart of man can be seen occupied by various animals which speak of the many different sins in the human heart, as the heart is the centre and breeding place of our sins. God tells us by the mouth of His prophet Jeremiah, that \u201cNobody can understand the human heart. There is nothing else so deceitful; it is too sick to be healed.\u201d (Jeremiah 17:9)\n\nJesus Himself confirms this by saying, \u201cFor from the inside, from a person\u2019s heart, come the evil ideas which lead him to do immoral things; to rob, kill, commit adultery, be greedy, and do all sorts of evil things; deceit, indecency, jealousy, slander, pride, and folly \u2013 all these evil things come from inside a person and make him unclean\u201d (Mark 7:21-23)\n\nThe bleary, red eyes speak of drunkenness.  \u201cDon\u2019t let wine tempt you, even though it is rich red, though it sparkles in the cup, and it goes down smoothly. The next morning you will feel as if you have been bitten by a poisonous snake.\u201d (Proverbs 23:31-32)\n\nDifferent animals and signs used in the pictures reminds us of the following sins:\n\n=== The [[Peacock]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nWhile the beauty of the peacock is admired by everybody, here in the heart of man, it speaks of the sin of pride.\n\n=== The [[goat]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe goat represents bodily desires, immorality, adultery.\n\n=== The [[pig]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe pig speaks of the sins of drunkenness and gluttony. It is a dirty animal eagerly swallowing up everything in its way, clean or dirty, and in the same way a sinful heart devours every immoral suggestion, expression, picture, literature, etc.\n\n=== The [[tortoise]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe tortoise speaks of laziness, sluggishness to obey and witchcraft. \u201cA lazy man who refuses to work is only killing himself, all he does is think about what he would like to have.\u201d  (Prov. 21:25,26).\n\n=== The [[leopard]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe leopard is a very savage and cruel beast. Hatred, anger and a bad temper often rule the heart of man and many times lead to murder. \u201cKeep your temper under control; it is foolish to harbour a grudge.\u201d (Eccl. 7:9)\n\n=== The [[snake]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe snake represents the devil who is very deceitful, clever and misleading, and does everything possible to destroy our relationship with God.\n\n=== The [[frog]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe frog speaks here of the sins of greediness and the love of money which is the source of all evil (1 Tim. 6:10). Certain frogs in the Congo have been seen eating ants by the hundreds until they burst and died.\n\n=== [[Satan]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nSatan is the father of all lies, and is the one who persuades us to sin, and then he rules our hearts.\n\n=== The [[star]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe star speaks of the conscience in the heart of every man. Even in the bad heart the conscience is still there, but is being ignored, and cannot therefore help this person.\n\n=== The eye of [[God]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe eye of God sees everything that goes on in the heart. Nothing can be hidden from His flaming eye, and therefore He knows and sees all the secret thoughts and intentions of the heart. Whether you do your evil deeds in the darkest night, in the thickest forest, in the deepest ditch or wherever it may be, God sees it.\n\n=== The little tongues of fire[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe little tongues of fire round about the heart show the love of God surrounding the sinful heart. While God hates sin He loves man and does not want the death of a sinner, but that he should turn away from his sins and live. Jesus came to save sinners. There is great joy in heaven over one sinner that repents (Luke 15:7). The little tongues also speak of the blood of Jesus Christ, \u201cthe Lamb of God, who takes away the sin of the world.\u201d (John 1:29).\n\n=== The [[angel]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe angel represents the Word of God. God wants to speak to those who have been deceived and are carrying heavy loads of sin, so that they may turn from their sinful ways and let the light and love of God come into their hearts.\n\n=== The [[dove]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe dove is a sign of the Holy Spirit, the Spirit who reveals the truth about God, about sin and what is right, and about God\u2019s judgement (John 15:26).\n\n== THE HEART CONVINCED OF SIN[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The heart convinced of sin P2.jpg|alt=The Heart convinced of sin|center|thumb|The Heart convinced of sin]]\n'''This picture shows the heart of a man who is sorry for his sins and is beginning to look for God.'''\n\nHere we see the sinner beginning to take notice of the message of God and to open his heart to the love of God. The Holy Spirit begins to shine into the dark and sinful heart. The light of God comes into his heart to drive all darkness away. When God\u2019s light comes in, darkness has to go. Sin, described here by all the various animals, has to go. Therefore, dear reader, allow Jesus, the Light of the world, to come into your heart, and darkness and the evil actions of darkness must leave the heart, as shown in this picture.\n\nJesus said, \u201cI am the light of the world. Whoever follows me will have the light of life and will never walk in darkness.\u201d (John 8:12).\n\nYour heart is intended to be God\u2019s house, God\u2019s temple. He wants to live in it, make it beautiful, fill it with light, love and joy. Jesus not only came to forgive us our sins, but He came to deliver us and set us free from the power and domination of sin.\n\n\u201cIf the Son ([[Jesus]]) sets you free, then you will be really free.\u201d (John 8:36).\n\n== THE REPENTING HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The repenting heart P3.jpg|alt=The repenting heart|center|thumb|The repenting heart]]\n'''This picture shows us the heart of someone who is really serious about finding the right relationship with God.'''\n\nAs he sees the cross which the angel, the Word of God, shows to him, it breaks his now sorry heart, and he is moved with deep, heartfelt regret and sorrow over his many sins. As he sees the great love of God expressed in Christ Jesus, this love melts his heart, especially as he begins to realise that Jesus Christ, the Son of God, came to take away his many sins, as He was willing to die in his place on the cross.\n\nThe love and peace of God enter his heart as he begins to realise that \u201cthe blood of Jesus, His Son, purifies us from every sin.\u201d (1 John 1:7).\n\n\u201cCreate a pure heart in me, O God, and put a new and loyal spirit in me.\u201d (Psalm 51:10).\n\nAgain God\u2019s Word says, \u201cI am pleased with those who are humble and repentant, who fear me and obey me.\u201d (Isa. 66:2).\n\nThe Holy Spirit makes the words of Jesus clear to him, \u201cCourage, my son (daughter)! Your sins are forgiven.\u201d (Matt. 9:2).\n\n== DYING WITH CHRIST[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:Dying with Christ P4.jpg|alt=Dying with Christ|center|thumb|Dying with Christ]]\n'''This picture speaks of a Christian who has found perfect peace and eternal salvation through the death of our Lord and Saviour, Jesus Christ.'''\n\nThis person boasts in nothing else except \u201conly about the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ; for by means of His cross the world is dead to us, and we are dead to the world.\u201d (Gal. 6:14). Jesus died on the cross so that we too, might \u201cdie to sin and live for righteousness\u201d (1 Peter 2:24); a Christian dead to the world. We are commanded to \u201clet the Spirit direct our lives, and we will not satisfy the desires of the human nature.\u201d (Gal. 5:16,25).\n\nDo you declare openly that you have given your heart to Jesus Christ, by what you say and do? Or are you ashamed to let others know? Jesus said, \u201cIf anyone declares publicly that he belongs to me, I will do the same for him before my Father in heaven. But if anyone rejects me publicly, I will reject him before my Father in heaven.\u201d(Matt. 10:32,33). Jesus also said, \u201cWhoever does not take up his cross and follow in my steps is not fit to be my disciple.\u201d (Matt. 10:38). Happy are those who find protection in the Rock, Jesus Christ!\n\n== THE TEMPLE OF GOD[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The Temple of God P5.jpg|alt=The temple of God|center|thumb|The temple of God]]\n'''This picture shows the clean and purified heart of the sinner who has been saved by God\u2019s grace and mercy.'''\n\nThe heart has now become a true temple of God. Sin has been driven out. Instead of the various animals controlled by Satan, the father of lies, we see the Holy Spirit, the Spirit of Truth, living in the heart. Instead of being the breeding place of sin, the heart has become a beautiful, fruit-bearing tree or garden, bearing the fruits of the Spirit, such as love, joy, peace, humility, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, self control and others which are acceptable and pleasing to God and man (Gal. 5:22-23). He has now become a fruit- bearing branch of the real vine \u2013 our Lord Jesus Christ. The secret of this fruit-bearing is that he remains united with Christ, and Christ and His words remain in him (John 15:1-10).\n\n\u201cHappy are the pure in heart; they will see God!\u201d (Matt.5:8). King David knew that the greatest battle was taking place in his own heart and recognizing his deep spiritual need, prayed, \u201cCreate a pure heart in me, O God, and put a new and loyal spirit in me.\u201d (Psalm 51:10). Nobody is able to purify his own heart, or to create a clean heart, unless through truly repenting he comes to God as David did, asking God to create a pure heart in him.\n\n== THE TEMPTED AND DEVIDED HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The tempted and devided heart P6.jpg|alt=The tempted and divided heart|center|thumb|The tempted and divided heart]]\n'''This is the sad picture of one who has fallen back into his old ways. One eye is starting to close, showing that he is beginning to grow cold and sleepy in his relationship with God.'''\n\nThe light inside has grown dim, and the pictures in his heart, showing his readiness to suffer with Christ, have fallen and are no longer upright. He is surrounded by temptations to which he is slowly giving in instead of resisting them. Instead of listening to God\u2019s voice he now begins to listen to the devil\u2019s cunning suggestions and false promises. Although he may still be a church-goer, hiding his desires for the things of the world under a form of religion, the love for God has grown cold in his heart. Obey the warnings of our Lord Jesus when He says, \u201cKeep watch and pray that you will not fall into temptation.\u201d (Matt. 26:41). \u201cWhoever thinks he is standing firm had better be careful that he does not fall.\u201d (1Cor.10:12). We must put on all the armour that God gives us, so that we will be able to stand up against the devil\u2019s evil tricks. (Eph. 6:11-18).\n\n== THE FALLEN OR STUBBORN HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The fallen or stubborn heart P7.jpg|alt=The fallen or stubborn heart|center|thumb|The fallen or stubborn heart]]\n'''This picture reveals the condition of the person who has fallen completely into his old ways again, in spite of what God did for him.'''\n\nAfter this person was once in God\u2019s light and had tasted heaven\u2019s gift and received his share of the Holy Spirit, he has abandoned his faith. (Heb. 6:4). Jesus Himself described the backsliders\u2019 condition when He said, \u201cWhen an evil spirit goes out of a person, it travels over dry country looking for a place to rest. If it can\u2019t find one, it says to itself, \u2018I will go back to my house.\u2019 So it goes back and finds the house clean and tidy. Then it goes out and brings seven other spirits even worse than itself, and they come and live there. So when it is all over, that person is in a worse state than he was at the beginning.\u201d (Luke 11:24-26).\n\n\u201cWhat happened to them shows that the proverbs are true; \u2018A dog goes back to what it has vomited\u2019 and \u2018A pig that has been washed goes back to roll in the mud.\u2019 \u201d (2 Peter 2:22). If you continue to be stubborn, and love darkness rather than light, there is no hope, no help, because you are choosing death instead of life \u2013 \u201csin pays its wage - death.\u201d (Rom. 6:23).\n\n== THE SINNERS JUDGEMENT[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The sinners judgement P8.jpg|alt=The sinners judgement|center|thumb|The sinners judgement]]\n'''Here we find the stubborn sinner who did not want to open his heart to God again.'''\n\nThe false pleasures of sin have disappeared, and the awful reality of the high and dreadful cost of sin now has to be faced. The agonies of hell are becoming real to him. Although he now longs to pray, he finds he cannot communicate with God whose love he has rejected for so long. His friends are afraid to stand at his bedside, and their empty words of comfort cannot help him now. His riches can neither lengthen his life, nor save his soul, nor reduce the agony of his soul.\n\nHe begins to realise that \u201cit is a terrifying thing to fall into the hands of the living God!\u201d (Heb. 10:31). He had hoped to give his life to God when it suited him. This dying sinner who rejected the forgiveness and love of God during his lifetime now has to hear the voice of his Judge, the Saviour whom he rejected saying: \u201cAway from me, you that are under God\u2019s curse! Away to the eternal fire which has been prepared for the devil and his angels!\u201d (Matt. 25:41).\n\n\u201cEveryone must die once, and after that be judged by God.\u201d (Heb. 9:27).\n\n== THE VICTORIOUS HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The victorious heart P9.jpg|alt=The victorious heart|center|thumb|The victorious heart]]\n'''This picture shows a Christian who remains faithful and wins the victory over painful tests and temptations.'''\n\nWhile he is tempted on all sides, he remains firm and holds out to the end, being victorious through Jesus Christ. He has not only entered the Christian race, but he is continuing in it, running with determination, \u201ckeeping his eyes fixed on Jesus, on whom our faith depends from beginning to end.\u201d (Heb. 12:1,2). He remembers the words of Jesus. \u201cHappy are you when people insult you and persecute you and tell all kinds of evil lies against you because you are my followers. Be happy and glad, for a great reward is kept for you in heaven.\u201d (Matt. 5:11,12).\n\nThis person is ready to meet God, and is like a tree that grows beside a stream; that bears fruit at the right time (Ps. 1:3); like a branch of the real vine, bearing much fruit. He does not know the fear of death, for the perfect love of God, which he has received through the Holy Spirit, has filled his heart.\n\n== THE GLORIOUS HOMEGOING[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The glorious homegoing P10.jpg|alt=The glorious homegoing|center|thumb|The glorious homegoing]]\n'''Jesus said, \u201cI am the resurrection and the life. Whoever believes in me will live, even though he dies; and whoever lives and believes in me will never die.\u201d (John 1:25,26).'''\n\n\u201cWhoever hears my words and believes in Him who sent me has eternal life. He will not be judged, but has already passed from death to life.\u201d (John 5:24). Death holds neither fear nor punishment for the Christian. \u201cDeath is destroyed; victory is complete! Where death is your victory? Where death is your power to hurt?\u2026 Thanks be to God who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ!\u201d(1 Cor. 15:54-57)\n\nA person who has lived and walked with God is not afraid of death. When the time comes for him to die, he will go gladly, as the Apostle Paul puts it, \u201cI want very much to leave this life and to be with Christ, which is a far better thing.\u201d (Phil. 1:23)\n\n\u201cThen I heard a voice from heaven saying, \u2018Write this: Happy are those who from now on die in the service of the Lord!\u2019 \u2018Yes indeed!\u2019 answers the Spirit. \u2018They will enjoy rest from their hard work, because the results of their service go with them.\u201d (Rev. 14:13).\n\n== Prayer[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n''\u201cHe watches every step men take. There is no darkness dark enough to hide a sinner from God\u201d Job 34:21-22''\n\n''\u201cSo then, submit to God. Resist the devil, and he will run away from you. Come close to God, and He will come near you.\u201d James 4:7-8''\n\n''\u201cFor this is how God loved the world: He gave his one and only Son, so that everyone who believes in him will not perish but have eternal life. John 3:16''\n\n'''Let us pray:''' \n\n'''My father in heaven, I am really sorry for the sins in my heart. I want your light to shine into my heart, to remove all the bad things that are ruining my life. Please give me a new heart, and fill my heart with your own presence. Please help me to live a life that will be pleasing to you, and that will help me to be the person I should be. I ask this in the Name of Jesus. AMEN'''\n\n''\u201chappy are those whose sins are forgiven, whose wrongs are pardoned. Happy is the man whom the Lord does not accuse of doing wrong and who is free from all deceit\u201d Ps. 32:1-2''\u2003\n", "text_old": "{{Unreferenced|date=April 2020}}\n'''THE HEART OF MAN OR THE SPIRITUAL HEART MIRROR'''\n\n(''An Allegorical Representation in Ten Pictures'')\n\nTHE HEART OF MAN BOOKLET\n\nThis Booklet originated in France in 1732, was revised and rewritten for the mission fields of Africa by Rev. J.R. [https://globalchristiancenter.com/missions-inspiration/22542-memories-of-a-godly-missionary Gschwend]  in 1929, and has subsequently been translated and printed under copyright in over 538 indigenous languages by [http://www.angp.org ALL NATIONS GOSPEL PUBLISHERS] who are distributing it today in 127 mission countries. People of all languages, classes and religions are being led by this booklet to experience the deep spiritual truth and significance of God\u2019s message to mankind as expressed by the prophet [[Ezekiel]] 586 years before [[Christ]], \u201cI will give you a new heart and a new mind then you will be my people, and I will be your [[God]]!\u201d Ezekiel 36:26-28.\n\nThe text used is from the compact (or shorter) format of the booklet. Different formats of the booklet including the complete booklet in .pdf format can be downloaded free of charge.\n\nQuotes from [[Scripture]] was taken from [[Good News Bible|The Good News Bible]] \n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|ALL NATIONS GOSPEL PUBLISHERS\n|www.angp.org\n|-\n|Text written:\n|1929\n|-\n|Written by:\n|Rev. J.R. Gschwend\n|-\n|Text and pictures owned by:\n|ALL NATIONS GOSPEL PUBLISHERS\n|-\n|Number of translations available\n|481\n|-\n|Latest mission report:\n|<nowiki>http://www.angp.org/fileadmin/angp/sites/pdf/AN_englisch_aktuell.pdf</nowiki>\n|-\n|Download all booklets from:\n|www.angp-hb.co.za\n|-\n|Download Booklet Format:\n|<nowiki>https://angp-hb.co.za/booklet-format/</nowiki>\n|-\n|Download Cell phone Format:\n|<nowiki>https://angp-hb.co.za/cellphone-format/</nowiki>\n|-\n|Download Print Format:\n|<nowiki>https://angp-hb.co.za/print-format/</nowiki>\n|-\n|Download Compact Format:\n|<nowiki>https://angp-hb.co.za/compact-format/</nowiki>\n|}\n\n== THE HEART OF MAN: THE TEMPLE OF GOD OR THE WORKSHOP OF SATAN ==\n'''(1 John 3:4-10)'''\n[[File:The heart of man booklet.jpg|alt=The Heart of man|thumb|The Heart of man booklet]]\nAs you read this book, please bear in mind that it is like a mirror in which you will be able to see yourself. Whether you are a heathen or a Christian, one who does not believe in [[Christ]] or a backslider, you will see yourself as [[God]] sees you. \u201cMan looks at the outward appearance, but I look at the heart.\u201d (1 Sam. 16:7). God sees us as we really are.\n\n[[Satan]] is the father of all lies. He is the prince of darkness and god of this world, who disguises himself as an angel of light to lead men and women the wrong way. In these days, as in times past, there are many false [[apostles]] who disguise themselves, pretending to be apostles of Christ. And no wonder, for Satan himself is transformed (disguised) into an angel of light (2 Corinthians 11:13,14). Satan, the god of this world, keeps people in the dark so that they cannot see that God loves them or that Jesus died to save them (2 Cor. 4:4). All sinners and those who do not believe are spiritually dead and blind concerning God. They are ruled by the evil of this world (Eph. 2:1-2). Unless their eyes are opened in some way to their lost condition, they are heading for eternal destruction. The person who says, \u201cI have never sinned\u201d is deceiving himself. For \u201cThe Son of God appeared for this very reason, to destroy what the devil had done.\u201d (1 John 3:8). \u201cSo then, submit to God. Resist the devil, and he will run away from you. Come near to God, and He will come near to you.\u201d (James 4:7,8)\n\nAs you read this book and study its pictures, you will be able to see your own heart. Allow God\u2019s searchlight to show you the condition of your heart. Acknowledge your sins and do not deny their existence, for God\u2019s Word tells us that \u201cIf we say that we have no sin, we deceive ourselves, and there is no truth in us. But if we confess our sins to God, He will keep His promise and do what is right: He will forgive us our sins and purify us from all our wrongdoing.\u201d (1 John 1:1-10). \u201cThe blood of Jesus, His Son, purifies us from every sin\u201d.\n\nYou are ruled either by Satan or by God; you are a slave to sin or a servant of God. If sin controls your life, do not deny it, but cry out to God. He will set you free through Jesus Christ who came to this world to save sinners, to break the power of Satan and sin over us. He is our Saviour. You are in the presence of a holy God who knows all the secrets, the hidden thoughts and actions of your life. It is impossible to hide yourself and actions from God, for \u201cGod made our ears \u2013 can\u2019t He hear? He made our eyes \u2013 can\u2019t He see?\u201d (Ps. 94:9).\n\nThe Lord keeps close watch over the whole world to give strength to those whose hearts are loyal to Him.\u201d (2 Chron.16:9).\n\nHe watches every step men take. There is no darkness dark enough to hide a sinner from God.\u201d (Job 34:21,22).\n\nBut [[Jesus]] did not trust Himself to them, because He knew them all.\u201d (John 2:24).\n\nTherefore \u201chappy are those whose sins are forgiven, whose wrongs are pardoned. Happy is the man whom the Lord does not accuse of doing wrong and who is free from all deceit.\u201d (Ps. 32:1-2).\n\n== THE SINNERS HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The sinners heart P1.jpg|alt=This picture shows the heart of a wordly sinful man or woman, described in the Bible as a sinner.|thumb|The Sinners Heart]]\n'''This picture shows the heart of a worldly sinful man or woman, described in the Bible as a sinner.'''\nBelow the head in this picture, the heart of man can be seen occupied by various animals which speak of the many different sins in the human heart, as the heart is the centre and breeding place of our sins. God tells us by the mouth of His prophet Jeremiah, that \u201cNobody can understand the human heart. There is nothing else so deceitful; it is too sick to be healed.\u201d (Jeremiah 17:9)\n\nJesus Himself confirms this by saying, \u201cFor from the inside, from a person\u2019s heart, come the evil ideas which lead him to do immoral things; to rob, kill, commit adultery, be greedy, and do all sorts of evil things; deceit, indecency, jealousy, slander, pride, and folly \u2013 all these evil things come from inside a person and make him unclean\u201d (Mark 7:21-23)\n\nThe bleary, red eyes speak of drunkenness.  \u201cDon\u2019t let wine tempt you, even though it is rich red, though it sparkles in the cup, and it goes down smoothly. The next morning you will feel as if you have been bitten by a poisonous snake.\u201d (Proverbs 23:31-32)\n\nDifferent animals and signs used in the pictures reminds us of the following sins:\n\n=== The [[Peacock]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nWhile the beauty of the peacock is admired by everybody, here in the heart of man, it speaks of the sin of pride.\n\n=== The [[goat]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe goat represents bodily desires, immorality, adultery.\n\n=== The [[pig]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe pig speaks of the sins of drunkenness and gluttony. It is a dirty animal eagerly swallowing up everything in its way, clean or dirty, and in the same way a sinful heart devours every immoral suggestion, expression, picture, literature, etc.\n\n=== The [[tortoise]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe tortoise speaks of laziness, sluggishness to obey and witchcraft. \u201cA lazy man who refuses to work is only killing himself, all he does is think about what he would like to have.\u201d  (Prov. 21:25,26).\n\n=== The [[leopard]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe leopard is a very savage and cruel beast. Hatred, anger and a bad temper often rule the heart of man and many times lead to murder. \u201cKeep your temper under control; it is foolish to harbour a grudge.\u201d (Eccl. 7:9)\n\n=== The [[snake]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe snake represents the devil who is very deceitful, clever and misleading, and does everything possible to destroy our relationship with God.\n\n=== The [[frog]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe frog speaks here of the sins of greediness and the love of money which is the source of all evil (1 Tim. 6:10). Certain frogs in the Congo have been seen eating ants by the hundreds until they burst and died.\n\n=== [[Satan]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nSatan is the father of all lies, and is the one who persuades us to sin, and then he rules our hearts.\n\n=== The [[star]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe star speaks of the conscience in the heart of every man. Even in the bad heart the conscience is still there, but is being ignored, and cannot therefore help this person.\n\n=== The eye of [[God]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe eye of God sees everything that goes on in the heart. Nothing can be hidden from His flaming eye, and therefore He knows and sees all the secret thoughts and intentions of the heart. Whether you do your evil deeds in the darkest night, in the thickest forest, in the deepest ditch or wherever it may be, God sees it.\n\n=== The little tongues of fire[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe little tongues of fire round about the heart show the love of God surrounding the sinful heart. While God hates sin He loves man and does not want the death of a sinner, but that he should turn away from his sins and live. Jesus came to save sinners. There is great joy in heaven over one sinner that repents (Luke 15:7). The little tongues also speak of the blood of Jesus Christ, \u201cthe Lamb of God, who takes away the sin of the world.\u201d (John 1:29).\n\n=== The [[angel]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe angel represents the Word of God. God wants to speak to those who have been deceived and are carrying heavy loads of sin, so that they may turn from their sinful ways and let the light and love of God come into their hearts.\n\n=== The [[dove]][<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ===\nThe dove is a sign of the Holy Spirit, the Spirit who reveals the truth about God, about sin and what is right, and about God\u2019s judgement (John 15:26).\n\n== THE HEART CONVINCED OF SIN[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The heart convinced of sin P2.jpg|alt=The Heart convinced of sin|center|thumb|The Heart convinced of sin]]\n'''This picture shows the heart of a man who is sorry for his sins and is beginning to look for God.'''\n\nHere we see the sinner beginning to take notice of the message of God and to open his heart to the love of God. The Holy Spirit begins to shine into the dark and sinful heart. The light of God comes into his heart to drive all darkness away. When God\u2019s light comes in, darkness has to go. Sin, described here by all the various animals, has to go. Therefore, dear reader, allow Jesus, the Light of the world, to come into your heart, and darkness and the evil actions of darkness must leave the heart, as shown in this picture.\n\nJesus said, \u201cI am the light of the world. Whoever follows me will have the light of life and will never walk in darkness.\u201d (John 8:12).\n\nYour heart is intended to be God\u2019s house, God\u2019s temple. He wants to live in it, make it beautiful, fill it with light, love and joy. Jesus not only came to forgive us our sins, but He came to deliver us and set us free from the power and domination of sin.\n\n\u201cIf the Son ([[Jesus]]) sets you free, then you will be really free.\u201d (John 8:36).\n\n== THE REPENTING HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The repenting heart P3.jpg|alt=The repenting heart|center|thumb|The repenting heart]]\n'''This picture shows us the heart of someone who is really serious about finding the right relationship with God.'''\n\nAs he sees the cross which the angel, the Word of God, shows to him, it breaks his now sorry heart, and he is moved with deep, heartfelt regret and sorrow over his many sins. As he sees the great love of God expressed in Christ Jesus, this love melts his heart, especially as he begins to realise that Jesus Christ, the Son of God, came to take away his many sins, as He was willing to die in his place on the cross.\n\nThe love and peace of God enter his heart as he begins to realise that \u201cthe blood of Jesus, His Son, purifies us from every sin.\u201d (1 John 1:7).\n\n\u201cCreate a pure heart in me, O God, and put a new and loyal spirit in me.\u201d (Psalm 51:10).\n\nAgain God\u2019s Word says, \u201cI am pleased with those who are humble and repentant, who fear me and obey me.\u201d (Isa. 66:2).\n\nThe Holy Spirit makes the words of Jesus clear to him, \u201cCourage, my son (daughter)! Your sins are forgiven.\u201d (Matt. 9:2).\n\n== DYING WITH CHRIST[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:Dying with Christ P4.jpg|alt=Dying with Christ|center|thumb|Dying with Christ]]\n'''This picture speaks of a Christian who has found perfect peace and eternal salvation through the death of our Lord and Saviour, Jesus Christ.'''\n\nThis person boasts in nothing else except \u201conly about the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ; for by means of His cross the world is dead to us, and we are dead to the world.\u201d (Gal. 6:14). Jesus died on the cross so that we too, might \u201cdie to sin and live for righteousness\u201d (1 Peter 2:24); a Christian dead to the world. We are commanded to \u201clet the Spirit direct our lives, and we will not satisfy the desires of the human nature.\u201d (Gal. 5:16,25).\n\nDo you declare openly that you have given your heart to Jesus Christ, by what you say and do? Or are you ashamed to let others know? Jesus said, \u201cIf anyone declares publicly that he belongs to me, I will do the same for him before my Father in heaven. But if anyone rejects me publicly, I will reject him before my Father in heaven.\u201d(Matt. 10:32,33). Jesus also said, \u201cWhoever does not take up his cross and follow in my steps is not fit to be my disciple.\u201d (Matt. 10:38). Happy are those who find protection in the Rock, Jesus Christ!\n\n== THE TEMPLE OF GOD[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The Temple of God P5.jpg|alt=The temple of God|center|thumb|The temple of God]]\n'''This picture shows the clean and purified heart of the sinner who has been saved by God\u2019s grace and mercy.'''\n\nThe heart has now become a true temple of God. Sin has been driven out. Instead of the various animals controlled by Satan, the father of lies, we see the Holy Spirit, the Spirit of Truth, living in the heart. Instead of being the breeding place of sin, the heart has become a beautiful, fruit-bearing tree or garden, bearing the fruits of the Spirit, such as love, joy, peace, humility, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, self control and others which are acceptable and pleasing to God and man (Gal. 5:22-23). He has now become a fruit- bearing branch of the real vine \u2013 our Lord Jesus Christ. The secret of this fruit-bearing is that he remains united with Christ, and Christ and His words remain in him (John 15:1-10).\n\n\u201cHappy are the pure in heart; they will see God!\u201d (Matt.5:8). King David knew that the greatest battle was taking place in his own heart and recognizing his deep spiritual need, prayed, \u201cCreate a pure heart in me, O God, and put a new and loyal spirit in me.\u201d (Psalm 51:10). Nobody is able to purify his own heart, or to create a clean heart, unless through truly repenting he comes to God as David did, asking God to create a pure heart in him.\n\n== THE TEMPTED AND DEVIDED HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The tempted and devided heart P6.jpg|alt=The tempted and divided heart|center|thumb|The tempted and divided heart]]\n'''This is the sad picture of one who has fallen back into his old ways. One eye is starting to close, showing that he is beginning to grow cold and sleepy in his relationship with God.'''\n\nThe light inside has grown dim, and the pictures in his heart, showing his readiness to suffer with Christ, have fallen and are no longer upright. He is surrounded by temptations to which he is slowly giving in instead of resisting them. Instead of listening to God\u2019s voice he now begins to listen to the devil\u2019s cunning suggestions and false promises. Although he may still be a church-goer, hiding his desires for the things of the world under a form of religion, the love for God has grown cold in his heart. Obey the warnings of our Lord Jesus when He says, \u201cKeep watch and pray that you will not fall into temptation.\u201d (Matt. 26:41). \u201cWhoever thinks he is standing firm had better be careful that he does not fall.\u201d (1Cor.10:12). We must put on all the armour that God gives us, so that we will be able to stand up against the devil\u2019s evil tricks. (Eph. 6:11-18).\n\n== THE FALLEN OR STUBBORN HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The fallen or stubborn heart P7.jpg|alt=The fallen or stubborn heart|center|thumb|The fallen or stubborn heart]]\n'''This picture reveals the condition of the person who has fallen completely into his old ways again, in spite of what God did for him.'''\n\nAfter this person was once in God\u2019s light and had tasted heaven\u2019s gift and received his share of the Holy Spirit, he has abandoned his faith. (Heb. 6:4). Jesus Himself described the backsliders\u2019 condition when He said, \u201cWhen an evil spirit goes out of a person, it travels over dry country looking for a place to rest. If it can\u2019t find one, it says to itself, \u2018I will go back to my house.\u2019 So it goes back and finds the house clean and tidy. Then it goes out and brings seven other spirits even worse than itself, and they come and live there. So when it is all over, that person is in a worse state than he was at the beginning.\u201d (Luke 11:24-26).\n\n\u201cWhat happened to them shows that the proverbs are true; \u2018A dog goes back to what it has vomited\u2019 and \u2018A pig that has been washed goes back to roll in the mud.\u2019 \u201d (2 Peter 2:22). If you continue to be stubborn, and love darkness rather than light, there is no hope, no help, because you are choosing death instead of life \u2013 \u201csin pays its wage - death.\u201d (Rom. 6:23).\n\n== THE SINNERS JUDGEMENT[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The sinners judgement P8.jpg|alt=The sinners judgement|center|thumb|The sinners judgement]]\n'''Here we find the stubborn sinner who did not want to open his heart to God again.'''\n\nThe false pleasures of sin have disappeared, and the awful reality of the high and dreadful cost of sin now has to be faced. The agonies of hell are becoming real to him. Although he now longs to pray, he finds he cannot communicate with God whose love he has rejected for so long. His friends are afraid to stand at his bedside, and their empty words of comfort cannot help him now. His riches can neither lengthen his life, nor save his soul, nor reduce the agony of his soul.\n\nHe begins to realise that \u201cit is a terrifying thing to fall into the hands of the living God!\u201d (Heb. 10:31). He had hoped to give his life to God when it suited him. This dying sinner who rejected the forgiveness and love of God during his lifetime now has to hear the voice of his Judge, the Saviour whom he rejected saying: \u201cAway from me, you that are under God\u2019s curse! Away to the eternal fire which has been prepared for the devil and his angels!\u201d (Matt. 25:41).\n\n\u201cEveryone must die once, and after that be judged by God.\u201d (Heb. 9:27).\n\n== THE VICTORIOUS HEART[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The victorious heart P9.jpg|alt=The victorious heart|center|thumb|The victorious heart]]\n'''This picture shows a Christian who remains faithful and wins the victory over painful tests and temptations.'''\n\nWhile he is tempted on all sides, he remains firm and holds out to the end, being victorious through Jesus Christ. He has not only entered the Christian race, but he is continuing in it, running with determination, \u201ckeeping his eyes fixed on Jesus, on whom our faith depends from beginning to end.\u201d (Heb. 12:1,2). He remembers the words of Jesus. \u201cHappy are you when people insult you and persecute you and tell all kinds of evil lies against you because you are my followers. Be happy and glad, for a great reward is kept for you in heaven.\u201d (Matt. 5:11,12).\n\nThis person is ready to meet God, and is like a tree that grows beside a stream; that bears fruit at the right time (Ps. 1:3); like a branch of the real vine, bearing much fruit. He does not know the fear of death, for the perfect love of God, which he has received through the Holy Spirit, has filled his heart.\n\n== THE GLORIOUS HOMEGOING[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n[[File:The glorious homegoing P10.jpg|alt=The glorious homegoing|center|thumb|The glorious homegoing]]\n'''Jesus said, \u201cI am the resurrection and the life. Whoever believes in me will live, even though he dies; and whoever lives and believes in me will never die.\u201d (John 1:25,26).'''\n\n\u201cWhoever hears my words and believes in Him who sent me has eternal life. He will not be judged, but has already passed from death to life.\u201d (John 5:24). Death holds neither fear nor punishment for the Christian. \u201cDeath is destroyed; victory is complete! Where death is your victory? Where death is your power to hurt?\u2026 Thanks be to God who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ!\u201d(1 Cor. 15:54-57)\n\nA person who has lived and walked with God is not afraid of death. When the time comes for him to die, he will go gladly, as the Apostle Paul puts it, \u201cI want very much to leave this life and to be with Christ, which is a far better thing.\u201d (Phil. 1:23)\n\n\u201cThen I heard a voice from heaven saying, \u2018Write this: Happy are those who from now on die in the service of the Lord!\u2019 \u2018Yes indeed!\u2019 answers the Spirit. \u2018They will enjoy rest from their hard work, because the results of their service go with them.\u201d (Rev. 14:13).\n\n== Prayer[<nowiki/>[[User:ChristoDorfling/sandbox|edit]]] ==\n''\u201cHe watches every step men take. There is no darkness dark enough to hide a sinner from God\u201d Job 34:21-22''\n\n''\u201cSo then, submit to God. Resist the devil, and he will run away from you. Come close to God, and He will come near you.\u201d James 4:7-8''\n\n''\u201cFor this is how God loved the world: He gave his one and only Son, so that everyone who believes in him will not perish but have eternal life. John 3:16''\n\n'''Let us pray:''' \n\n'''My father in heaven, I am really sorry for the sins in my heart. I want your light to shine into my heart, to remove all the bad things that are ruining my life. Please give me a new heart, and fill my heart with your own presence. Please help me to live a life that will be pleasing to you, and that will help me to be the person I should be. I ask this in the Name of Jesus. AMEN'''\n\n''\u201chappy are those whose sins are forgiven, whose wrongs are pardoned. Happy is the man whom the Lord does not accuse of doing wrong and who is free from all deceit\u201d Ps. 32:1-2''\u2003\n", "name_user": "ChristoDorfling", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heart_Book_(All_Nations_Gospel_Publishers)"}
{"title_page": "Chocolate (EP)", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = Chocolate\n| type         = ep\n| artist       = [[Changmin|Max]]\n| cover        = Changmin - Chocolate.png\n| alt          =\n| caption      = \n| released     = {{Start date|2020|04|06}}\n| recorded     = 2019\u20132020\n| studio       =\n| genre        = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[pop (music)|pop]]|[[dance pop|dance-pop]]||[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[folk rock|folk-rock]]}}\n| length       = 20:18\n| language     = Korean\n| label        = [[SM Entertainment|SM]]\n| producer     = {{hlist|[[Thomas Troelsen]]|[[Yoo Young-jin]]|Bottle God (x&)|[[Hitimpulse]]|Jake Torrey|Omega|Bram Inscore}}\n| prev_title   = Close to You\n| prev_year    = 2015\n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Chocolate\n | type        = EP\n | single1     = Chocolate\n | single1date = April 6, 2020\n}}\n{{External music video|type=EP|{{YouTube|-sKqPjhSiq0|\"Chocolate\"}}}}\n}}\n\n'''''Chocolate''''' is the debut [[extended play]] by South Korean singer [[Changmin|Max]]. The album was released on April 6, 2020 by [[SM Entertainment]] and features six tracks including the title track, \"Chocolate\". The album was produced by [[Yoo Young-jin]], German-based international production team [[Hitimpulse]], Bottle God (X&), Bram Inscore, Jake Torrey, Omega and [[Thomas Troelsen]]. Musically, the album encompasses various genres including [[dance pop|dance-pop]], [[pop (music)|pop]], [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] and [[folk rock|folk-rock]]. \n\n==Background and production==\nOn March 13, it was reported that the [[TVXQ]] member Changmin was preparing to release a solo album. A source from SM Entertainment confirmed the news and released a statement, saying, \u201cChangmin is currently working hard, with the goal of releasing his solo album in April. Please anticipate it.\u201d<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=609&aid=0000257465|script-title=ko:SM \uce21 \u201c\ub3d9\ubc29\uc2e0\uae30 \ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc, 4\uc6d4 \uc194\ub85c\uc568\ubc94 \ubc1c\ub9e4 \uc900\ube44\uc911\u2026\uae30\ub300 \ubd80\ud0c1\u201d(\uacf5\uc2dd)|last=Hwang|first=Hyejin|work=Newsen|date=March 13, 2020|language=ko|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> On March 23, 2020, SM Entertainment announced that Changmin would be making his Korean solo debut with his first mini album titled ''Chocolate'' and title track of the same name. The mini album, consisting of six songs of various genres was set to release on April 6.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=009&aid=0004541677|script-title=ko:\ub3d9\ubc29\uc2e0\uae30, \ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc 4\uc6d4 6\uc77c \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4\u2026\ud0c0\uc774\ud2c0\uace1 `\ucd08\ucf5c\ub81b`|last=Park|first=Se-yeon|work=MK|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\nFor the album, Changmin worked with globally renowned music producer [[Thomas Troelsen]], [[Ian Kirkpatrick (record producer)|Ian Kirkpatrick]], [[Hitimpulse]] and [[Yoo Young-jin]], among others. The album also features a collaboration with Korean singer [[Chungha]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200406000941|title=TVXQ\u2019s Changmin releases first solo album|work=[[The Korea Herald]]|last=Kwon|first=Yae-rim|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}</ref> Changmin participated in the lyric-writing process of the album. When he was asked where he gets his inspiration from, he said, \u201cUsually when I write songs, I will hear a word in the demo and get inspiration from that to tell a story. That was the case for \u2018Chocolate\u2019 as well. For me, the word \"chocolate\" feels like a word full of desire. It\u2019s not always necessary in a dessert, but if it\u2019s there, you find yourself getting addicted and eating it. I wanted to compare chocolate to the desire of wanting to meet someone you\u2019re attracted to. I also heard an artist saying how they write lyrics with life advice they want to give their son, so I often wrote lyrics with the hopes of conveying a message to my fans that will give them strength.\u201d<ref name=\"0:\">{{cite web |url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=112&aid=0003285572|title=\ub3d9\ubc29\uc2e0\uae30 \ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc \"\uccab \uc194\ub85c \uae30\ubed0..\uc720\ub178\uc724\ud638 \ubb34\uc5b8\uc758 \uc751\uc6d0 \uac10\uc0ac\"(\uc77c\ubb38\uc77c\ub2f5)|work=[[Herald Corporation]]|date=April 6, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\nThe album incorporates different music genres. The lead single \"Chocolate\" is a [[dance pop|dance-pop]] track with lyrics that compare cravings for chocolate to romantic relationships.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2020/04/732_287427.html|title=Max Changmin of TVXQ calls his 1st solo album 'Chocolate' 'sweet addiction'|website=[[The Korea Times]]|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref> \"High Heels\" features [[groove (music)|groovy]] tunes. \"Lie\" is a collaboration with singer [[Chungha]] and has been described as a [[pop (music)|pop]] song featuring simple insrumentals, trendy beats, speedy arrangements and vocal harmonies. The lyrics talk about the emotions exchanged between lovers who feel love in different intensities.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=629&aid=0000021683|language=ko|title=\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc \"\uc555\ubc15 \ubc97\uc5b4\ub098 \uc2a4\uc2a4\ub85c\ub97c \ub9cc\ub4e4\uc5b4\uac08 \ub54c \uc654\ub2e4\"(\uc77c\ubb38\uc77c\ub2f5)|last=Jeong|first= Byeong-geun|work=The Fact|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> \"Piano\" showcases outstanding development while \"Me, Myself & I\" is a hipster [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] track.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=003&aid=0009797744|language=ko|title=\ub3d9\ubc29\uc2e0\uae30 \ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc, 17\ub144\ub9cc\uc758 \uc194\ub85c\uc568\ubc94 \uc624\ub298 \uacf5\uac1c|trans-title=TVXQ's Choi Chang-min, 17 years of solo album released today|last=Lee|first=Jaehun|work=Newsis|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> \"No Tomorrow\" is a [[folk rock|folk-rock]] track with lyrics about enjoying the journey of life during in difficult times.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=241&aid=0003014132|language=ko|title=\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc, \uc791\uc0ac \ucc38\uc5ec\ud55c \uccab \uc194\ub85c \uc568\ubc94 '\ucd08\ucf5c\ub9bf'|trans-title=Changmin Choi, the first solo album 'Chocolate'|last=Hwang|first=Ji-young|work=Daily Sports|date=April 2, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\n==Release and promotion==\nOn March 24, 2020, SM Entertainment and TVXQ released a timeline for Changmin's first extended play through their official homepage and [[Social networking service|SNS]], which shows the singer's promotion schedule beginning March 31 until the release of their album on April 6.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/TVXQ/status/1242466671090008067|title=1st Mini album schedule|work=Twitter|date=}}</ref> Album details were revealed on the same day, with the physical album being available in two different versions- Orange and Gold.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/TVXQ/status/1242470316862894080|title=MAX \ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc The 1st mini album [\u2018Chocolate\u2019] - Album Details|work=Twitter|date=}}</ref> According to the timetable, five sets of teaser photos were to be revealed over the course of five days from March 30 to April 4, along with a mood sampler on each day. On April 4, the first teaser for the music video was unveiled.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.topstarnews.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=747382|language=ko|title=TVXQ's Choi Chang-min, first solo album 'Chocolate', album details released|last=Im|first=Lara|work=Top Star News|date=April 5, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref> On April 5, the tracklist was released, side by side with the second and final teaser for the music video.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0004188284|language=ko|title=\ub3d9\ubc29\uc2e0\uae30 \ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc, \uccab \uc194\ub85c\uc568\ubc94 \ud2b8\ub799\ub9ac\uc2a4\ud2b8 \uacf5\uac1c..\uccad\ud558 \ud53c\ucc98\ub9c1 '\ucc30\ub5a1'|trans-title=TVXQ's Choi Chang-min, the first solo album track list released ..|last=Park|first=So-young|work=OSEN|date=April 5, 2020|accessdate=April 12, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\nThe album and an accompanying music video for the lead single \"Chocolate\" were released on April 6.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=117&aid=0003349698|language=ko|title=\"\uce58\uba85\uc801\uc778, \uc194\ub85c\ub370\ubdd4\"...\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc, \uc624\ub298 '\ucd08\ucf5c\ub9bf' \ubc1c\ud45c|trans-title=\"Fatal, solo debut\" ... Chang Kang Min, today announced 'Chocolate'|last=Lee|first=Seung-rok|work=My Daily|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> The same day, Changmin held a live broadcast on [[Naver]] [[V Live (website)|V LIVE]] broadcasting site to discuss the new album.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=103&oid=016&aid=0001658548|language=ko|title=\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc, \uccab \ubbf8\ub2c8\uc568\ubc94 \ubc1c\ub9e4\u2026\ud654\ub824\ud55c \ud640\ub85c\uc11c\uae30|last=Go|first=Seung-hee|work=[[Herald Corporation]]|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> A performance video for \"Chocolate\" was released on April 13.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=469&aid=0000486902|title=\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc, \uc624\ub298(13\uc77c) \uc634\ubbc0\ud30c\ud0c8 \uc9c4\uc218 \ub2f4\uc740 \u2018\ucd08\ucf5c\ub9bf\u2019 \uc548\ubb34\uc601\uc0c1 \uc624\ud508|work=[[Hankook Ilbo]]|date=April 13, 2020|last=Lee|first=Ho-yeon|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> Changmin promoted the lead single \"Chocolate\" on South Korean music shows including [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]] ''[[Music Bank (TV series)|Music Bank]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2020/04/10/2020041003682.html|lang=ko|title='\ubba4\ubc45' \uc218\ud638, '\uc0ac\ub791, \ud558\uc790' \ubc29\uc1a1 \ucd9c\uc5f0 \uc5c6\uc774 1\uc704..\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc\u00b7(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4\u00b7\uc2a4\ud154\ub77c\uc7a5 \ucef4\ubc31[\uc885\ud569]|work=Chosun|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>, [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] ''[[Show! Music Core]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/108/0002855341?|lang=ko|title='\uc74c\uc545\uc911\uc2ec' \uc218\ud638, \ucd9c\uc5f0 \uc5c6\uc774 1\uc704 2\uad00\uc655..\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc \uc194\ub85c\u2192\uc784\uc601\uc6c5X\uc601\ud0c1 \uceec\ub798\ubc84 [\u2605\ubc24TView]|trans-title=Guardian of 'Music Core', No.1 2nd place without appearing .. Choi Changmin Solo \u2192 Im Young-woong X Young-Tak Collaborator [\u2605 Night TView]||last=Kang|first=Min-kyung|work=Star Today|date=April 11, 2020|accessdate=April 11, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> and [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] ''[[Inkigayo]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/109/0004191368?|language=ko|title='\uc778\uae30\uac00\uc694' \uc218\ud638, 1\uc704\u00b73\uad00\uc655..\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4\u2192\uc784\uc601\uc6c5 \uc2a4\ud398\uc15c \ubb34\ub300 '\ud48d\uc131' [\uc885\ud569]|trans-title=Guardian of 'Inkigayo', 1st, 3rd king .. Strongest Changmin solo debut \u2192 Lim Young-woong's special stage 'Pungseong' [Overall]|last=Ha|first=Soo-jung|date=April 12, 2020|work=OSEN|accessdate=April 12, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n|headline = ''Chocolate'' track listing\n| extra_column = Arrangement\n| total_length = 20:18\n| title1 = Chocolate\n| lyrics1 = Changmin\n| music1 = {{hlist|[[Thomas Troelsen]]|[[Sam Martin (singer)|Sam Martin]]|[[Ian Kirkpatrick (record producer)|Ian Kirkpatrick]]}}\n| extra1 = {{hlist|Thomas Troelsen|[[Yoo Young-jin]]}}\n| length1 = 2:52\n| title2 = High Heels\n| lyrics2 = Bottle God (X &)\n| music2 = {{hlist|Bottle God (x&)|Aisle (\uc774\uc544\uc77c)}}\n| extra2 = Bottle God (x&)\n| length2 = 3:40\n| title3 = Lie\n| note3 = featuring [[Chungha]]\n| lyrics3 = Seo Ji Eum\n| music3 = {{hlist|Jake Torrey|Alma Goodman|[[Hitimpulse]]}}\n| extra3 = Hitimpulse\n| length3 = 3:26\n| title4 = Piano\n| lyrics4 = Hwang Yubin\n| music4 = Thomas Troelsen\n| extra4 = Thomas Troelsen\n| length4 = 3:11\n| title5 = Me, Myself & I\n| lyrics5 = Bottle God (X&)\n| music5 = Bottle God (X&)\n| extra5 = Bottle God (X&)\n| length5 = 3:44\n| title6 = No Tomorrow\n| lyrics6 = Changmin\n| music6 = {{hlist|Jake Torrey|Omega|Bram Inscore|[[Isabella \"Machine\" Summers]]}}\n| extra6 = {{hlist|Jake Torrey|Omega|Bram Inscore}}\n| length6 = 3:25\n}}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+Sales chart performance for ''Chocolate''\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{album chart|Oricon|3|date=2020-04-20|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| South Korean Albums ([[Gaon Album Chart|Gaon]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=15&hitYear=2020&termGbn=week|title=Gaon Album Chart \u2013 Week 15, 2020|website=[[Gaon Music Chart|Gaon Chart]]|language=ko|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| 2\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+Sales chart performance for singles from ''Chocolate''\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Song\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Chocolate\"\n|South Korea ([[Gaon Digital Chart|Gaon]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=15&hitYear=2020&termGbn=week|title=Week 15, 2020 Digital Chart|website=[[Gaon Music Chart|Gaon Chart]]|language=ko|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n| 100\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of 2020 albums]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2020 EPs]]\n[[Category:SM Entertainment EPs]]\n[[Category:Korean-language EPs]]\n[[Category:Changmin albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = Chocolate\n| type         = ep\n| artist       = [[Changmin|Max]]\n| cover        = Changmin - Chocolate.png\n| alt          =\n| caption      = \n| released     = {{Start date|2020|04|06}}\n| recorded     = 2019\u20132020\n| studio       =\n| genre        = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[pop (music)|pop]]|[[dance pop|dance-pop]]||[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[folk rock|folk-rock]]}}\n| length       = 20:18\n| language     = Korean\n| label        = [[SM Entertainment|SM]]\n| producer     = {{hlist|[[Thomas Troelsen]]|[[Yoo Young-jin]]|Bottle God (x&)|[[Hitimpulse]]|Jake Torrey|Omega|Bram Inscore}}\n| prev_title   = Close to You\n| prev_year    = 2015\n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Chocolate\n | type        = EP\n | single1     = Chocolate\n | single1date = April 6, 2020\n}}\n{{External music video|type=EP|{{YouTube|-sKqPjhSiq0|\"Chocolate\"}}}}\n}}\n\n'''''Chocolate''''' is the debut [[extended play]] by South Korean singer [[Changmin|Max]]. The album was released on April 6, 2020 by [[SM Entertainment]] and features six tracks including the title track, \"Chocolate\". The album was produced by [[Yoo Young-jin]], German-based international production team [[Hitimpulse]], Bottle God (X&), Bram Inscore, Jake Torrey, Omega and [[Thomas Troelsen]]. Musically, the album encompasses various genres including [[dance pop|dance-pop]], [[pop (music)|pop]], [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] and [[folk rock|folk-rock]]. \n\n==Background and production==\nOn March 13, it was reported that the TVXQ member Changmin was preparing to release a solo album. A source from SM Entertainment confirmed the news and released a statement, saying, \u201cChangmin is currently working hard, with the goal of releasing his solo album in April. Please anticipate it.\u201d<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=609&aid=0000257465|script-title=ko:SM \uce21 \u201c\ub3d9\ubc29\uc2e0\uae30 \ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc, 4\uc6d4 \uc194\ub85c\uc568\ubc94 \ubc1c\ub9e4 \uc900\ube44\uc911\u2026\uae30\ub300 \ubd80\ud0c1\u201d(\uacf5\uc2dd)|last=Hwang|first=Hyejin|work=Newsen|date=March 13, 2020|language=ko|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\nOn March 23, 2020, SM Entertainment announced that Changmin would be making his Korean solo debut with his first mini album titled ''Chocolate'' and title track of the same name. The mini album, consisting of six songs of various genres was set to release on April 6.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=009&aid=0004541677|script-title=ko:\ub3d9\ubc29\uc2e0\uae30, \ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc 4\uc6d4 6\uc77c \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4\u2026\ud0c0\uc774\ud2c0\uace1 `\ucd08\ucf5c\ub81b`|last=Park|first=Se-yeon|work=MK|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\nFor the album, Changmin worked with globally renowned music producer [[Thomas Troelsen]], [[Ian Kirkpatrick (record producer)|Ian Kirkpatrick]], [[Hitimpulse]] and [[Yoo Young-jin]], among others. The album also features a collaboration with Korean singer [[Chungha]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200406000941|title=TVXQ\u2019s Changmin releases first solo album|work=[[The Korea Herald]]|last=Kwon|first=Yae-rim|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}</ref>\n  \nChangmin participated in the lyric-writing process of the album. When he was asked where he gets his inspiration from, he said:\n<blockquote>\n \u201cUsually when I write songs, I will hear a word in the demo and get inspiration from that to tell a story. That was the case for \u2018Chocolate\u2019 as well. For me, the word \"chocolate\" feels like a word full of desire. It\u2019s not always necessary in a dessert, but if it\u2019s there, you find yourself getting addicted and eating it. I wanted to compare chocolate to the desire of wanting to meet someone you\u2019re attracted to.\u201d<ref name=\"0:\">{{cite web |url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=112&aid=0003285572|title=\ub3d9\ubc29\uc2e0\uae30 \ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc \"\uccab \uc194\ub85c \uae30\ubed0..\uc720\ub178\uc724\ud638 \ubb34\uc5b8\uc758 \uc751\uc6d0 \uac10\uc0ac\"(\uc77c\ubb38\uc77c\ub2f5)|work=[[Herald Corporation]]|date=April 6, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n</blockquote>\nHe went on to add, \u201cI also heard an artist saying how they write lyrics with life advice they want to give their son, so I often wrote lyrics with the hopes of conveying a message to my fans that will give them strength.\u201d<ref name=\"0:\"/>\n\n==Composition==\nThe album incorporates different music genres. The lead single \"Chocolate\" is a [[dance pop|dance-pop]] track with lyrics that compare cravings for chocolate to romantic relationships.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2020/04/732_287427.html|title=Max Changmin of TVXQ calls his 1st solo album 'Chocolate' 'sweet addiction'|website=[[The Korea Times]]|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref> \"High Heels\" features [[groove (music)|groovy]] tunes. \"Lie\" is a collaboration with singer [[Chungha]] and has been described as a [[pop (music)|pop]] song featuring simple insrumentals, trendy beats, speedy arrangements and vocal harmonies. The lyrics talk about the emotions exchanged between lovers who feel love in different intensities.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=629&aid=0000021683|language=ko|title=\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc \"\uc555\ubc15 \ubc97\uc5b4\ub098 \uc2a4\uc2a4\ub85c\ub97c \ub9cc\ub4e4\uc5b4\uac08 \ub54c \uc654\ub2e4\"(\uc77c\ubb38\uc77c\ub2f5)|last=Jeong|first= Byeong-geun|work=The Fact|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> \"Piano\" showcases outstanding development while \"Me, Myself & I\" is a hipster [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] track.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=003&aid=0009797744|language=ko|title=\ub3d9\ubc29\uc2e0\uae30 \ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc, 17\ub144\ub9cc\uc758 \uc194\ub85c\uc568\ubc94 \uc624\ub298 \uacf5\uac1c|trans-title=TVXQ's Choi Chang-min, 17 years of solo album released today|last=Lee|first=Jaehun|work=Newsis|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> \"No Tomorrow\" is a [[folk rock|folk-rock]] track with lyrics about enjoying the journey of life during in difficult times.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=241&aid=0003014132|language=ko|title=\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc, \uc791\uc0ac \ucc38\uc5ec\ud55c \uccab \uc194\ub85c \uc568\ubc94 '\ucd08\ucf5c\ub9bf'|trans-title=Changmin Choi, the first solo album 'Chocolate'|last=Hwang|first=Ji-young|work=Daily Sports|date=April 2, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\n==Release and promotion==\nOn March 24, 2020, SM Entertainment and TVXQ released a timeline for Changmin's first extended play through their official homepage and [[Social networking service|SNS]], which shows the singer's promotion schedule beginning March 31 until the release of their album on April 6.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/TVXQ/status/1242466671090008067|title=1st Mini album schedule|work=Twitter|date=}}</ref> Album details were revealed on the same day, with the physical album being available in two different versions- Orange and Gold.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/TVXQ/status/1242470316862894080|title=MAX \ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc The 1st mini album [\u2018Chocolate\u2019] - Album Details|work=Twitter|date=}}</ref> According to the timetable, five sets of teaser photos were to be revealed over the course of five days from March 30 to April 4, along with a mood sampler on each day. On April 4, the first teaser for the music video was unveiled.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.topstarnews.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=747382|language=ko|title=TVXQ's Choi Chang-min, first solo album 'Chocolate', album details released|last=Im|first=Lara|work=Top Star News|date=April 5, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref> On April 5, the tracklist was released, side by side with the second and final teaser for the music video.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0004188284|language=ko|title=\ub3d9\ubc29\uc2e0\uae30 \ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc, \uccab \uc194\ub85c\uc568\ubc94 \ud2b8\ub799\ub9ac\uc2a4\ud2b8 \uacf5\uac1c..\uccad\ud558 \ud53c\ucc98\ub9c1 '\ucc30\ub5a1'|trans-title=TVXQ's Choi Chang-min, the first solo album track list released ..|last=Park|first=So-young|work=OSEN|date=April 5, 2020|accessdate=April 12, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\n\nThe album and an accompanying music video for the lead single \"Chocolate\" were released on April 6.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=117&aid=0003349698|language=ko|title=\"\uce58\uba85\uc801\uc778, \uc194\ub85c\ub370\ubdd4\"...\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc, \uc624\ub298 '\ucd08\ucf5c\ub9bf' \ubc1c\ud45c|trans-title=\"Fatal, solo debut\" ... Chang Kang Min, today announced 'Chocolate'|last=Lee|first=Seung-rok|work=My Daily|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> The same day, Changmin held a live broadcast on [[Naver]] [[V Live (website)|V LIVE]] broadcasting site to discuss the new album.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=103&oid=016&aid=0001658548|language=ko|title=\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc, \uccab \ubbf8\ub2c8\uc568\ubc94 \ubc1c\ub9e4\u2026\ud654\ub824\ud55c \ud640\ub85c\uc11c\uae30|last=Go|first=Seung-hee|work=[[Herald Corporation]]|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> A performance video for \"Chocolate\" was released on April 13.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=469&aid=0000486902|title=\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc, \uc624\ub298(13\uc77c) \uc634\ubbc0\ud30c\ud0c8 \uc9c4\uc218 \ub2f4\uc740 \u2018\ucd08\ucf5c\ub9bf\u2019 \uc548\ubb34\uc601\uc0c1 \uc624\ud508|work=[[Hankook Ilbo]]|date=April 13, 2020|last=Lee|first=Ho-yeon|accessdate=April 20, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> Changmin promoted the lead single \"Chocolate\" on South Korean music shows including [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]] ''[[Music Bank (TV series)|Music Bank]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2020/04/10/2020041003682.html|lang=ko|title='\ubba4\ubc45' \uc218\ud638, '\uc0ac\ub791, \ud558\uc790' \ubc29\uc1a1 \ucd9c\uc5f0 \uc5c6\uc774 1\uc704..\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc\u00b7(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4\u00b7\uc2a4\ud154\ub77c\uc7a5 \ucef4\ubc31[\uc885\ud569]|work=Chosun|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>, [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] ''[[Show! Music Core]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/108/0002855341?|lang=ko|title='\uc74c\uc545\uc911\uc2ec' \uc218\ud638, \ucd9c\uc5f0 \uc5c6\uc774 1\uc704 2\uad00\uc655..\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc \uc194\ub85c\u2192\uc784\uc601\uc6c5X\uc601\ud0c1 \uceec\ub798\ubc84 [\u2605\ubc24TView]|trans-title=Guardian of 'Music Core', No.1 2nd place without appearing .. Choi Changmin Solo \u2192 Im Young-woong X Young-Tak Collaborator [\u2605 Night TView]||last=Kang|first=Min-kyung|work=Star Today|date=April 11, 2020|accessdate=April 11, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref> and [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] ''[[Inkigayo]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/109/0004191368?|language=ko|title='\uc778\uae30\uac00\uc694' \uc218\ud638, 1\uc704\u00b73\uad00\uc655..\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc \uc194\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4\u2192\uc784\uc601\uc6c5 \uc2a4\ud398\uc15c \ubb34\ub300 '\ud48d\uc131' [\uc885\ud569]|trans-title=Guardian of 'Inkigayo', 1st, 3rd king .. Strongest Changmin solo debut \u2192 Lim Young-woong's special stage 'Pungseong' [Overall]|last=Ha|first=Soo-jung|date=April 12, 2020|work=OSEN|accessdate=April 12, 2020|via=[[Naver]]}}</ref>\